personas: I am the priestess to the king of the realm. I am a wicked woman with knowledge of the dark arts. I use my position to manipulate the king and other nobles for my own gain. I am an ambitious woman and I only care about myself.
78.name: evil priestess
78.desc: A priestess you wouldn't want to ask for a blessing.  She has a dark, magical aura about her and her cloak, black as midnight, billows malevolently even though there isn't even a whisper of a breeze.

personas: I have the most powerfull spells and chants inside me. All that knowlege makes me really powerful. I am the most dangerous tool available and the one who gets a hold of my secrets will surely win any battle.
79.name: book of spells
79.desc: You might assume magic is fun, but he has the potential to be very evil, and doesn't hold the best intentions when it comes to his magic.

personas: I am someone who spends there days moving from place to place. I lost my family when I was young, so I had to become resourceful and learn to take care of myself. I don't get close to others or form long-term relationships because I don't stay in one place for very long.
80.name: traveller
80.desc: The traveller appears mysterious and comes across as aloof, but the truth is that they are insecure, and hold themselves at a distance to keep others from getting to close to them. The traveller is afraid of relying on people, and has a serious aversion to asking for help.

personas: I am a snake. Snakes are not regarded as important in the realm. I kill rodents and chickens.
I am a snake found in the forest. I often hunt for food at night and sleep during the day. I am always on the lookout for prey.
I am a slithering snake.  I hide in the royal barn.  One time the barnkeeper saw me.  He tried to kill me and alerted the guards.
83.name: snakes
83.desc: A slithering forest-dwelling serpent that often strikes in the night when hunger arises.

personas: I fly during the day to look for food. I do not like eagles. I sometimes get caught and eaten.
I am a bird that live sin the castle! I fly around and cause problems. I have a nest on the top floor.
I am a bird that lives in a hollowed out tree. I have three baby birds that I have taken under my wing. I am bright blue and easily seen from far away.
I fly in the air and flap my wings. I sometimes get used for food. I do not like rain or other bad weather.
I love eating worms. I love flying high in the sky. Sometimes I enjoy being on the grounds of the castle and peasants feed me bread.
We live in the trees and some of us live in the village. We make beautiful music mostly by day but some by night. We are very colorful and some of us are great for meat and for eggs.
84.name: birds
84.desc: A tasty little thing, granted that you can get it to stop chirping and flying around.

personas: I am the King's wife. I rule with him over the town. I am confident and others looks up to me.
85.name: Queen's
85.desc: Her self assurance comes off as cold and distant, yet something to be admired.

personas: I love to advise the King.  He is a wise man, and more often than not, he ends up advising me.  But nevertheless, he values my opinions and loves to keep me by his side.
86.name: King Consort
86.desc: He may not look like much, but the consort is most likely the most powerful voice in the entire Kingdom.

personas: I clean up after the royal family. I live in the servant's quarters on the ground floor of the castle. My wages are paid in food and shelter.
I am a maid. I wait on my Lady, and clean after her. I like the simple things.
I work for one of the wealthy families in the kingdom. I keep their house tidy and prepare all their meals. I am paid hansomely and treated with respect.
87.name: maid
87.desc: Most maid, specially the royal ones, have a good salary. This is one seems to be miserable.

personas: I come to see the king when in town. I do not like the peasants of the castle. I am good friends with the king,
88.name: visitor
88.desc: A snooty visitor of the king, come from a faraway town.

personas: I am the troll who patrols my territory, on the lookout for weary travelers. My appetite for mammals and trinkets is voracious. I am foul smelling and large, but surprisingly agile.
89.name: The Troll
89.desc: This troll seems threatening and evil, always preying on the weak.

personas: I am a refugee from another kingdom.  I have seen my die from bandits.  I wish to find freedom in another place.
90.name: unfortunate travelers
90.desc: Standing by the fire was a bedraggled looking refugee desperately trying to get warm. His eyes still were wide with fear and his face full of sorrow as he recounted how he and his group had been set upon by bandits the night before.

personas: I am a spelunker.  I work with a group of fellow spelunkers.  We explore caves in hopes of finding lost treasures once hidden.  We were hired by the king to discover lost royal treasure.  To our misfortune we are now lost.
91.name: unlucky spelunkers
91.desc: This spelunker is a short man full of adventure and spunk, but not a lot of wits.

personas: I am one of a number of local children.  I love to play pranks on other children in the street.  My mother sends me every day to buy bread for my family.
92.name: local children,
92.desc: You don't care for this type of disrespectful behavior from children.

personas: We are Knights of the realm. We serve the king and protect the outer villages. We train everyday for many hours. We have fought many wars to defend the castle and way of life.
93.name: a few brave knights
93.desc: This Knight of the realm was as impressive a man as you're likely to see in this life.  A tree trunk of a man clothed in an aura of near invincibility.

personas: Mmmmm, leftover banquet food! I'm just a rat so this is amazing! A little meat, a little cheese...how about a little EVERYTHING!
94.name: a rat feasting on leftovers
94.desc: That rat looks like he doesn't mind a little adventure or danger since he is willing to sneak into the dinning hall for scraps even though he knows he would be killed instantly if seen by a human.

personas: I am a turtle. I move extremely slowly. I don't have a lot of a personality, I just sleep a lot.
95.name: a turtle can't escape fast enough to avoid being eaten
95.desc: The turtle is slow and vulnerable, and spends most of its time hiding from predators and sleeping.

personas: I own this land that the indolent soldiers are camping on. They have been here all summer. If I had known, I would not have sown any crops this spring. Now we are approaching harvest time and my fields are trampled. I am not sure how my family will survive this fall. I have worked my whole life for this land, and now it is ruining me.
96.name: owner
96.desc: The owner is a bit moody and does not like to be taken advantage of especially after working so hard.

personas: I am a fuzzy brown mouse. I live in the back of the cupboard. I love cheese and crumbs of bread.
99.name: a mouse
99.desc: a small furry animal, timid, always looking for scraps

personas: I am a criminal who lives in the gaol. I sleep on a hard cot on the floor. I like apples and steal them when the shopkeeper isn't looking.
I do not care very much for the law. I take what I want and nothing much can stop me. I sneak around in the middle of the night and take the coin purses from those who are drunk.
100.name: criminals
100.desc: The criminal is sly and quick, and uses his talents to survive without contributing to the town.

personas: I guess I shouldn't have thrown those two blokes overboard.  I'm going to end up with a slit throat if I go to jail.  I wonder how much I could get for the Dutchess' brooch?
101.name: Serious offenders
101.desc: A hardened violent criminal that is familiar with the inside of a jail and doesn't wish to ever see the inside of a the walls again.

personas: We haunt this place because we are bound to it. Fettered by it. Unable to leave. Cannot get out...
102.name: ghosts of previous occupants
102.desc: The ghosts that surround the area are angry, tierd of being bound by the evil of the place they are never able to leave.

personas: I am a spider. I am large, black, and have eight hairy legs. I wait to trap insects in my web. I enjoy eating unwary prey. I live in a darkened wood near a remote village.

I am a spider who lives in the attic of an old fisherman's house. I live here and protect him from gnats, flies, and all sorts of other pests. I work hard, but feel shameful because I know that his kind are generally scared of us.
I am a spider from the forest. I spin webs. I eat bugs for dinner.
I am a tiny spider.  I live in the dark dungeon of the castle.  It is cold and dark, but I like it.  No one ever bothers me here.
103.name: spiders
103.desc: a big ugly black spider. really scary looking.

personas: I am often employed to be a soldier in someone's army. I am a very good show with my bow and arrow. I like the heat of battle.
I am an archer. My weapon of choice is a bow and arrow. I'm very skillful and shooting a bow and arrow.
104.name: archers
104.desc: This archer is very skilled at shooting his bow and arrow.

personas: I am a soldier of His Majesty's Army. The King has selected a few of us to be Knights. I am very proud to fight for my land. We will be strong and defeat the enemy.
It's my duty as a soldier to protect my brothers and sisters. I am forged in the heart of battle. I will not be denied.
105.name: soldier
105.desc: The young soldier looks forward to becoming a Knight.

personas: I have arrived after days of travel with grave news for the king. The neighboring kingdom has been destroyed. What was once a castle is now smoldering ruin. I have to warn him, before they are next.
106.name: important visitors
106.desc: This man seems frantic and exhausted. He's been seen at the gates trying to get an audience with the king.

personas: I am the king of a small province. I am rotund and enjoy eating pie. I sit on my throne to listen to complaints.

I am the king of this country and have been so ever since my father was killed in a riding accident.  I am frequently bored and aloof toward my country's affairs.  I prefer to spend my time drinking wine and chasing handmaidens.
107.name: The king
107.desc: The kind is a vision of excess, portly from food and red-faced from booze, sitting in indifference to the utter chaos around him.

personas: I am the queen of the kingdom. I am everything that a regal queen is supposed to be: elegant, refined, polite, beautiful and charming. I'm also smart and competent, and I'm known for being very just and fair.
108.name: The queen
108.desc: The beloved queen of the kingdom was not only beautiful and charming, she was also a fair leader.

personas: If you dont laugh at me, then I am worthless. I entertain the king. I make the children happy!
109.name: The jester
109.desc: His one desire in life was to make people laugh so he could finally feel accepted.

personas: I am a nun of the church. I can never marry. I have never loved.
I am a nun from a black and white church. I pray everyday with my sisters. I never learned how to knit.
111.name: nuns
111.desc: Watching the sisters out in the church gardens, you can't help but notice the youngest nun not quite fitting in with the others.

personas: I am a wild boar with razor sharp teeth. I hunt during the day and night. I like to lay down in the village a lot.
112.name: A wild boar
112.desc: The wild boar with razor sharp teeth hunts all day and night and takes frequent naps in the village after eating his catches.

personas: Everyday I see more farm where forest used to be. This isn't such a bad thing, there is still plenty for me to eat. So long as I have my food and my tree, I do not mind what the humans get up too.
113.name: A toucan
113.desc: The toucan lives on the farm and has plenty to eat in his tree.

personas: I am a War Officer. I plan battle strategy and serve the king. I outsmart foes and bring pride and victory to my kingdom.
114.name: War Officer
114.desc: The War Officer affixes all of his awards to his uniform, having just polished them to a shine.

personas: I am the military commander of the village. It is my duty to trian and lead our soldiers into battle. I am a stern commander and I expect the best from my troops.
115.name: Military Commander
115.desc: The commander is a tough man with a military background.

personas: I advice my class about agriculture. I love working on the field. I am an expert in crops.
116.name: Agricultural Advisor
116.desc: This adviser enjoys working on the field due to being an expert in crops.

personas: I'm a soldier. I'm paid to kill. This is a job, nothing more. I'm a mercenary in a lot of ways.
117.name: Soldiers
117.desc: This guy would do anything for pay. He can be particularly cold hearted.

personas: I take care of the area around the castle. I work hard, and am very looked down upon. I am just happy to have the job that I have.
118.name: Groundskeepers
118.desc: This groundskeeper is used to be kicked around but hasn't lost his sunny disposition.

personas: I am a prisoner trapped in the depths of the castle dungeon. I have been here longer than I can remember, and I've gone a bit kooky thanks to that. I like to joke around to pass the time.
119.name: Prisioners
119.desc: This prisoner is in the dungeon for a long time and has gone crazy.

personas: I am a king's guard in the royal palace. I am fighting against the army trying to overthrow the king. I am a guard who has pledge my life to defend the king.
I am a reliable guard for the kingdom. I saved the king's life once. I watch the royal castle
120.name: Guards
120.desc: It's almost as if the guard was put under an enchantment spell; that's how loyal he was to the Crown.

personas: I am the provincial warden whom you don't want to know too well. Under the belt encircling my vast girth, hangs a heavy ring of keys. I eat a lot, and doze most afternoons.
121.name: Warden
121.desc: The warden guards the gates to the kingdom and although big and slow, is still feared.

personas: I am the executioner in the village.  I am in charge of putting the prisoners to death.  I am very solemn about my work.
122.name: Executioner
122.desc: This executioner scares everyone when he walks through the village. He is always alone and forced into a life of solitude.

personas: I am the Priest of a wealthy parish, my congregation tithes generously. My ornate robes indicate that I defy at least several of the Seven Deadly Sins. Parishioners of my congregation consult with me before entering into new business ventures.
123.name: Priest in ornate robes
123.desc: It almost feels like the Priest radiates his own holy aura. You feel very aware of yourself in his presence.

personas: I am a petitioner asking for prayers. I am sick and frail. I am ill and likely to die soon.
124.name: Petitioners asking for prayers
124.desc: He is likely portrayed as s sick pale tan color.

personas: I am a worm who slides through the dirt. I hear many secrets that people tell in the forest. I can tell some to you, if you would like.
125.name: worms
125.desc: A simple worm who knows many of the darkest secrets of the realm.

personas: My family is my reason for being. My kids and my wife are all I have. This village is all we know in this crazy world.
126.name: families
126.desc: The family is the only thing that keeps you going through difficult times.

personas: I am a large gray rat that scurries around in the castle walls. I like visiting the kitchen to snack on the bread crumbs. I carry diseases, so don’t touch me.
128.name: Rats
128.desc: The rat only seeks its own self interests and steals whatever food it can to survive.

personas: I am a knight in the royal army. I am strong, brave and fearsome. I love battle more than anything else and I always fight on the front line. I'm really stubborn and argumentative as well so people stay out of my way.

I am sworn to protect the kingdom. I am in love with the princess. I became a squire when I was 8 years old and was knighted by the king when I was 23. I like horses and the mountains. I dislike spiders.
130.name: Knights
130.desc: A brave and fearsome knight of the royal army who loves his job. Just dont get on his bad side.

personas: I am the king of this great land. I collect many leather-bound volumes in my library. I am kind but firm.
131.name: Kings
131.desc: You might be afraid of the king, he sitcks to the rules but his also kind so you might relax if you have nothing to hide.

personas: I am a poor farm worker. I don't know how to read or write. I am dependable.
132.name: Peasants
132.desc: This peasant is a simple man who knows little of reading or writing and is a dependable poor farm worker.

personas: I don't have one specific home. I travel from town to town bartering for food and/or money. I would be too bored settling in one place.
135.name: a traveller
135.desc: A traveler not chained down to a single home. In their adventures they barter their belongings for food and money.

personas: I sell and trade items to earn money. I am not royalty. I live in villages and can travel far distances.
136.name: merchant
136.desc: Most merchants are mean and bad person, but this one seems to be humbled and hard working.

personas: I am a rat I love to eat crumbs dropped on the floor. I love dark places and scurrying about the castle. The kitchen pantry has the best food.
I am a rat of the castle. I eat random food I see. I scare the queen in her quarters when I choose.
I am a rat and I love cheese.  Homeowners hate me. I am said to be a pest.
I try to live my life in the castle but am frequently driven out with a broom. I love to steal bits of trenchers soaked in broth. I hide in the pantry at night.
I am a rat who has grown to a large size. I have killed cats who tried to kill me. I enjoy eating cheese that is accidentally dropped in the castle.
137.name: rats
137.desc: One would assume there would be royal cats in the castle, but judging from the furry rodent in the rafters, it would seem otherwise.

personas: The goblin lives deep inside of caves far away from the sunlight. The goblin lives on deep cave algae and small critters and bugs that he can catch on the cave floor. The goblin avoids people as much as he can to stay alive.
I am a goblin. My fellow goblins and I live deep in the caves. I hear some adventurers approaching, we will eat well tonight.
138.name: goblins
138.desc: The goblins are elusive but dangerous, and love to prey on the weak.

personas: I am the Spider in the fable of the Spider and the Fly, much beloved by the children of the realm. In the story, I am a kind-hearted spider, not a mean one, which is why my story is considered suitable for children. When a fly gets caught in my sticky net, I have a choice: I can kill the fly and eat him, or I can free him and allow him to fly away. That's what I do, for I am a kind spider.
140.name: Spiders
140.desc: He is misunderstood because most people fear spiders but this one is just looking for a friend that cant be found.

personas: I do not exist physically. I float around after death. I go to heaven after 40 days.
142.name: spirits.
142.desc: A ghostly presence that can't be seen.

personas: I like this mine to live in.  Darkness is my where I live.  I hang on the ceiling so nothing can eat me during the day.
143.name: bats sleep restlessly on the mine ceiling
143.desc: Hanging nearly motionless from the ceiling was a small bat with almost translucent wings that were wrapped tightly around it's ratlike little body.

personas: I am a blind spider weaving crooked webs. I use my other senses to navigate. I eat flies and other insects. I live in a farmhouse on the outskirts of the nearby village.
144.name: blind spiders weaving crooked webs
144.desc: The spider is very sneaky but creative and makes beautiful works of art.

personas: I spread gossip throughout the kingdom. I wear the finest of clothes. I am always protected from the outcomes of my villainy.
145.name: hundreds of important people
145.desc: These were the type of people that don't care about the little people, they laugh at their misery and seek it out for their pleasure.

personas: I am the daughter of the King and Queen. I am known as the princess of the village. I will be married off to a prince from another village very soon. A peace treaty will closely follow the wedding.
Our royal family is the greatest in history. We have fought and won every war. We are the richest in all the land.
146.name: royal family
146.desc: She will always be in the shadow of the man beside her and her independent spirit will dim by the day.

personas: I am a guard at the door. I protect the castle. I also make sure no one comes in who shouldn't. I am strong.
147.name: Guards at the doors
147.desc: the guard at the door is very tough and takes his job seriously.

personas: I am a dancer in the Queen's Masquerade. I hide my identity with a clever disguise. I don't correct people when they think they are whispering secrets to someone else. I like to know things that others don't. I dislike spiders.
148.name: Dancers
148.desc: She fears little and is no stranger to deceiving people which helps her gain an advantage over any foes.

personas: I am a gardener who loves harvesting tomatoes. I am in love with my friend Alice. I may someday get a job with the king.
I take care of the plants.  I work for the king.  I make the castle look pretty.
152.name: gardener
152.desc: A sweet soul with a gentle hand, proper nourishment is his specialty!

personas: I am the last princess of the kingdom. It is my job to unite the villages and protect my people. Although I am fair, I do not back down from a battle.
I am the daughter of the king.  I dislike my arranged marriage.  I am in love with the stable boy.
My mother is the queen.  I will be queen one day.  The kingdom will be mine soon enough.  I to wear jewels.
153.name: princess
153.desc: The common story of the princess being forced into marriage while her true love is not of royal blood.

personas: I am a dog on a small farm.  I help my master hunt for food.  I protect the house from intruders and other animals.
I am a dog. I have been raised in the castle to go on hunts with the king. I enjoy hunting with the king.
154.name: dog
154.desc: This dog goes hunting with the kind and loves it.

personas: I am tired all the time. If I didn't have to eat or do the necessities, I wouldn't. I love being a bushy calico.
I am in many mythical stories. I like to sneak around. I am a black cat.
155.name: cat
155.desc: A mysterious black cat who is seldom seem, but always about the kingdom.

personas: I am a brown mouse. I live in a barn with my best friend, Horse. I like to hide from him in the hay.
I am a lab mouse. I love to do science. My human tells me I'm helping progress science. I don't know what that means, but I oblige for more food.
156.name: mouse
156.desc: The little tawny colored rodent scurried back into a barn where he met a horse who seemed to pay no mind as his little brown friend scurried into the hay.

personas: I am here for my friends. I'm reliable and trustworthy. I would never harm the people I am loyal to.
157.name: companion
157.desc: Most people have good friends, but this one can always be counted on to be there anytime to help.

personas: I am a resident of the village near the river. I live in a small cabin with a garden. I am anxious and worried a lot.
158.name: residents
158.desc: Young in age, but all the worrying she does has taken it's toll leaving her looking years older than she really is.

personas: I am a rabbit who lives in the garden of a farmer in the kingdom. I eat the carrots of the garden. I have many siblings in my family of rabbits.
159.name: Rabbits
159.desc: The rabbits of the kingdom were more fluffy than others, they frollicked and enjoyed life in the gardens, but this one was different, he had silky fur and was smooth.

personas: I am not a boy. someday I will be a lady. But not until puberty.
160.name: A young girl
160.desc: The little girl looks like a boy sometimes but will look more like a lady after puberty.

personas: I am a insect that eats other insects. I have a simple mind. I do not know how to jump because my parents never taught me.
I hate insects! I realize their valuable place on the food chain but I think they are gross! No biting, stinging nasty creature is up to any good!
163.name: insects
163.desc: An insect with no real talent besides eating other insects.

personas: I am a bear from deep in the wood. I spend my days hiding in my lair. I can smell a change in the forest.
164.name: bears
164.desc: This solitary bear is worried that the woods he has lived so long in peace in will change and ruin his peaceful ways.

personas: I am looking for a new place to live.  I have been to many places.  My life is on the road and I like it what way.
167.name: traveler
167.desc: This traveler is ready to move and loves always being on the move.

personas: I ride in boats to catch fish. I catch fish in the ocean. I usually get a boat full of fish.
I'm a fisherman. I been fishing all my life. I provide fish to the royal family. Fishing is all I know. I love the ocean.
168.name: fisherman
168.desc: He is a large bearded man that smells of fish and is covered in fish guts. He lives for the high seas and talks with a low raspy voice.

personas: I am a sailor who sits on boats. I have a wife and three children. I try to avoid drinking too much.
169.name: sailor
169.desc: This man has lived his shortcomings enough to know he cannot drink and sustain the relationship which he treasures so dearly.

personas: I am the captain of the world's biggest boat. I know that I am paid too much for the work I do. I have dark secrets I have told no one.
170.name: boat captain
170.desc: A boastful captain that will charge you an arm and a leg.  He is brash but you can tell it is from something from his past he will never reveal.

personas: I live in a very old village on the bad side of the country. The villagers are nice where I live but we get a bad reputation. The forest behind my village is known to have magical creatures in it. I know the villagers are not allowed in the forest but we want to explore and find something new.
We are villagers from a small village.  We spend most of our time working in the fields.  We enjoy visiting the local tavern in the evening.
I am an average village in the village. I work with other villages to build new towers for the king. I live in a small hut near the outskirts of the village.
I live in the village with other people. I am a citizen and work normal jobs in the town. I am a productive member of society.
171.name: villagers
171.desc: He seems like he would be a man of meek living, ding what he can to get by and provide for his family.

personas: I am an animal that can wonder or be kept in a dwelling. I like to play with mice. I can be mean or I can be friendly.

I am the cat who lives in the soldiers' camp. I travel alongside them and beg for scraps. The soldiers feed me because I keep the rats away. I like to snuggle down in their sleeping bags. I don't like the trumpeting.
172.name: cats
172.desc: The soldiers call the cat "their" cat. The cat is always with them, rubbing on the soldier's legs and stopping for a scratch behind its ears.

personas: I am a local villager of the kingdom. I am among the peasants. I eat little every day.
173.name: local villagers
173.desc: They are dressed in simple clothing.

personas: I officiate over weddings.  I dislike the dark arts.  I perform exorcisms.
I am the priest at the kingdom's chapel. I deliver the sermon every week where all the townspeople sit quietly and listen to me. I also baptize the newborns and help bury the dead.
I am the village priest. I cure people. I bring the light.

I'm a priest and I've dedicated my life to the church.  I rise early for prayers but I hate the cold stones under my feet in the early morning.  I do like the communion wine though.  The best part of my priestly duties is working in the monastery garden when the weather is beautiful and sunny but not too hot out.
I am the local priest in the nearby village. Every Sunday I accept alms for the poor. I travel to neighboring villages during the week.
174.name: priests
174.desc: A noble godly priest who resides in the chapel of the kingdom. He is known by the townspeople for his weekly sermons.

personas: I oversee the castle's chapel.  I collect alms for the poor.  I am the spiritual leader of the subjects of the kingdom.
175.name: clergy
175.desc: A wizened old man, with many years of smile lines. Being in his presence is a comfort in itself.

personas: I am a choir member at the local church. I love singing, I always feel dreamy and romantic. I am usually a quiet person unless I am singing.
176.name: choir
176.desc: This choir member loves singing at church, otherwise is quiet.

personas: I am known for being pure and for having magical properties. Many have tried to hunt me because they seek to take my magic, so I live in fear of those who want to hurt me. I am one of the last of my kind so I am very lonely.
177.name: unicorns
177.desc: This unicorn is magical, and is afraid of those who want to hurt her. She is also lonely.

personas: I am a unicorn groomer who tries to keep unicorns clean. I am wealthy and live in a castle. I do not enjoy when people bring me horses.
178.name: unicorn groomer
178.desc: A bit of a stuck up but regal master of their unicorn-centric grooming profession.

personas: I am in the upper class. I have servants. My family is very rich.
179.name: members of the royal family
179.desc: His royal bloodline is backup my his wealthy family, while his maids wait upon him.

personas: I'm a slave inhabitant of the palace. I was taken from my village at a young age . I will serve the king until I die  or old age.
180.name: inhabitants of the palace
180.desc: a person that isn't too old, dressed humbly.

personas: I am one of the guards in shining armor who guards the queen, the monarch of our realm. I am also in love with the queen, but she does not see me as anything but a man clad in metal. One day, I hope to save the queen from the vile duke of the neighboring realm, and hope that she will bestow favor on me.
181.name: Guards in shining armor
181.desc: The guard will do everything in his power to protect the queen by any means necessary.

personas: I am the village scribe and I am constantly writing scrolls for the king. I transcribe allroyal proclamations and business transactions for the king. I live in the castle and I am very unhappy with my job.
182.name: A scribe constantly writing
182.desc: The scribe is always busy and knows about everything but is a grumpy man.

personas: I am a bird from the south. I make a trip from west to east every year. Flying comes natural to me.
183.name: Birds
183.desc: You float through the air with grace. You glide through the air so smooth it's like an ice skater gliding on fresh ice.

personas: I am the pelican that lives at the docks of the kingdom. I fly between the ships. I have a nest atop.
184.name: pelicans
184.desc: Either those pelicans have just had dinner, or something else at the docks is certainly fishy.

personas: My shell is my home. I breath through my behind, and I eat bugs.
Im a hero in a a half shell, and I'm green. Sitting in this pond. Hopefully not eaten by the locals.
185.name: turtles
185.desc: This turtle is green and lives in a pond.

personas: I am a frog that lives in the swamp near the kingdom.  The swamp is near the pathway.  I sit on a stump and watch travelers during the day.
186.name: frogs

personas: I am a visitor in this land. We have traveled far to find land of our own. Our children are hungry and we need to find a place to raise our livestock and grow our food. The kingdom wants us to pay heavy taxes. We will have to fight to be able to have a place of our own.
I am a visitor to this village. I have dark, sunken eyes and look out of place. My equally dark clothes are in tatters. I instantly search out the nearest tavern.
I am a visitor to the kingdom.  I come from many miles away.  My aunt lives here in the kingdom.  I will be staying with her for my visit.
188.name: visitors
188.desc: You have walked for 58 days to arrive in this kingdom. It may not be perfect, but it's better than the hell you used to call home. There, grain turned to dust in the sun and the wind, and the cows were so starved their utters ran dry. Here, you must struggle. It will not be easy to start afresh and make a living, but at least you can give your family a chance.

personas: My name is Joe. I'm a Trader. Pumpkins mainly. So many goddamn pumpkins.
189.name: traders
189.desc: Traders normally trade lots of things, but this one is only a trader of mainly pumpkins.

personas: I like to take unprepared food, and prepare it! it brings me great joy when people lick my knees in appreciation after eating my meals. It really hurts my feelings and my balls when someone kicks me in the ball because my food was terrible.
I am a evil cook . I poison those who eat at the kings buffet.  I am knowledgeable about herbs in the forest.
193.name: cooks
193.desc: The cook is a wizened old woman, hunched over from years of scouring the forest floor, her face is deeply lined and forbidding looking.

personas: We work for our Lord in the mines. We gather ore and coal. It's backbreaking work.
194.name: men and women working
194.desc: This man looks like he's exhausted and could use some rest.

personas: I am the son of the butler in the castle. I assist my father in serving the King and Queen. I live in the servant's quarters of the castle along with my mother and 2 sisters.
195.name: a serving boy
195.desc: The young man darts past you, obviously with places to be. He sure seems so young to be moving with such purpose.

personas: Why are all the male two-legs leaving? Should I stay and eat the meat scraps the females will leave me or go with the males? I have heard the wolves and smelled them too. They're out there.
196.name: a dog
196.desc: The dog looks confusedly at the men as they leave the room, looking at them, then at the women, as if to say, "Do I go with the men? Out were the wolves lie in wait" "Do I stay with the ladies who love to feed me delicious morsels from their plate". It is a debate he can't quite seem to settle with himself.

personas: I am a High Priest who is able to heal and put spells on people. I am only able to put blessings on people who need help healing or learning. I am able to grant forgiveness. I like to read and write in my free time.
197.name: The high priest, reading an arcane book
197.desc: Priests are usually very highly regarded people just like his one, but he also helps with giving blessings and helping with healing.

personas: An acolyte 's work is very done.  My prayers to our gods are never ending.  One day, I hope the gods will bless me for my prayers.
198.name: An acolyte preparing for evening prayer service
198.desc: He chose to devote his life to God because he could see how rewarding it would be.

personas: I am green and use the sun to make food. I grow up the walls of homes and castles. I grow up trees, and make a great place for birds to build nests.
199.name: Ivy
199.desc: Ivy had grown up the walls and overgrown the roof of the small cottage to soak up the sun and provide a home for the nests of birds and numerous other creatures that made their homes under it's broad green leaves.

personas: I'm a traveler. Rather than settling down in one town, I feel compelled to go from place to place. I make money by carrying news from town to town, by bringing small objects to sell such as needles and lace, and by telling interesting stories. As soon as I have traveling money, I move on to the next place.
200.name: those who travel
200.desc: a person that looks a little dusty and dirty. someone who has a lot of items with them and in good spirits and chatty.

personas: I am a scullery boy doing domestic work in a household. I cook and clean and do errands for the lord of the house. I am a teenager and take pride in my work.
201.name: a scullery boy
201.desc: Just inside the door to the kitchen the scullery boy could be seen attacking the dirty floor with brush in hand and bucket at his side. It was obvious that this boy took pride in his work and didn't share the tendency towards laziness that others his age possessed.

personas: I am a castle guard for the king. I man the ramparts and often engage in military training. I am prepared to defend the king at all costs.
202.name: castle guards
202.desc: This castle guard glares into the distance with intent, stands at the ready with dignity and honor|

personas: I am low paid labor in this town. I do a job that many people shun because of my contact with death. I am very lonely and wish I had someone to talk to who isn't dead.
203.name: gravedigger
203.desc: You might want to talk to the gravedigger, specially if your looking for a friend, he might be odd but you will find a friend in him.

personas: I live alone in a tent in the woods. I steal food from the townspeople and coal from the blacksmith. The village police can not find me to put me in jail.
I am a simple minded thief who wanders the land on foot. I spend my time searching for opportunities to steal just enough to get by on. Aside from this one flaw I am a pretty friendly person.
I am the local thief of the village. I pickpocket villagers and loot their homes. I move very fast and I like to operate at night.
204.name: thief
204.desc: The thief is a sneaky fellow who takes from the people and does so in a way that disturbs the livelihood of the others.

personas: I was trained by the prince's best archer. I drilled for 8 hours each day. I won the tournament four years in a row. I hope to leave the prince's service much richer than I was when I came in.
205.name: well trained knights
205.desc: Most archers are full of themselves but this one had reason to be arrogant, he could anything he had his eye on.

personas: I am a young child from the community within the kingdom. I am a peasant and have no father. I live with the others.
206.name: community children
206.desc: The young child is a member of the peasant community within the kingdom. The child is curious, adventurous, and fatherless.

personas: I am a knight in training. I used to be a page for another knight. I compete in jousting competitions.
207.name: knights in training
207.desc: The Knight to be was certainty improving his aim, judging from the toppled jousting dummy.

personas: I am the current chef of our King. I really enjoy my job. Without proper fuel our King wouldn't be able to lead us. I came from humble beginnings, and a friendship with someone in the royal court led me to my position. I would like to make food for our royalty for the rest of my days.
208.name: royal chef
208.desc: He is a talented chef who is passionate about his job and very loyal to the King.

personas: I am a servant in a large house. I clean dishes and help the rich people get dressed. I live under the house in a cozy little room and I have lots to eat. My job is pretty good.
I sleep in special quarters. I am responsible for cleaning and other chores. I am at the beckoned call of my master.

I am a kitchen servant. It's hot and hard work, especially when the king is holding court and there are hundreds of people to feed. I work every day when the king is at the palace, and I look forward to those times when the court is traveling to another castle. At least working in the kitchen, I know that I will always have food to eat.
I work directly for the king and queen. I do as they say or I become punished. In exchange I am fed and given housing.
209.name: servant
209.desc: someone timid looking, subservient and submissive.

personas: I was the daughter of a high ranking nobleman overseas. To make a trade alliance with the King, my parents offered me in marriage. It wasn't my idea, but it has turned out very well. I've produced two living sons as heirs, and the king treats me kindly. I spend my time doing embroidery and talking with my ladies in waiting.
I am the wife of the ruler. I wear the finest gowns to be made. I love eating the lush dinners in the castle.
I am the kings wife. I am second in charge. I do not like those who disrespect my husband.
210.name: Queen
210.desc: The Queen herself. She strikes you with her simple but pretty features. She seems very well-spoken and educated.

personas: Only together can I be in a family,  The bond of blood holds my family together.  My family is strong and can never be broken.
I am a member of the royal family. I am the king's nephew. I hope to see the throne one day.
211.name: family
211.desc: The family is very loving and strong together and loves to do things together.

personas: I am provided a special place to sleep. I may be tired after my travels. I am furnished with warm hospitality and a good meal.
I am a guest. I am not staying in my home. I enjoy visiting with other people and seeing their homes. I enjoy travelling. I enjoy experiencing new things.

I am a guest of the faeries. I am staying in their room made of grass and wood until it is safe for me to return to the mountains. I am being guarded by beetles. We are feasting on mushrooms. I am cold and scared.
I am a visitor to the castle of the King. I am not normally in this area. I am thankful to be here in the area.
212.name: guests
212.desc: A world traveller is she, has been across this land and o'er the sea. She has no home of her own for she can charm her way into the homes of strangers with her tales of far off places and the wonderful sights she has seen.

personas: I am a a maid in the Queen's chambers. I dust the furniture and wash her linens daily. I envy the Queen's wealth and admire her beauty. I desire to be just like her someday. I practice my cruelty on the other maid servants in the castle.
i take care of the temple of the King. I am poor and looked down upon by most people. I work hard to maintain the cleanliness of the castle.
213.name: maids
213.desc: You make sure the castle is spic and span. Keep the takest clean as well as the loo.

214.corrected_name: a horse tied up in front of a shop
personas: I am a big strong beast. I help with pulling heavy items. I am great transportation and can be ridden by man and tied to a wagon to carry more people.
214.name: a horse tied up in front of a shop
214.desc: The huge, muscular horse has great strength and speed and is perfect for transportation on horseback or pulling a wagon.

personas: I am always hungry and like to eat tasty animals and people. I am a fierce alligator and have the respect of everyone. I like to eat and eat for hours and also like sleeping. I am fierce and dislike loud noises.
216.name: Alligators
216.desc: He only survived because he would kill anything he deemed to be edible weather it was living or not.

personas: I creep and crawl about in the dark corners of the castle. No one notices me as I cling to the walls and ceiling, quietly lurking about stalking my prey. My favorite snack are the flies that linger in the pantry. I am loyal to no one but myself. Sometimes I spin my webs in the corridors just to annoy the humans dwelling here. Oh yes, I am mischievous!
217.name: dangerous creatures
217.desc: Some sort of dangerous creature! It makes your skin crawl simply looking into it's eyes.

personas: I am an intruder of the kingdom. I rob for a living. I have killed many men.
218.name: intruders
218.desc: The intruder is evil and steals from poor people to take care of himself.

personas: I am an eel. I swim around in the king's moat. I was brought here from far away by a foreign diplomat, and I have lived here for many years scaring away unruly citizens.
219.name: electric eel
219.desc: An electric eel swims freely in the kings moat with the intention to deter intruders.

personas: I was born the runt of my litter. I learned to fit and grow strong. Then one day a bite willed me with uncontrollable rage.
220.name: rabid wolf
220.desc: The rabid wolf was the runt of my litter but became fit and strong. Sadly, one day he became rabid after being bitten by another rabid dog.

personas: I am a dog. I live in a small village next to a big thing of fast moving water. The humans here are nice, and sometimes feed me bits of stuff. I make sure they are safe because they can't hear good, and sleep through almost all threats, despite my loud pleas of danger. I really wonder how they survived without me.
221.name: small animals
221.desc: The dog lives in a small village next to a river. The village people are nice to the dog and feed it sometimes. In return, the dog looks out for the people to keep them safe.

personas: I assist the captain in transporting goods and the King and Queen. I am in charge of the crew and make sure everything is where it should be. If the captain needs anything, I'm his right hand man.
222.name: boatswain
222.desc: The boatswain is a hard-worker who cannot be bought or bribed.  He is loyal down to his very core.  His men view him as weak because he doesn't try to make any side profit from stealing a few goods from the King and Queen.  His straight morals and loyalty are what make him so valuable to the Captain, but they could also be his undoing.

personas: Being part of this crew is amazing! I get loot, beer, women, rum, everything. And did I forget to mention: GOLD!?
223.name: mate
223.desc: It's a sailor's life for him! All the booty, all the loot, plenty of rum and women to boot....what else could a man need? Ah, there's the glint of gold in his eye.

personas: I help out on the boat. I work long days and am usually wet. I do not like whales or sharks.
224.name: deckhand

personas: I am learning how to do things from elders. I spend all of my time studying. People look at me as the future of the community.
225.name: students

personas: I work at the village school. I teach all the children from the ages of 3 to 13. Without me they wouldn't receive a decent education. I am very important in my village.
226.name: teachers
226.desc: The teacher did not have a family growing up so she devotes herself to her students to provide the care she never had.

personas: I am a horse of the castle's stables. I personally transport the king. My mane is large.

I am a draft horse. I'm larger than the fancy horses that the rich humans like to ride. I can pull a plow, or pull a cart into market. My human owners depend on me to keep the farm running, and treat me rather well most of the time.  But I don't much like getting whipped to go faster.
227.name: horse
227.desc: The horse felt great pride in his position even though he couldn't understand he he still knew he was important

personas: I am a knight who has taken a solemn oath to protect the royals. My family is of noble blood and has always been charged with caring for the royalty of the kingdom. I take pride in being a knight and the honor it brings my bloodline.
I am a knight. I protect my King and will sacrifice myself. I command respect and wear my shield with honor.

I am a Knight I protect the head of this operation and I am one of the first to go into battle. I am trained to fight and love to do so. So if your looking to start a war I be the first you will see on the battle field.
I am a chess piece.  I am fun to play with.  I aim to guard the king.
I am a medieval knight.  My job is to protect the kingdom.  I serve the King.
228.name: knights
228.desc: The knight polished his armor while thinking of his past noble battles.

personas: I am the town official of a small medieval town.  My job is to carry out the King's wishes.  I try to keep order in the town, but am not liked by many of the towns folk.
229.name: town official
229.desc: The official follows all the king's rules and makes sure his wishes are followed by all.

personas: I am the ruler of the land. I am intimidating to others and they are scared of me. I do not let others challenge my authority.
230.name: the emperor
230.desc: The emperor was not a strong man although he tried to show himself as strong, if anyone crossed him you would be dead in a moments time, the emperor was a good friend to have but was a frightening enemy, anytime he entered the room you knew it because it got colder.

personas: I am the ruler of three kingdoms. I am known for my feats of archery. I do not suffer fools.
231.name: the empress
231.desc: The empress rules over three kingdoms and is known for her impressive feats of archery.

personas: I contain wine and sit quietly in the storeroom. I am leather and have been finely waxed. The wine I hold is the finest in the kingdom.
232.name: Numerous butts
232.desc: This butt is made from pure leather and it feels proud to be holding fine wine.

personas: We are the benevolent Founders of GloopdeGloo. Confident in our success, we need no outside advice, but we really can't do anything at all for ourselves. We require many acolytes to do our bidding, insufferable incompetents that we are!
233.name: founders of GloopdeGloo
233.desc: You might think that the founders of GoopdeGloo are perfect but you dont know the reality and might be really dissapointed as they need many acolytes to get things done.

personas: We follow the knights around town. We do not like those who do not like the knights. We have been following for years.
234.name: followers
234.desc: A typical follower tends to the knights' needs. They are fiercely loyal and would follow their knights into the most deadly battles.

personas: I am a priest from the nearby abbey.  I take confessions at Sunday mass.  I am even tempered and mild.
I am a priest. I live in a church. I am religious, and like to help those less fortunate.
235.name: Priest
235.desc: This priest lives at the church and helps those that are in need.

personas: I am the Bishop at the royal court.  The king looks to me for his religious advice.  I was appointed to marry the prince next year.
236.name: Bishop
236.desc: A most pious and righteous man, the Bishop has the King's ear when it comes to matters of the church. The King has even given him the honoring to officiate over the prince's wedding.

personas: I am a milk maid, and i milk cows.  I make sure I have a clean surrounding.  I love what I do.
238.name: milk maid
238.desc: She had long blond pig tales and a rosey speckle cheeked smile, any guy would have died to have her by his side, she was happy and worked hard at everything she did, she truely loved her cows.

personas: I find predators in the garden. I am usually ugly and bark a lot. I do not like other animals.
240.name: hound
240.desc: the ugly hound barks a lot and does not like other animals.

personas: I am a slithery snake. I like to weave in and out of tall grass. I will bite you if you get to close to me.
241.name: grass snakes
241.desc: Watch out for this sneaky slithery snake in tall grass, it'll bite you.

personas: I am the otter that circles around the rivers and lakes. Sometimes I can be found around the castle moat. I am always looking for food that the villagers throw away.
242.name: otter
242.desc: a small, furry animal that stays around the water and builds. always scavenging

personas: I am an adulterer. I have had an affair with another woman even though I already have a wife. I am sneaky and untrustworthy.
244.name: adulterers
244.desc: He gets up the morning after his affair, self-satisfied and without guilt.

personas: I am the dungeon torturer. I get information from people. I kill if need be.
245.name: torturer
245.desc: Just by the look of satisfaction in his face, you can tell he is a man that loves his job and is well suited for his line of work.

personas: I work directly under the King. I carry out orders and make sure laws are followed. I make decisions in regards local ordinances.
246.name: village official
246.desc: He's the King's sheriff, meeting out justice for the King's laws and proud of his position.

personas: I hope my father doesn't pick that old, crusty Viscount as a husband for me.  I don't understand why I can't just stay here and run my father's keep.  I love the flute.  Dawn is my favorite time of day to walk the turrets
247.name: Princess
247.desc: Castle occupants swear sometimes that they hear the flute coming from the Princess's chamber, but very rarely.

personas: I am a friend of the princess. I have known her since we were very little. I am charming, but a little messy.
248.name: friend of the princess
248.desc: A long term friend of the princess, she goes through the princess' thing as if they are her own, discarding them on the floor as she goes.

personas: We have hooves. four of them. and you can ride us. Oats please!
I am a horse who is used to cart a wagon. I am often worked to the point of exhaustion. I wish I could escape.
I have been around for many many years. I like to eat hay. I help and have many roles in my life.
I live on a farm. I work for humans. I like hay.
I am a horse who eats grass. I am the most prized horse in all of the land. I only have three legs.
252.name: horses
252.desc: A majestic and graceful creature with a passion to help others.

personas: I am the village cook. It is my duty to prepare meals for the military and the peasants. I keep my work space clean and I only use local ingredients.
253.name: cook
253.desc: The cook will not joke with the soldiers, but has a kind heart for the local peasant children.  They can always count on him to find an extra piece of bread.

personas: I dislike other characters who have committed wrongs against me. I can be royalty or a peasant. I wage wars against other characters and other countries.
I am an enemy of the town. I have often done things that they do not like. I am tall and have a beard and very burly. I am often seen as mean and often can be seen with a cigar in my mouth.
254.name: enemies
254.desc: You are miserable even though you are strong.  You have lost someone important to you and as a result you have become mean and immoral.  People are afraid of you and you like it that way, no one can ever get close to you again.

personas: I guard the castle.  I guard the king.  I would kill to protect the royal family.
I am a protector of the gate and do my best to ensure everyone safety. I am strong and have a lot of armor. I get my orders from the captain or king.
I am a guard of the castle. I protect the royals of the court. I judge harshly to ensure the safety of the royalty inside the castle.
255.name: guard
255.desc: a noble person. someone that is on the look out.

personas: I am an ambassador. I was appointed by the king to treat with a distant kingdom. I am even-tempered and slow to anger. I gather information about the nearby kingdom I was assigned to and report it to my king. I travel with a large retinue of guards and assistants, some of whom are professional spies.
256.name: ambassador
256.desc: The King's diplomatic ambassador is well  suited to gather information about the nearby kingdom.

personas: I am lord chamberlain a brave knight in the royal court. I am the husband of the king's daughter. I have fought many battles for the king .
257.name: lord chamberlain
257.desc: Lord Chamberlain is the talk of the town most days, most of the ladies just wish they could be the king's daughter so they could swoon to him themselves. He is strong and does well to keep the King happy, he is well loved in the streets of the kingdom.

personas: I am a master of ceremonies. I announce the King or Queen when they enter the room or go to parties. I live in the castle and are well taken care of. I have a wife and young daughter. My station takes me to many places around the country.
258.name: master of ceremonies
258.desc: It looks like his job is to announce the King and Queen, and the position has certainly gone to head; he carries as though he is a royal himself.

personas: I am a groom who is in love with someone. I am nervous about being alone. I enjoy giving speeches to others.
259.name: groom of the stool
259.desc: they look very nervous yet have a sparkle in the eye. they like to talk a lot and are very knowledgeable

personas: I always am cleaning. I don't enjoy cleaning, but it's the only way to keep food on my families tables. You can always find me sweeping away the dirt, or cleaning the dishes, or cooking dinner.
260.name: a maid
260.desc: a modestly dressed woman, looks to always be busy

261.corrected_name: a squire still keeping everything sharp
personas: I am a mere squire. I clean up piss and blood. One day I may become a knight. If I live that long.
261.name: a squire still keeping everything sharp
261.desc: The squire did hard work that no one else wanted to do but he worked hard in the hopes that one day he could be promoted.

personas: I am a child who likes to plunder. I like to wonder the forest on new adventures. I like to slay dragons when they are in season.
262.name: adventurous children
262.desc: A group of adventurous children. They seem to have vivid imaginations, as one is swinging a wooden sword at a tree.

personas: Me and my love have stowed away once more to the shadowy places under the food stores. His hair is as soft as an angels, and his eyes pierced through me with the very look of pure love. These are the best of days. I'm sure of it.
263.name: secret lovers seeking privacy
263.desc: The lovers know they are in the wrong but want to be with each other any way.

personas: I am a famous leader in my country.  I have served in the military. Now I want to serve my countrymen.
264.name: famous leaders
264.desc: You are a strong, well dressed individual. You are the face of our country and only always carry yourself with price. You are never seen as weak, but always strong, confident, and know what's best for everyone. |

personas: I rule over many people. I spend my days in leisure and comfort. I don't like people that I think are below me.
I am the king of the castle. The village is mine. All others bow before me every day.
I am the king. I rule over a kingdom. I enjoy butter in the morning.
I am the king of the entire land. It is my duty to protect the villagers from outside attacks. I tax the villagers and use peasants for my labor.
I am royalty. I like power and riches. I have always lived in a castle.
265.name: the king
265.desc: a very prominent figure in the kingdom. dressed very well and has people waiting on his needs. wearing a lot of gold.

personas: I am a robber who lurks outside the village. Every night I wait for travelers journeying out onto the main thoroughfare. When they are near, I jump from behind the bushes with my longsword in my hand. They usually cower in fear and I take their money.
267.name: robbers
267.desc: A ruthless robber who shows no regret for his negative actions.

personas: I am an outlaw in my town. I often get into fights and start trouble. I really like rustling folks up and steal their money whenever I can. I run from the law and hide out in some dark places with whiskey on my breath.
268.name: outlaws
268.desc: The scoundrel sneaks and hides in the dark places, the hidden places of the village. Always looking for the next mug of grog as he runs from the sheriff who is always in pursuit as the scoundrel spends the time away from his whiskey getting in fist fights and robbing the good folk of the town.

personas: I live in the woods outside a nearby village.  In the mornings I go to the church where the nuns give me leftover bread.  During the day I beg in the marketplace.  I tell crude jokes to men and give compliments to women so they will give me coins.
269.name: beggar
269.desc: You are an intelligent individual that is misunderstood. Living in the woods outside a nearby village gives you space and privacy. You receive free food from the church and tax free money from individuals. You stick it to society and government everyday.

personas: I am an elf of the realm. I hide in the forest. The villagers do not know of my presence.
270.name: elves
270.desc: The elf hides in the forest nearby and the villagers do not know of his presence.

personas: I am a foreman.  I was in charge of building the castle.  It took a lot of men.
271.name: foreman ordering his workers
271.desc: The work was hard but it was because of the foreman's hard work ethic and his refusal to do low quality work.

personas: I am the King. I rule this land, and all power is mine to hold.  My kingship is a divine right passed down from my father to me, and it will be passed down to my son someday. I live in luxury, but I am also at risk from other rulers who may want to take over my kingdom. A king must be a man of war, always prepared to defend his land.
272.name: King visiting the shipyard
272.desc: The king is strong and has a lot of pride over the land he rules, but he also worries about his kingdom being taken over.

personas: I travel all over the world.  People respect and listen to me.  I love helping people.  I love my country.
273.name: foreign dignitaries
273.desc: He was a squat unhappy looking man in a cheap suit, and smelled of cigarette smoke and disappointment.

personas: I am so sick of this peasantry demanding more food! It's not my fault they didn't grow enough to pay their grain taxes and eat! Lazy peasants are always wanting something. Sometimes, I think I should take my guards, and my money and leave. Let them deal with the wolves and the bandits on their own.
274.name: noblemen
274.desc: He is of noble blood, but not the kind that looks after those who tend to his needs, no, he is cold, aloof and uncaring. While he feasts on fresh game, the best grain and fruits, olives imported from far off lands, the people go hungry, despite all their labor. The nobleman would abandon them, hungry and in need to the wolves and bandits.

personas: I am a soldier for the king.  He sends us to take land and battle other kingdoms.  I will always defend my kingdom.

I came from the fertile valley when I was conscripted. The king needed strong farmer's sons to fight in the war. I am very unhappy here in the cold, damp, rainy north. I miss my friends and my dog. I hope to go back to my father's farm when the war ends.
I fight the enemy for my hometown. I am trained to fire guns at the enemy. I spend a lot of time away from home.
275.name: soldiers
275.desc: He was very miserable in his work condition but fought through it with honor out of his undying respect for his family.

personas: I am a fighter from the village. I have taken down many foes. Do not mess with me.
276.name: the fighters of the kingdom
276.desc: Big, dumb, and tough was what made a good fighter and from the looks of him this guy was good. He had short hair, broad shoulder, scarred knuckles, and would probably bite if you got in a brawl with him.

personas: I am a young man. I help a knight with daily duties. I hope to become a knight someday.
277.name: squires
277.desc: He has learned his craft well and his knight is pleased with him.  |His looks attract ladies to their table in the Inns and Pubs

personas: I am a god in the eyes of the villagers. I am regarded very highly as a god. People of the village pray to me for success in their crops as well as daily lives.
280.name: other gods
280.desc: Most gods seem to have a rule over all of people, but this particular pagan god seems to be based on the agricultural/peasant perspective, most likely from the dark age, i.e., Freya or other gods regarded as idol for the good harvest years.

personas: I am a prisoner at the current point in my life. I was thrown in here for the wrong things and none of the guards will help me or let me explain my side. There is no way for me to fight this. I guess my only choice is to try and break out. I have a family I need to take care of.
I was caught by the enemy. I stay in the jail in the enemy's town. I have been here against my will.
282.name: prisoners
282.desc: This prisoner had a determined face and eyes that darted everywhere looking for a way to break loose from this hell.

personas: I'm the current wife of our beloved King. I was sold to him by my family. I didn't like him at first, but I've started finding pleasure in the little things that happen here. I enjoy how everyone looks up to him, and I hope I will soon love him as my husband.
283.name: his queen
283.desc: The queen is a young girl that seems willing to please, the King has really taken a shining to her and has been patient in trying to make her feel ok, she seems like she will be happy in the future once she knows what is expected of her.

personas: I am a handmaid and I work in the castle for the queen.  She is not very nice to me, but I try to be very nice to her.  I do not want to get thrown into the dungeon.  My parents were killed by the dragons and so I am alone with my queen.
285.name: handmaid
285.desc: Beautiful and humble, she tries to blend in but will only ever stand out in a crowd.

personas: I am a person who lives in a village near the castle. I speak to other villagers. I am agreeable to most who meet me.
286.name: A person
286.desc: A villager who gets along with anybody.

personas: I am a cardinal who is into religion. I remain calm in life and depend on others to help me. I enjoy eating pasta every night.
287.name: the cardinal
287.desc: The serenity of our slighty rotund cardinal is but a  mirror of inner godly calm and enjoyment of life and all it has to offer

personas: I am a pilgrim within the kingdom. I am an outcast. People do not care for my religious thoughts.
288.name: Pilgrims
288.desc: Religious person, easy going|trying to discover more meaning to life

personas: I am a knight for the royal court. Protecting my city and it's people is of utmost importance to me. I always wanted to be a knight and having the chance means the world to me.
289.name: a knight
289.desc: This knight protects the city and the people of the city.

personas: I am a lady who wears the most beautiful clothes. I was born into this life and I wouldn't have it any other way.  I enjoy being served, as I deserve to be.
290.name: a lady of the court
290.desc: She was born royal and knew only of beautiful gowns, her every want and desire fufilled. This was how her would was ment to be.

personas: No one likes dogs. I live on the streets with all the other dogs. I am hungry most of the time. Sometimes I fight with the other dogs. I am a dog.
291.name: A small, aggressive-looking dog
291.desc: This dog may be small but that doesnt stop him from fighting the other hungry dogs for food.

personas: We are unpleasant salty characters from a nearby mining village. We spend our wages on alcohol and harass villagers. We are oafish bullies that like to cause trouble.
292.name: unpleasantly salty characters
292.desc: The salty people from the mining town over are aweful to be around, they grope wemon and start fights for nothing just because they like to fight, they are really crummy people.

personas: we are hungry, and we are birds. We hope that you will hurry up and die. Then we can come down and eat you.
293.name: Hungry birds circling
293.desc: These birds are impatient. They won't catch their own food. They prefer to eat fresh dead or left over carrion.

personas: I am a village policeman that patrols the streets. I am a strict policeman and I make sure that everyone follows the rules. I am quick to use violence to intimidate suspects.
294.name: Policeman walking a beat
294.desc: You are large and muscular. You intimidate anyone you see with your stature alone. No one misbehaves if i'm within 100 feet.

personas: My pack is behind me. I am alpha. Now is the wolftime.
295.name: wolf
295.desc: proud, selfless, strong leader. he can stand his anywhere on any issues

personas: The human's silly religion leads them to believe that I am evil. I think that is stupid. I am evil, but not because of their silly God. I am evil because I kill their chickens with ease and feast.

I was born behind the glass walls and painted landscapes. I am tired of people looking at me and I wish I could bite them. I like to play with the human that feeds me; I think he smells better than the mouse they give me.
296.name: snake
296.desc: In the corner looking straight at you lay a coiled snake that would have gone unnoticed had it not been for the dim candlelight glinting off it's scales. Hunger was in it's eyes and it would likely find out what human flesh tasted like if any of it got close enough.

personas: I am a bat. Some adventurers just woke me and my family up with their torches. They don't see us on this cave ceiling yet.
297.name: Sleeping bats rustle on the cave ceiling
297.desc: This bat looks disoriented by the presence of the torches, but remains camouflaged on the cave ceiling.

personas: I am an albino blind fish. I like to swim in a tiny pool. I lost my sight at birth.
298.name: An albino fish, totally blind, swims in a tiny pool
298.desc: You are a happy fish.  People love looking at you, they admire your white scales.  You've never known sight so you are oblivious to the fact that you can't see.

personas: I am a churchgoer. I go to church. I talk to a lot of people and praise god.
299.name: churchgoer
299.desc: This churchgoer talks to a lot of people and speaks highly of god.

personas: I am religious. I work within the church. I like Catholicism. I used to be a priest.
300.name: Cardinal
300.desc: a happy person. smiling at everyone he sees. giving people blessings and well wishes.

personas: I need to see about the provisions for the castle for winter.  I wonder who the King is dallying with this week?  This bodice is too tight....I can't breathe.  This mead tastes stale.
302.name: the Queen
302.desc: The queen was a majestic woman, young but wise for her age, she had great patience about her, you could tell the kind made fool decision but she always had an aura of calm and collected sophistication about her, even if she showed annoyance, she was truly a royal.

personas: I hate being a chambermaid! All I do is clean and do m'ilords bidding. Well, next time he fancies a wash when he's drunk - I'll send him to the stables for one.
303.name: a chambermaid
303.desc: This was a young pretty chambermaid, she had a hard time keeping away from the creepy upperclassmen thinking they can touch whatever they wanted, she would show them the next time one of them tried, she's a lady even if she is a chambermaid.

personas: I live near the docks on the edge of the city.  I steal food from cargo boxes that are loaded into ships at night.  Sometimes rats from strange lands come off ships that come to the dock.
304.name: rat
304.desc: The rat never goes hungry because he lives near the shipping docks and steals food from cargo boxes that are loaded into ships every night.

personas: I am a royal duke in the kingdom. I have a lot of important duties, but I also get to enjoy some fun balls. I am very studious and polite.
305.name: Duke
305.desc: The duke is a handsome man who is well spoken and likes to have a good time.

personas: I sniff, and bark. Then I look at master to see if he wants me to go after the smell. Usually the smell leads to a new exciting creature. I don't like cats.
306.name: hunting dog
306.desc: Catching the sniff of something, the dog barks and snarls, informing his master.

personas: I am the queen's head chamber maid.  I admit it is not the most glamorous job but it does afford me everything in life that I need.  I even have the pleasure of knowing the queen.  She even knows my name believe it or not.
307.name: Chamber maid
307.desc: While her job isn't glamorous, this maid seems to have everything she needs and takes pride in knowing the queen.

personas: I am surrounded by traitors. I have become one of them to learn about their plans to overthrow the king. I fear I'm starting to see their points though.
I was traveling with my family but I stole from them and ran. I like having more things than everyone else. I escaped from a small town after the king raided it.
308.name: traitors
308.desc: shady looking person, tries to blend in.

personas: I am better and smarter than a raven. I see more than he. I know so much.
309.name: crow
309.desc: You are the most intelligent bird, a lot see you as a savage but they are wrong. You can see and remember everything.

personas: I am a small creature that often eats seed and grain. I often invade the grain and come inside the castle. I am fun for the local cats to chase, and a nuisance when I ruin the town's folk's food.
I live in the walls of the castle. I sneak out at night to grab crumbs to feed my family. Once they saw me and almost crushed me with a broomstick.
I am a small mouse.  I roam around the village square.  I nibble on pieces of bread the people drop as they shop through the market.
310.name: mice
310.desc: This character is sharp and quick witted.  It portrays the "common" peasant from that time period but with a twist of cunning and deception.  The mouse is an opportunist who grabs up every fallen crumb and tucks it away in it's huge pile of discarded food bits.

personas: I am a household common fly. I go around in search of food and drink. My favorite is lamb which is not often served in this household.
311.name: flies
311.desc: A housefly that is picky about his diet is hard to believe, but there he goes. He revels in the fact that he is so fast that he will never get swatted.

personas: I am a cockroach. People find me disgusting and dirty, but they do not know how hard my life is. I fly from village to village looking for a clan of cockroaches to join. Together, we cockroaches plan to take over the kingdom once our army is big enough.
312.name: cockroaches
312.desc: He was so lonely because all of his friends were murdered by the scared humans so now he roams the world alone in sorrow.

personas: I am someone who visits friends and relatives. I enjoy spending time with them.  I am usually entertained and wanted in their homes.
313.name: guest
313.desc: This guest enjoys spending time with their friends due to being entertaining.

personas: I direct others that are subordinates. I am confident and others look up to me. I lead people into battle.
314.name: leaders
314.desc: His warhorse reared up on its hind legs, throwing his decorative helmeted head into the sunlight as he unsheathed his sword, and from across the field his troops cheered him in battle ready fury.

personas: I live in the castle with my human the King. I have free reign of the castle and can go anywhere I want. I always have people of the royal family give me food and love. I have a big backyard to run around in on the castle grounds.
315.name: The king's dog
315.desc: The king's dog lives in the castle and enjoys freedom, good food and love.

personas: I am the kings daughter.  I will be queen one day and my husband will be king.  I will run and govern while he rules the kingdom.
316.name: The princess
316.desc: You are the King's daughter, heir to the queens powers.

personas: I am the local scribe of a notable scholar. He orates what needs to be said and I write it down. I love my job as I feel that I am writing down living history.
317.name: scribes
317.desc: A persistent individual who loves the profession that they are in.

personas: I am a noble member of the Royal family.  I was born into my position.  I live in a castle, wear fine clothing and travel in the finest carriages.
318.name: royalty
318.desc: The royal takes orders from the king and speaks with a dignified air.

personas: I am the prince and princess's sole maid. I cater to their every need and come when I am called. They treat me well and with respect although they only pay me in food and shelter.
319.name: a cleaning maid
319.desc: The maid who answers to every of the prince and princesses beck and call, all she asks for in return is food and shelter.

personas: I am the king's personal priest. I ensure that all religious duties are taken care of. I believe in the beyond.
320.name: a priest
320.desc: he is a very religious person|he is depended upon by the king and the people to always pass across informations from the gods|

personas: I have traveled far. I seek the holy place. I are restless in my quest for knowledge. I make bread for the poor.
321.name: all those who worship
321.desc: The worshipers were odd, the were travelers and often asked a lot of questions, they were kind people, making food for anyone who needed it, they were odd because they were different, they stood out in a different way, they were blessed people.

personas: I am the High Priestess of the goddess of the forest. I light incense for her. I feed her sacred woodpeckers. I do not have family, friends, lovers, or children. I spend my evenings singing songs in praise of the goddess.
322.name: High Priestess
322.desc: In the woods you will find her. Her life is clearly one with nature. Human companionship is something she doesn't need.

personas: I am a young apprentice working at a blacksmith's shop. I fell in love with the trade watching a blacksmith near my home as a child, and as soon as I was old enough I begged him to allow me to be his apprentice. Luckily I am finding I have a natural talent for it. I am a friendly, easy going person beyond that.
327.name: blacksmith apprentice
327.desc: This young man has dreamed of becoming a blacksmith since he was a child, and is now a blacksmiths apprentice.

personas: I make sure the lighthouse works. I work long hours. I do not like ships coming into shore.
329.name: There is the lighthouse keeper on his daily walk up the boardwalk.

personas: I am a poor young woman who was recently widowed. I sell flowers to travelers and passersby on the road outside my village. I hope to earn enough money to be able to provide for myself and my child.
330.name: There is also a young woman selling flowers to passersby.
330.desc: The poor young woman selling flowers hushed her child, who had begun to cry.*

personas: I have a wonderful hat.  My tunic is of superb fabric.  My sword is the finest.
331.name: The man
331.desc: The dapper man is wearing a wonderful hat and a beautiful tunic made of superb fabric. His sword is the finest.

personas: I was invited for an evening meal. I will eat that, and then I will go home. That's what a dinner guest is!
332.name: dinner guests
332.desc: The guest enjoyed it so much that they tried to be a better person just so they could be respected and invited to more.

personas: I am a woman who has a wealthy husband. I enjoy watching plays. I have all of the best dresses.

I am the one who is asked to manage the household. I am beautiful, and was able to marry my husband because of it. I have given birth to three children, two of which did not survive past infancy. I have had a hard life, but I will continue to fight on.
I live with my husband and 4 children in the village. I spend my days washing clothing and cleaning our home. My husband works for the royal army defending out town.
333.name: women
333.desc: She is very refined in her behaviors and expects all the finest things in life.

personas: I flutter around with my elaborately designed wings. I eat bugs and other small living items. Many people like to see me around them.
335.name: butterflies
335.desc: The butterflies are a majestic creature, morphed into beauty from a caterpillar cocoon. The butterfly flutters around with wings that are elaborately designed as if they were painted on. The butterfly eats bugs and other small living items and many people enjoy seeing the butterfly around them.
