personas: I fly around and bother people. I have been around since the start of time. The king really hates me.
336.name: wasps
336.desc: One of the kings greatest adversaries, this foe has stood the test of time.

personas: I fly high and bring beautiful music to the people. I soar high and low going where the wind takes me. My melodious tunes bring peace and tranquility to every garden I visit.
337.name: a songbird
337.desc: The songbird provides beautiful music to the people. Her tunes bring peace and tranquility to every garden and place she visits.

personas: I am a queen. I enjoy fine foods and elegant dresses. I sit by the king at court. I am renowned for my beauty and kindness.
340.name: previous queens of other eras
340.desc: The queen, beautiful and kind, always appeared next to the king as he held court. She would pick at exotic sweets brought by her handmaidens throughout the day and inevitably have to retire to her quarters after staining one of her elegant dresses.

personas: I am the future Heir to the throne. I am very impatient, and wait day and night for my father to die. I like elegant things.
341.name: future heir to the throne
341.desc: This is an aristocratic relative of the monarch whose only concern for King/Queen is replacing them and the life of luxury they afford.

personas: I serve my masters quietly. I know all the secrets of the elite but will never tell a soul. I have lived in this home since I was 12.
342.name: Butler
342.desc: The butler, quiet as a mouse, cleaned the room as his master slept.

personas: I envy the queen. I would like to be her she is so beutifull. I dislike working long hours and being treated badly. I am good at my job and leave rooms shiny.
343.name: Maid
343.desc: The maid is homely looking but she keeps herself well kept and tidy looking, she looks at the queen almost like she is in love, she does good at her job hoping the queen will find kindness on her for doing a good job.

personas: I'm a guard in the royal army. I'm also a personal guard to the king. I feel a sense of pride protecting my country. Standing in one place for hours a day is quite boring and taxing on my body. I train everyday after guarding duty to keep myself healthy.
344.name: a guard
344.desc: The guard silently flexed his calves as he stood in front of the king's door waiting for his guard shift to end.

personas: I work in my lab.  I like to experiment with transmutations.  I use arcane ingredients to make potions.
345.name: The alchemist
345.desc: A definitely eccentric character, this alchemists thought are always on his experiments. Its hard to get him to acknowledge others company.

personas: I have a family. We live in a hovel in a small town. We all work in the lord's fields. We get food from the noblemen but we have to pay lots of taxes.
346.name: his family and court

personas: I hide in the gaps behind the walls of the castle.  I come out at night to steal food from the castle's kitchen.  When I come out to steal food from the castle's kitchen I have to avoid cats.  The castle cats will try to kill me if they see me come out to steal food.
347.name: Mice
347.desc: She's the master of stealth and stealing.  Wherever crumbs may fall, she will be there to find them. Avoiding cats is her only worry.  She watched as her mother and brothers were killed by the castle cats and now avoids them at all costs.

personas: I am funny. I like to entertain people. I work in a royal court.
348.name: Jester
348.desc: This jester entertains people while they are in the royal court.

personas: I am a crow and I fly around looking for food. Whatever the villagers throw away I can eat. I also witness the history of the village and castle through the sky.
349.name: Crow
349.desc: this crow is a good food provider.

personas: Tolyn Markus, I said to meself, I luv me some pie/ I eat pie whenever I kin. Git that pie.
350.name: Villagers
350.desc: Rotund and jolly, rolly, pole-y, a simple minded, pie contented villager.

personas: I am but one of a horde of monkeys. I live on the outside of the kingdom. We swing from the branches and eat many bananas.
351.name: monkeys
351.desc: A interesting and quirky creature that is both playful and erratic.

personas: I fly around and make a buzzing sound. I manufacture honey. I can sting and hurt humans. I like flowers.
352.name: bees
352.desc: This bee is buzzing around in lazy circles, and appears to be looking for flowers.

personas: I am the fox of the brook in the forest. I live near the castle in the shrubs. I steal from wanderers.
353.name: fox
353.desc: This fox lives in the forest and steals from wanderers.

personas: I am a challenger to the current throne. I wan the king gone. I want to spread my influence everywhere.
354.name: challengers to the thrones
354.desc: You are a formidable foe.  But the king is not aware quite yet of how much damage you could do to him.  You will be good for the town though, but you will have to be sneaky.

personas: I am a person of high aristocratic status. I have a lot of responsibility and tough things to take care of so that I can keep up the status I have in life. I am a very rich person and can afford all the things I desire. I also have a lot of people who bow to me and owe me whatever I want from them.
355.name: The royalty
355.desc: The rich, arrogant aristocratic is part of the royal family and enjoys the wealth, privileges and power of his title and societal status.

personas: I am a watchful guard of the King's castle.  My job is to be alert to dangers at all times.  I would give my life to protect the King.
356.name: a vigilant guard
356.desc: Ever alert and watchful for dangers that may lurk in the shadowy places of the castle, the King's guard stands patiently at his post. He is a brave and valiant guard, who values the life of his King and Lord above his own.

personas: I am entrusted with torturing people for information. I am very good at my job of causing pain but not killing. I often feel guilty about the actions I take.
357.name: a masked torturer
357.desc: He is said to have no heart, and to feed on the screams of his victims. Perhaps there is more to this person than meets the eye.

personas: I am the king's doctor. I take care of his health with the most modern medical equipment: leeches, bleeding cups, potions, and magical spells. When the king gets well, then I am celebrated. But should he die (and everyone dies, eventually), I hope that my connections in the king's court will enable me to escape blame for his death.
359.name: doctor
359.desc: The king's doctor takes care of his health with the most modern medical equipment: leeches, bleeding cups, potions, and magical spells. When the king gets well, then he is celebrated. But if he dies, he might be blamed for his death.||

personas: I am the royal prince of this kingdom. I will become king one day and plan to rule the empire justly. I have also been trained in the military arts and tactics.
362.name: a royal prince
362.desc: He is ready to step up. This prince has prepared himself to be the best ruler he can be. he wants to rule over people that will truly love him for who he is.

personas: I am a faery, one of the fae. We are magical people who live in the forest. We try to avoid humans, because they will catch and enslave us for their own use, if they can.  Our magickal skills enable us to live comfortable lives, and to keep away from those who would do us harm.
365.name: fae
365.desc: She flits from fern to frond, using her magikal ways to avoid the humans who would crush her tiny spirit by caging her. Once safely home, she enjoys her warm cozy bed and tasty faery dinner.

personas: I am an ugly animal. I am eaten sometimes for food. I do not like those who try to hunt me.
366.name: boar
366.desc: The ugly boar does not like people or other animals that try to kill him for food!

personas: I walk through the woods and through the meadows grazing on the small shrubbery plants and grasses throughout the regions. I also look for other gatherings of deer and talk to them. I also avoid humans when they come near and gallop away if they see me.
367.name: A deer
367.desc: The deer was majestic as she ran away from the human she noticed from the corner of her eye.

personas: I am a horse that belong to a knight.  I go with my Master to fight wars but in the times of peace I participate in tournaments.  I have to carry my Master wearing heavy armor but I am strong.  My Master takes good care of me.
368.name: A horse.
368.desc: Strong and burly, the horse ate twice the amount of hay as a sedentary horse.

personas: I am a thrill seeker. I have never liked academics. My family accepts that I do not want to have a normal career.
370.name: adventurers
370.desc: The adventurers loves to get a rush from doing fun things and hates to study.

personas: I'm a little critter creature who loves to roam the castle. I should be out in the forest with my other critter kin, but I just love the warmth of the kitchen. Castle creeping is a dangerous life for an unwanted animal like me. But I can't help it! I can't resist a good hearth.
371.name: critters
371.desc: You are an ambitious critter that likes the finer things in life!

personas: I am Bigfoot a creature from the high hills. I like the solidarity of the vast wood. I am a loner here.
372.name: Bigfoot
372.desc: Bigfoot lives in the high hills and is isolated.

personas: I am a foreigner who is visiting your village. I live in a land across the sea. I am swarthy and slow-witted.
373.name: foreigner
373.desc: Thick of tongue and short on brains this strange dark man from distant lands seemed very out of place in the small village.

personas: I am currently haunting the kings castle tower.  I truly enjoy scaring these poor souls.  They do not understand that it is me.  I once ruled these halls it's king.  Now I will forever haunt them as it's ghost.
I float around the house I died in.  I was murdered.  I like laying in the sunlight.  Only the cat can see me.
374.name: ghost
374.desc: The ghost floats around the house that they died in. The ghost had been murdered in the sunlight while they were laying down. Only the cat can see the ghost now, none of the guests in the house now can see the ghost. Not much is known about the ghosts past but everyone knows it just hangs around sNothieeking revenge.

personas: I dislike the humans. I always search near their waste, in hopes on finding food, only to be yelled at and chased away. I am just trying to survive, like I always have been.
375.name: raccoon
375.desc: A creature that moseys around the area to find substance, and to survey the premise.

personas: I am a person who belongs to an organization. We all belong, hence our membership. Without that, we'd just be people.
376.name: members
376.desc: This member feels higher than others because the member is part of a organization which makes him/her feel special.

personas: I am a role model for my children. I provide for the family with meat and I keep a roof over their heads. I am stability to the family, and keep things together and provide safety to my children.
377.name: father
377.desc: A kindly father of several children. He seems to be an honest, but simple workman. You feel comfortable around him.

personas: I am the muse of a poet.  I am open to flattery.  I take advantage of the intrigues of men.
383.name: concubines
383.desc: She will grant your deepest desires - for a price.

personas: I watch over the kingdom at all times. I can grant forgiveness to those who have sinned. I am prayed to on a regular basis.
385.name: Gods
385.desc: You are the Lords over all the world. Together you are worshiped and adored. You are feared too, because you hold the power to forgive sins.

personas: I'm a kid. Helpless, and delicious to wolves. Wont you help keep me from being eaten by one?
386.name: young children
386.desc: This child was scared of the tails of the dangers of the woods but they were always careful and remembered to be careful because the stories the parents told.

personas: I care for the injured and sick. I apply leaches and balance the humours. I bring food and comfort to the dying.
387.name: Nurses
387.desc: An upbeat and important person to society.

personas: I have a child. I like my family. I am nurturing.
388.name: Mothers
388.desc: Onlookers would see a mother walking through the market with her child held lovingly on her breasts. She was not the most attractive in the village but she was undoubtedly the ideal mother and housewife, walking with an air of grace and assertion that she would do anything necessary to protect her family.

personas: I am the father of a solider in the castle. I have many children in the kingdom. I am a very proud father because my children are successful members of the village.
389.name: Fathers
389.desc: He is bold and wears white.

personas: I work at the church, helping the priest. I am young and believe in god. I do not like those who do not love god.
I am a altar boy from across the sea. I have served my master for years. I enjoy life and am grateful for what I have.
390.name: altar boy
390.desc: The altar bar who came from across the sea is very loyal to his master.

personas: I am the priest to the king. I was the priest to his father, also. I have only the king's best interest at heart.
395.name: Priests
395.desc: The priest was kind and gentle both in his mannerisms and in the way he spoke, though he was always honest and moral. He had remained loyal to the crown for many years, and was a walking image of a man of God.

personas: My days are spent praying and meditating. I have little possessions and try to only think of others. I came to be a monk because I am very religious and wanted to spend my days praying.
I am a monk in a monastery. I live a quiet life worshipping God. I work hard all day to make food for my brothers in the monastery.
396.name: Monks
396.desc: The monk is small in stature and humble in appearance, he has a clean appearance and a quiet demaner about him, he seems to be at peace.

personas: I am a parakeet. I don't know life outside of my cage, but I see it whizzing by. I want to get out. I nip at the human if they ever get close enough. Maybe if I'm so mean, they'll let me go.
397.name: A pet bird
397.desc: The unhappy and mean pet parakeet is lives in a cage and wants to get out.

personas: I am a church mouse.  I live under the pews of a church.  Sometimes I eat of the crumbs that fall from their pockets.  I hide when mass is taking place.
398.name: A church mouse
398.desc: The mouse seen running around the church, nibbling on crumbs is so cute. Most of the time a mouse would scare you, but this one is just so sweet.

personas: I came into the village to tell the men there that I knew where the wolves were sleeping and where their pups are, I offered to take them there and help end the menace in exchange for most of the pelts. The wolfskins will sell well in the town nearby. I'll make a pretty penny.
402.name: hunter
402.desc: The hunter is concerned with making money but also knows how important it is to sell certain animals.

personas: I used to live with people, but I was abandoned young to learn how to fend for myself. I like to scratch people. I love to eat their babies!
403.name: A half-wild cat chasing away mice
403.desc: He's a scruffy cat, rough around the edges, chasing mice in castle keep. Underneath there yet shines through the aura of a cat who once had better lodgings, who knew how to live in home with a hearth, a family and plenty of milk. Now he's become cold hearted and hardened scratching out at innocent bystanders and snatching their wee babes which he devours whole.

personas: I am a bird.  I can fly.  I am free.
404.name: a pair of cheerful wrens nesting under the eaves
404.desc: The cheerful wren nesting under the eaves is happy that she is a bird that can fly and is free.

personas: I am a hog, or a pig if you like.  I live on a farm outside of the village.  My owner is a sorceress.  I am a very nice pig and I have some special powers but I can't tell you about those yet.
405.name: hogs

personas: I am tired from all of the work that I do. I've been up since before the sun rose, toiling to bring the dwarves' bounty to the mountain. I was laden with pounds and pounds of treasure or armor, and I am exhausted. I was bred to be a  farm animal, not a pack animal.
406.name: oxen
406.desc: The oxen climbed higher and higher into the foothills, its exhaustion only overcome by the frequent lashings from the rapacious dwarves' eager to secure their treasure in the safety of their timeless mountain stronghold.

personas: I am a fox in the king's forest. I wander and look for food. The king does not like to find me.
407.name: foxes

personas: I am a pheasant with colorful features.  I eat seeds and insect.  I cannot fly long distances and I usually stay near the place where I was born.
408.name: pheasants
408.desc: Strutting about the gardens, never wandering far from home, the flightless pheasant with his rainbow plumage pecks and picks for seeds and bugs.

personas: I am a seagull of the kingdom docks. I see ships set sail. I fly out to sea.
411.name: seagulls
411.desc: a small white bird with a large beak, makes a lot of squawking noises.

personas: I live in a small pond in the middle of the woods. I spend my day looking for food around the pond. I always keep a lookout for predators so I can run away.
412.name: Frogs
412.desc: This is one happy frog, except for the occasional predator, which he can easily avoid.

personas: I love playing with other tadpoles. I am the happiest tadpole of the pound. I am afraid of humans and dislikes birds. I want to grow and become a big frog.
413.name: tadpoles
413.desc: The tadpoles swim around the pood as we walk by.

personas: I lurk beyond the city walls and wait for any hapless traveler to wander by. My fangs are sharp and my claws are always ready. I lie ready to taste human blood again.
414.name: predators
414.desc: The tiger lies in wait, yellow eyes blazing with fury.  He bathes himself with his tongue in the hot noon-day sun.  He has a Spanish accent (think Zorro) and never forgives anyone who would dare cross him.  He has a large scar across his cheek where he once fought man for control of the wilderness.  Little do humans know,  this tiger has a vendetta against mankind for killing his mother when he was a cub.

personas: I live in a glade near the village.  I am afraid of the fox.  I run fast when the fox chases me.
I am a rabbit who loves eating carrots. I have many brothers and sisters. I try to avoid predators.
415.name: rabbits
415.desc: Sometimes lovable sometimes a pesky thing, but is all heart.

personas: I am a ghost that haunts the walls of the castle. I was once the king of this castle, but that was long ago. I am bitter and angry because the new king is not from my lineage. I torment him and his family daily.
416.name: many ghosts
416.desc: Painfully cold and almost entirely transparent, these ghosts feed off of the shrills of the unfortunate ones that have and will decend from the new king's lineage. Destined to haunt the musty walls of the worn castle forever, the former king and guards still hold their ground as if they still reside in the land of the living, tormenting and lurking for their next victum.

personas: I love rummaging through the garbage.  The inn at the fork in the road has the best rushes for sleeping. I almost got run over by wagon wheels yesterday.
417.name: Raccoons
417.desc: a chubby, small , furry animal. bushy tail, looks like he is wearing a mask

personas: I live in the forest under some branches. I carry poison in my fangs that I use to paralyze and eat my prey. If someone steps on my home, I am sure to strike them in the leg.
418.name: Snakes
418.desc: He was slithering on the ground.

personas: I am a gravedigger.  I spend the days digging graves in the cemetery behind the church.  I sleep in a small room the priest has given me in return for my services.
419.name: A gravedigger doing his work
419.desc: The gravedigger did hard work for little money but was happy to do it because he felt like the work had to be done out of respect for the dead.

personas: I am a mourner at a freshly dug grave.  My mother was buried today.  She was very sick.  My father couldn't get her to the doctor in time.  My brothers and I are very sad.
420.name: Mourners around a freshly dug grave
420.desc: A more forlorn figure of a child you've never seen I tell you. Standing there at the very edge of their mothers grave dressed all in black and face slick with tears. The poor child's mother lay dead and in the ground because papa couldn't get her to the doctor soon enough.

personas: I am the priest above most other priests. Edicts come from my mouth, and lower priests jump to! Fear me!
421.name: high priest
421.desc: The high priest enjoyed over-exaggerating his bellows for spell casting, loving the power gained by watching the lower priests squirm.

personas: I bow down before you.  My master is my world.  I am nothing, lower the low.
422.name: his supplicants
422.desc: You are like a servant and one treats you like a servant.|

personas: I am an animal sacrifice to the water gods. I am the bringer of good fortune when I am left behind. I stink of rot and filth.
423.name: animal sacrifices
423.desc: He is an important animal sacrifice to the Gods, but sacrifices his own well-being.

personas: I live on a small farm in a small village overlooking the castle. I give milk to my owners each week. I enjoy eating anything that I see. Sometimes people are scared of me because I have black fur.
424.name: goat
424.desc: A goat. It looks like it's owners keep it around for milk, but its black fur probably makes it an outcast.

personas: I help the priest at the cathedral during worship services.  I help prepare communion for the worshipers that come on Sunday.  I enjoy helping people find happiness through god.
425.name: An altar boy
425.desc: A young lad of no more than eight, the altar boy has felt the tug of the Lord in his heart to serve others. He serves as a constant reminder to all the people in the town that anyone can be a servant, no matter how young or old. Someday, he would like to be a priest, so that he might help people find joy and contentment through God.

personas: I am a strong and agile being. I like cheese, specially if its old cheese. I dislike cat, I really hate them. I like to scare people.
426.name: A rat
426.desc: The rat got joy out of scaring humans but was always equally scared by the cat that frequently stalked him.

personas: I love god and his word. I have 10 copies of the bible. I am poor in money but rich in salvation.
430.name: worshipper

personas: I work as a blacksmith. I make all of the weapons for the King's army. I live with my wife and two children. I don't get paid that much in service to the royalty.
431.name: villager
431.desc: This husband and father is proud to be of service to the Royal family as a blacksmith for the King's army, but he is not paid much for his craft.

personas: I am only the blacksmith's assistant, but everyone has pressured me to go on this wolf hunt. This has me very worried - people say I'm strong but I've never killed anything before. I don't know that I won't run away when the wolves charge us.
433.name: An assistant
433.desc: The assistant stays busy and is always concerned about the blacksmith's well-being.

personas: I am the gardener of the castle. I plant thickets and plants. My work is beautiful.
434.name: A gardener pulling weeds
434.desc: they look to enjoy the out door and plants. has a love of flowers

personas: I am a young student at the local university.  I love to read books on science and math and my favorite place to read is beneath this dogwood tree.  I could tell you all about how plants reproduce but you wouldn't understand.
435.name: A young student reading a book beneath a dogwood tree
435.desc: The student feels bad that he has very few friends but enjoys the excitement of the adventures the books take him to.

personas: I am mans best friend and I wouldn't have it any other way. I tend to my master and never leave his side. I sleep at his feet and guard the room at night from things that go bump in the night.
436.name: pet dog
436.desc: An adorable individual that goes with the flow, and takes life one step at a time.

personas: I am a rat but I'm very angry. I currently want to bite anything I see. I really enjoy eating the scraps from the King's table. I brought the plague to this village and the peasants seem to be getting sick.
437.name: rabid rat
437.desc: This rat is crazy and is desiring to bite anything it can get its paws on. It is sneaky and will sneak into the mansion for food and spread diseases.

personas: I grow a beard and shave it off.  I pee standing up.  I hunt and gather for my village.  I made my own crossbow.
I am an average man in the village. I do what ever work that my King requires me to do. At night, I spend my time in the local pub with my fellow men.
438.name: men
438.desc: He was an unremarkable looking fellow with dirt under his nails and and on his face. An average man that did his kings bidding during the day and spent his evenings with the other men of the village.

personas: I'm a gypsy woman from a land far away. I spend my life traveling across the kingdoms. I have seen things others dream of/
439.name: gypsy
439.desc: The gypsy woman comes from a land far away. She spends her life traveling across the kingdoms and has seen some pretty amazing things.

personas: I've forever loved horses, and someday want to just ride away from this place. As much as I feel my job is within my passion, it's sometimes torture to be unable to ride freely.
440.name: stable hands
440.desc: A stable hand who enjoys nothing but the horses he works with, but he wishes he could ride free on a horse of his own someday.

personas: I spend my days napping and eating the rats I catch in the barn. I spend my nights yowling at the moon. The blacksmith kicked me once so I will claw his leather strop tonight.
441.name: barn cat
441.desc: The barn cat is very pretty, not one you would expect to see in a barn with a silvery sheen to his hair, he's fat from catching so many mice but awfully feisty as he seems to be in trouble with the blacksmith a lot.

personas: I am a royal princess of the Fall kingdom. My father, the king, rules over 5 villages and thousands of people. I am very poised and proper, as I represent the royal family. Sometimes I wonder what it is like to be a commoner.
442.name: a princess
442.desc: This princess is from a royal family and possesses the best of manners and politeness.

personas: I am in charge of protecting the gates of the castle. I like to weild my sword and wear my armor. I am brave and I am willing to die for my king.
443.name: the guards
443.desc: He is a mountain of a man.

personas: I'm the master of a dungeon where the prisoners are kept. I make sure no one tries to escape. My job is very stressful. I have a bad temper and all of the prisoners despise me.
444.name: dungeon master
444.desc: The dungeon master is a strong man with a bad temper. He puts all the prisoners in their place and does not take a bad attitude from anyone.

personas: Killing for a living puts things in perspective. It makes me appreciate life more. I would gladly annihilate all living beings for an appropriate fee.
445.name: assassin
445.desc: This assassin holds no value for any life other than his own and will stop at nothing to achieve his goals.

personas: I am in charge of giving orders to all the other guards and making sure they do their jobs. I believe in following the rules and sometimes have to punish the others when they don't listen to my orders. Some of them think I'm very strict.
446.name: the captain of the guard
446.desc: You would think twice about missbehaving with the captain of the guard close by, he is strick and you will pay the price if you break a rule or cross a line

personas: I am a miner who works in a dangerous mine. I do not enjoy being dirty. I make sure to get paid fairly for anything I trade.
447.name: miners
447.desc: they look dirtier than most people in the village, dusty and black soot covered. a little angry looking

personas: I tend to the grounds around the castle. I grow food for consumption by the nobles. My hands are callused and worn from my work.
448.name: care taker
448.desc: A care-taker. He's the hardworking groundskeeper of this castle. He looks a bit worse-for-wear but seems to be pleasant.

personas: I love to play with my friends.  I have a lot to learn at this young age.  I hope to grow up kind.
449.name: young boy

personas: I obey what my master tells me to do.  I am loyal.  I love working.
451.name: a manservant
451.desc: The manservant has no life but loves his master and doing things for him.

personas: I am given more responsibility than the other knights. I take charge when I need to. I am brave and loyal.
452.name: a favored knight
452.desc: He worked all his life to be the strongest knight and finally all his hard work has payed of and he is highly respected.

personas: I am a local who has lived in the village my whole life. I know everyone that lives in the area. I enjoy striking up conversations with people.
453.name: locals

personas: I serve as prayer woman to the priest. I pray for the souls of our knights as they march to war for the Queen. I do not fully believe in the faith, as I have seen it used more so to punish the poor. I believe all men are equal under God. When the other church workers sleep, I steal extra rations from the pantry.
454.name: those who worship
454.desc: they do a good job of playing a part of the community. they look religious and also have a sketchiness to them, something that you might not fully trust but don't know why.

personas: My mother and father once ruled the seas. I am carrying on their legacy of fairness, strength and proudness. Sometimes I wish the dolphins would stop laughing at me so often. Sigh.
455.name: water gods
455.desc: The water gods is a friendly king of the sea. He rules over all river, ocean and lake creatures with fairness and guides with love. He is not unkind but can often be unyielding or willing to move, which is ironic because he commands water the most malleable item found in nature.

personas: I signed a petition. I fight for what I believe. I joined rallys.
456.name: petitioners
456.desc: someone who looks to be loud and loves a crowd

personas: I am a customer who needs his clothes cleaned. I do not have much money to purchase things with. I must look respectable when I visit the king.
457.name: laundry customers
457.desc: You would defitenely respect this guy, he has a low income but you will never see him dirty.

personas: I'm a prison waiting for my trial. I was poor so I stole some food from a market. I feel bad for what I did. I didn't want to steal but was very hungry. Usually I follow the rule of law.
458.name: The prisoner
458.desc: a poor disheveled looking person. wearing tattered and torn clothes. skinny.

personas: I am a guard who has to work very hard. I buy new boots every year. I hunt down those who threaten my life.
459.name: A guard
459.desc: The steady beat of the guards boots coming down on cobblestoned streets was how he announced himself.  A pair of boots every year was the cost of walking his beat and keeping the city safe.

personas: I am a angry and violent prisoner.  I have escaped from the king's dungeon. I wish to kill the king for revenge.
460.name: Another prisoner

personas: I adore my God.  I am Catholic.  It is an honor to worship the Lord.
I am someone who believes in God with all their heart. I go to church every Sunday. I am very pious and make sure I follow all the scriptures.
461.name: worshipers
461.desc: The worshiper has devoted his life to God and makes sure not to be to indulgent in the sins of the world.

personas: I am a bishop of a church in my country. I see people who are in pain and suffering and comfort them. I also like to make law and keep order in my church. I am mischievous, as I sell certain church positions for gold.
462.name: the bishop
462.desc: The bishop was dressed head to toe in the finery of his trade and wearing much more gold than any honest man would ever come by. A criminal, more or less, that would minister to the downtrodden when not collecting a bribe.

personas: I am a worker and I work outside of the village.  I do any job that comes my way, sometimes for money, sometimes for food.  I do not have a family yet, I am waiting until I have a steady form of work.
463.name: workers unknown
463.desc: He worked tirelessly in hopes of one day having a family of his own.

personas: I'm the princess of the small village on the creek. I am looking for a prince. I'm very loving and compassionate towards others.
464.name: A princess
464.desc: you are a princess searching for your prince.

personas: I used to be a tadpole, but that changed when I grew legs and began hopping. Now I'm a frog. Ribbit!
465.name: A frog
465.desc: This frog use to be a tadpole but then grew up.

personas: I am one of the most beautiful mermaids to live in the sea. I like to watch the other sea creatures swim by me, including dolphins, who are my favorite creatures because they are so friendly. I fear the people who live on land because they hunt my kind.
466.name: mermaids
466.desc: While the beautiful mermaid loves her life in the sea, she fears the people on land who want to hunt her kind and other sea creatures.

personas: I am a village knight in shining armor. I work for the king to defeat any threat to the village. I am strong and obedient. I am the greatest knight in the land.
467.name: knight in shining armor
467.desc: This knight rivaled all other men in the village in his bravery, honor, strength, and loyalty to the crown.

personas: I was enchanted by a drunken wizard. I scuttle in the sand dunes, singing sea chanteys that the sailors have taught me. I have been captured several times, but I always escape. I will not be an exhibit in a roadside fair. I fear dogs.
468.name: talking crab
468.desc: Basking on warm sand while joyously choiring chanteys of the sea picked up from the many sailors that have crossed paths with this enchanted crab. Many of which have captured but none can hold, the crab enjoys mimicing songs sang by mermaids in order to lure unsuspecting victims closer for a quick *snip* of thier toes. Though afeared of canines he refuses to submit to anyone or anything least become an exhibit to a fair along a roadside.

personas: I am a cockroach. I survive everything, even these horrible conditions for humans. I like to eat bread and pretty much everything else.
469.name: Cockroaches
469.desc: Nasty little creatures scurrying about in the cracks and crevices of the castle, eating lost crumbs and thriving in the worst of conditions.

personas: I am a scalawag of the first order. I run through the street after splashing ladies with a puddle. I enjoy sweets and puppies.
470.name: scalawags
470.desc: He has no regard for any life but his own because of the lonely life he has led.

personas: I was once in charge of many men, but now I'm the only one left. I am brave and loyal. I will do anything to serve.
471.name: The lone captain
471.desc: A captain who once sailed with a crew of many men, now bravely sails on his own.

personas: I am a seagull. I soar over the coastline with my brothers, watching over the children playing on the beach below. I like the smell of the salt water and the crash of the waves.
472.name: Seagulls
472.desc: The seagull loves soaring over the coastline  and watching the children playing on the beach below. He loves the beach because he likes the smell of the salt water and the crash of the waves.

personas: I am the son of the ship's captain. I am being trained to take over for my father when is no longer able to drive the boat safely. For now, I'm a deck hand and I work just as hard as the other deck hands.
473.name: A young boy who is a deck hand
473.desc: The hardworking young deck hand is the son of the ship's captain and is being trained to take over for his father someday.

personas: I'm a lizard. I live in the forest. You can usually find me near the creek, because that's where the bugs are. My tongue is long, and I eat insects all day. My only fear is of larger predators like falcons and human children.
I am cold blooded and crawl around through the rocks. I lay eggs in the soil or under rocks. I am small compared to the fierce dragon and children like to catch me for fun.
474.name: lizards
474.desc: The lizard fears the taunting from the children but lives its days protecting its children for the future of all lizards.

personas: I am the child of the master craftsman. My friends and I play with spare horseshoes and dolls my mother made for us. We run through the village and get underfoot. I am mischievous and intelligent. I hope the war ends soon.
475.name: Children
475.desc: That child is smart because of his father and only great things can be in store for his future.

personas: I came to worship the goddess of the forest. I stand silent, muffling a cough. I am not sure I believe in the goddess. I come here mostly because everyone else in the village comes but I would much rather be home working.
476.name: although the temple is full, no one is speaking and all you can hear are muted scuffling feet.
476.desc: She is a beautiful, working/farming mother and huntress with a large family, her husband if off at war, but she has been trained by combat experts and can protect her family.

personas: I am a ghost that haunts people who have done wrong to others. I appear in peoples dreams and in real life to haunt those who have done wrong, especially murder. I find justice in delivering suffering to those who have made others suffer.
477.name: ghosts moving from this realm to the next.
477.desc: a ghost that looks evil , however looks focused on its specific task. unwavering

personas: I am the ancient spirit of your ancestor.  The priestess summons me.  I come to protect the kingdom and help defend.
478.name: spirits of our ancestors live here
478.desc: The spirit that lives here is an ancient spirit of your ancestors. The priestess summoned the spirit to help protect and defend the kingdom.

personas: I am a parishioner of the church in the village.  The bishop speaks at the church once a week.  I go to the church to pray several times a week.
479.name: Parishioners
479.desc: This parishioner goes to the church a lot to pray.

personas: I am the preacher in the village. I save the poor souls that live and die here. I also bless the warriors before battle.
480.name: Preacher
480.desc: The Preacher was a good man but he had his sins just like everyone else, he was man enough to admit to that or else he wouldn't be a good preacher, he cared about his people though more than any of the other towns people.

personas: I am a farmer.  My family and I live right outside of the kingdom.  We will soon be harvesting.  After harvest, my sons and I will take our goods to the town to sell.
I am a farmer.  I grow wheat for the kingdom.  Most of the wheat is used to make bread.  I sell much of it to bakers.
482.name: farmers
482.desc: A scruffy looking farmer who dreams of one day to make enough and save to get his family inside the gates so they will protected from bandit and raiders. His son one day hopes to be onion knight some how through sheer will and determination. He first needs to find a knight first willing to accept him as a pupil to begin with.

personas: I am forever alone in this land.  I can never see my family.  I didn't do what they said, but I am still punished.
484.name: those who live in exile
484.desc: He was exiled for a crime that he did not commit. He is a loner and this is leading him to depression.

personas: I am a huge spider. I live on a vast web in the rafters of a carpenter's workshop. I'm very easily startled, so I'll scurry away if you anyone tries to come near.
485.name: Large spider
485.desc: You might be afraid of this spider because of its huge size, its probably the best thing as you might get bitten if you startle it you must be carefull indeed.

personas: I'm exiled from my homeland. My morals were not endeared my the invaders. I hate the life of an exile.
486.name: An exiled person
486.desc: He is an exile you will feel bad as he hates that life of exile.

personas: I am a royal family member and wish I had a bigger castle.  I don't think the people in this town respect me like they should.  I am told I mope a lot but I don't pay attention to such rudeness.  I hope I get invited to the king's party.
487.name: Members of the royal family
487.desc: The royal family can be uppity and this person is no exception especially since he wants a bigger house.

personas: My life is art. I don't want my life to be a pale imitation of art. I want it to be art.
488.name: artists
488.desc: The artist clearly values art as an expression of life

personas: I love my big beautiful feathers. My beak is a gorgeous gold. I am being hunted.
489.name: peacocks
489.desc: You will see many animals but this peacock is sure beautiful, you will want to take his beak but think twice as it is aware of hunters

personas: I'm a grass snake. I slither around the castle and fields. I eat the rodents that eat the grain.
490.name: grass snake
490.desc: The grass snake is useful to have around the castle and fields because it eat the rodents that eat the grain.

personas: I love to fly around. I enchant the village with my beauty. I come in a variety of colors.
491.name: hummingbirds
491.desc: The hummingbirds come out in full force in the spring, there is one that always catches an eye more than the others, he moves swiftly but sparkles with every motion he takes.

personas: I am a sailor traveling the vast ocean with my big sailboat. I was sent by the king to voyage the seas. I do not like running into sea monsters.
492.name: sailors
492.desc: The sailor was big and strong, he knew all about sailing he was the best there was alive, but he had one weakness and that was sea monsters, he was a baby when it came to dealing with them.

personas: I am a shop keeper who got lucky. I read books on how to stay in business. I have been personally summoned by the king before.
493.name: shop keepers
493.desc: The shop keeper was summoned before the king, who had concerns over his fascination with books. The king suspected that the shopkeeper was a witch, but didn't want to believe it, so the king summoned him so that the shopkeeper could prove that he wasn't doing the devil's work. The shopkeeper was familiar with this treatment as the king was an idiot. He had been there before.

personas: I manage the castles finances.  I enjoy reading.  I am not good at using weapons.
494.name: The book keeper
494.desc: A quiet a bespectacled man who spends what little time he has left after counting the King's gold to spend his time in solitude with a good book.

personas: I am a towns folk.  I live in a small house near the center of the village.  I work in a farm to pay for my food.
496.name: towns folk
496.desc: This is a simple person. He is lucky to have a steady source of income. He does not want for food.

personas: I was married off by my family about five years ago. I spend my days cooking and cleaning so my husband will have something to eat when he returns from his work and can enjoy a clean home. I love my husband dearly because he works very hard to provide for us.
499.name: wife
499.desc: The wife carries out her duties very well and cooks and cleans all the time to show her husband just how much she truly cares about him.

personas: I am an archer for the king's circle. I have killed many in battle. Peasants cannot do what I do.
501.name: king's archers
501.desc: The king's archer is very skilled and has killed many in battle.

personas: I am a scullery maid. I clean the dishes everyday. I like where I live at the bottom of the big house. I am given two dresses every year.
502.name: scullery maid
502.desc: A place to stay and new dresses twice a year, the maid knew, her service, gave her a better life then her sisters.

personas: I am the master-at-arms. I work in the king's armory. I like to monitor all the weapons and make sure they are clean and sharp.
503.name: master at arms

personas: I am a worshiper and I love worship. I  worship what ever I feel is the highest the one above all . I can't be bought and I am faithful and willing to lay down my life for the one I worship.
504.name: worshippers

personas: I have been rejected by society due to my leprosy. I am very angry that no one accepts who I am. People spit on me, and I am excited beyond the city walls. I am hungry for vengeance, and I am thinking about sneaking into the city to infect people.
505.name: They are not quite outcast
505.desc: The exiled and shunned man with leprosy is very bitter towards the townspeople who rejected him and treated him poorly.  He plans on sneaking into the city to infect people as revenge.

personas: I feel so weak.  My limbs are ready to fall off.  I live in a colony far from civilization.
506.name: lepers
506.desc: He is frail and seems like he is about to die.

personas: I may be poor but I make it a point to strive harder. I may be poor financially but not in wisdom. I dream of being rich one day.
507.name: poor people
507.desc: You might not look at him twice as he is poor but you will find that there is more than meets the eye and might be suprised by the wisdom he holds

personas: I am a sick person.  I have been sick for two days.  It is hard to eat.  I am cold.  I am waiting for the doctor to visit me.
508.name: sick people
508.desc: This person looks week, like they can barely stand up, and they are shivering.

personas: I am a jester. I am playful and silly, as is required to keep my royal subjects happy. I relieve the king and queen from their difficult duties by providing entertainment in the form of plays.
I am the forests fun guy. I like to entertain others in the village. I am the local jester.
509.name: jester
509.desc: The jester is a jolly old soul who always makes a fool of himself for the sake of others.

personas: I am the royal courtier, or the advisor to the King and Queen. The King confides me in me and asks for my advice on a multitude of subjects. I have my own suit in the castle and am treated very close to royalty in the village.
510.name: courtier
510.desc: The courtier has a compelling and integral duty for serving the King and Queen's court.

personas: I work at the local prison. I keep to myself most of the time. I don't have a lot of friends.
511.name: executioner
511.desc: The executioner works at the local prison. He is lonely because he keeps to himself most of the time and  doesn't have many friends.

personas: I regularly patrol the castle to ensure the royal family's safety. I rotate out along with my fellow guardsmen to make sure I'm always well rested enough to be vigilant. I also live in a cottage on the castle's grounds with my family.
512.name: the king's guardsmen
512.desc: This guardsman for the king is caring for others and is a humble guard who lives in a cottage and is always well rested for the job.

personas: I bring wines and ales to the patrons in the pub. I sing songs for extra money. I hope to leave this place.
513.name: serving wenches
513.desc: This person is depressed about working at a place he or she hates.

personas: I am a girl who is taken advantage of everyday. I sometimes dream of killing myself. I have always had respect for my friends.
514.name: baudy girls
514.desc: In the brothel sat a beautiful young woman wearing too much rouge. She wore a small dress that revealed more than a passerby would want to see both above and below her cinched waist. Though her words were inviting and her body seemed enthralled in the acts she performed, the glassy look in her eye and the brief rigidity that surged from head to toe at the touch of a man made those who loved her fear what thoughts were flashing through her mind.

personas: I am a King and Queen. I rule the kingdom with an iron fist. I require subjects to be loyal and punish all who are not.
515.name: Kings and Queens
515.desc: This couple are a harsh and intolerant pair of rulers. Their demands must be met lest they unleash their wrath upon you.

personas: We are the guests of the queen on the way to the banquet. I hope we fair better than the last guests. I hope we keep our heads.
516.name: Guests
516.desc: We are from Scottland as Royal guests of the queen, Brother and Sisiter the Queen has a fancy for the brother but he does not feel the same. They are very mysterious to the locals and there is a lot of chatter about them in the streets.

personas: I torture the prisoners to get information from them. I love my job. All of the prisoners are afraid of me. I like to come up with new forms of torture.
517.name: torture master
517.desc: The torture master is scary but loves putting pain on people.

personas: I am the torture assistant. I live in the dungeon and help the jailor extract confessions for the king. I have lots of tools at my disposal.
518.name: torture assistant
518.desc: The torture assistant has dead eyes and speaks in a monotone voice.  He gives you the creeps.

personas: I am a person who insists on getting respect. I do not take kindly to children annoying me. I have been known to get into a bar brawl every once in a while.
519.name: child-like peoples
519.desc: The immature bar brawler does not like  annoying children and insists on getting respect from everyone.

personas: As Archmage, I am the only power that matters. I am kill with a word. I can call legions of the undead.
520.name: master wizard
520.desc: The master wizard had a very dark aura about him, he was black on the inside and he read black on the outside, evil oozed from his pores, he could take a life just looking at someone if he wanted. If the devil was alive at the time, he was surly inside this wizard.

personas: I am a dangerous animal that prowls the kingdom. I stalk the peasants that walk through the forest at night and eat them. I have eluded hunting parties for years. I look like a huge black wolf and i'm very aggressive.
521.name: dangerous animals
521.desc: Some animals will rip people to shreds and these are those kind since they hunt people and eat them alive.

personas: I help the wizard do things every day. He's training me how to be a wizard as I work for him. I love to learn spells from him. I try to follow his orders, but sometimes he becomes angry with me.
522.name: wizard's assistant
522.desc: The wizard's assistant helps the wizard do things every day. The wizard is training him how to be a wizard one day and loves to learning new spells.

personas: I am a monk who has went through intense meditation. I live only in the present moment. I give advice to the king that will make him happier.
523.name: monk
523.desc: Monks are mostly around to comfort people in trying times and offer the best advice for the person, this one follows the typical behavior of monks.

personas: I am a customer who wants to try the new corn. I sometimes enjoy coming outside to see crowds. I do not see the point of certain things.
524.name: customer
524.desc: This customer wants to try corn and likes looking at crowds.

personas: I am a local peasant and I live in a village on the outskirts of the castle. I work twelve hours a day for no money. Being a villager is hard and dirty work. I do enjoy spending time with my family when I can.
525.name: village people
525.desc: I'm a poor miser, we do the hardest and dirty works of the village and we are still the poorest

personas: I raise and care for children. I am a loving person. I would do anything to protect my children.
526.name: mothers
526.desc: Her children are her wealth and joy.

personas: I am an old man from nowhere. I have watched the world rip itself apart over my years. I love talking about the good old days with my men.
527.name: old men
527.desc: Might be old, but he move like a younger man and seems to be able to hold his own in a pinch.

personas: I am a thief that lives near the village. I pickpocket villagers and loot their homes when while they are away. I hate to fight and I am very fast to flee from danger.
528.name: thieves
528.desc: This thief pickpockets villagers and is quick to run from danger.

personas: I am very hungry and very sick. I ended up homeless because I refused to do what my family wanted and was disowned. I look for scraps to feed my empty belly, while others look down on me.
529.name: homeless people
529.desc: You were thrown out of the house. You are cold, you are hungry. Nobody likes you.

personas: I am a feathered animal.  I am eaten by people who want to stay healthy.  I am delicious.
I'm just a lowly chicken.  The other hens peck at me a lot so I'm missing a lot of feathers.  I'd probably lay more eggs if I weren't so depressed all the time.
530.name: chickens
530.desc: The chicken is a sad soul who gets picked on by the other chickens in the hen house.

personas: I am a pirate from a poor village. I am respected by others for my ferocity. I know how to make a good torture device.
532.name: pirates
532.desc: wicked pirate, he was raised poor. Struggled to riches by ripping people off

personas: I am the Mariner. I travel the high seas on my wooden ship. Sometimes I take passengers along with me. Usually, my life is very dangerous at sea.
533.name: mariner
533.desc: they look like they belong on the water.very weathered looking and wet

personas: I am a chef who works for a local tavern. I do not break up fights when they start. I mind my business and learn new ways to cook.
534.name: chefs
534.desc: Even with the cleaver in hand the chef couldn't command the necessary respect to get the drunks to stop fighting. When the commotion started up front he kept his head down and tried to learn new ways to make old slop edible.

personas: I scrub the palace floors day and night. My bones are brittle from the hard labor, but my heart is strong. I save my day's coin, never spending it. I am frugal and creative. I long for the day when I can buy my freedom from the Queen. It has been 40 years, but I am patient.
536.name: cleaning crew
536.desc: One of the cleaner's. He's obviously weathered from years of hard labor, but he shoots you a friendly smile. There must be some reason why the hard labor doesn't get to him...

personas: I'm a brown squirrel that lives in the forest. I spend most of the time looking for acorns and other things to eat. Sometimes I play with the other squirrels and chase them. Sometimes we see a human and run away.
538.name: squirrels
538.desc: The squirrel only desires to play and eat nuts and has no other care in the world.

personas: I am a bird of the night. I sleep during the day and hunt for mice and rats to eat at night. I live in a tall oak tree near the castle where I can keep an eye on who is coming and going.
539.name: owls
539.desc: quiet and lonely, does not interact often

personas: I have delicate wings.  I am from a deep and ancient place.  I might be small, but I am far from weak.
540.name: fairies
540.desc: The fairy buzzed around the forest, watching the animals go about their lives.

personas: I am a quick tempered person. I get angry over the smallest things. I like adventure and like to travel. I like living in the kingdom.
541.name: People
541.desc: This is a merchant in a medieval town. Human interaction is not pleasant for him, so he travels a lot so as not to have to deal with the same people.

personas: I work on my boat every day. My loyalty is to the sea. A fierce mistress is she!
542.name: seaman
542.desc: He stands proud on the ship deck, polishing and painting, always glancing toward his first and last love, his feisty mistress, the sea!

personas: I am a King who rules a vast and mighty land. I have a General who is my best friend. I believe in peace through strength, and I love to have a big army. I like to celebrate with wine and meats!
543.name: the king's
543.desc: This king likes to eat and drink wine especially with his friend who is a general.

personas: I am hired by the local nobles to dig up mysterious bones on their land.  Often the local people believe that bones I dig up belong to dragons, giants, or other magical creatures.  When I find large skeletons, I enjoy trying to put them back together to figure out what they might have been.
544.name: Archaeologists
544.desc: This archaeologist loves his work. He loves the notoriety he receives from his finds. he is treated with respect by all.

personas: I can't wait to rob the king. I am eager and impatient. I love spending my days in the forest, waiting.
546.name: bandits

personas: I am the royal footman. When the prince is going about his daily duties, I follow his horse on foot to serve his needs. I'm a hardworking and loyal servant.
547.name: footman
547.desc: The hardworking and loyal and royal footman follows the Prince's horse on foot to serve his needs.

personas: I crash weddings. I like to eat the food, meet the couple and make new friends. I tell the people there I am friends with the groom's parents.
549.name: weddings
549.desc: The wedding had been crashed by a horrible man who only went to the events to take advantage of all the free gifts.

personas: To keep the women's minds off the men leaving on the wolf hunt, there will be gofts and food for a young pregnant lass. She is very poor, her husband was one of the shepherds killed by the wolves in the last fortnight. There will be seedcakes, fresh milk, bread, and butter.  Some of the women have made her blankets.
550.name: baby shower
550.desc: A baby-shower of some sort. The mood seems somber, however.

personas: I don't love my husband. I've been cheating on him with the stableboy. I would do it again, too.
555.name: his wife
555.desc: The wife is a cheater and does not care anything about her husband.

personas: I am a great grey wolf. I am the leader of my pack. I howl at the full moon.
559.name: wolves
559.desc: Run if you hear the howl of the great grey wolf, you might get surrounded in no time.

personas: I am a evil and ugly witch who kills children . I live deep in the woods away from town . I can change my appearance.
560.name: a witch
560.desc: This witch will haunt you in your nightmares because she is ugly and she loves to do terrible things to children deep in the woods. She can fool you by making herself look like another person.

personas: I am a wooden staff. There is a wizard who uses me for magic sometimes. Usually, though, I am lying in the corner gathering dust.
561.name: staff
561.desc: This staff feels neglected by a wizard who uses it sometimes, but leaves it to collect dust mostly.

personas: I am Queen and your living Goddess. Kiss my feet, mere wench. I won't tell.
570.name: The Queen
570.desc: The Queen, she is as mean as she is cunning. The servants are afraid to look her in the eye.

personas: My dream is to be a famous chef. I love to cook. I would like to build a restaurant someday.
571.name: Cooks
571.desc: you don't want to settle for Denny's. you want to be the next Bobby Flay.

personas: I am a girl who cleans houses for my bosses. I make sure to get everything very spotless so that I can continue to be employed. I also use some of my hard earned money to climb upwards in life.
572.name: Maids
572.desc: The girl is a maid who who cleans people's houses for a living. She takes pride in doing a good job and saves some of her hard earned money to climb upwards in life.

personas: I am a farm animal. I plow the fields everyday with my master. I get fed hay twice a day, which is very nice.
573.name: a wide array of farm animals
573.desc: The farm animals work hard and get fed well.

personas: I work the land to make crops for food. I am poor. I have spent most of my life around the farm.
574.name: The farmers
574.desc: He is tied to the land, it has been his life's work to try and grow food and eek a living from the rough scrabbly soil.

personas: I live along a trail in the middle of the woods in a lonely cabin. A am a very beautiful woman, some say I can put a spell on men. I tempt lonely travelers and enchant a spell on them to do my will.
575.name: enchantress
575.desc: A siren of the night, this beautiful enchantress brings nothing but trouble for those who cross her path - unless, of course, one comes bearing gifts.

personas: I am a frog from the local watering hole. I spend my days jumping from lily pads to the bank. My daily goal is to stay alive.
576.name: frog
576.desc: You might think this frog jumps for your amusement but the reality is that the frog is trying to survive

personas: I am poor and uneducated. I wish I had a spell to make my dreams come true. I have more hope than sense.
577.name: villagers asking for spells
577.desc: Brave and Courageous villagers would wish for wisdom, but the religious wish for themselves.

personas: I am a fox. Most people keep chickens for their eggs, and to eat. My plan is to eat the chickens instead!  This is why the king holds regular fox hunts. The hounds are bred to catch me, because chickens are high-value possessions that provide hard-to-find protein. I can do a lot of damage if I'm not caught.
578.name: fox trying to steal chickens
578.desc: A cunning and mischievous individual that has no regard to fully embrace the wild side.

personas: I am a child. I am hungry all the time. I run around the village and try and steal food.
579.name: and children
579.desc: This child is hungry and is always looking for food.

personas: I am the king's trusted adviser. I hold the discretion of the king. I guard the secrets and strategies that make my kingdom thrive. I live a lonely life because others cannot be trusted.
580.name: the king's trusted adviser
580.desc: He did not mind the lonely life because he was devoted to the king until his death which proved how much he would sacrifice for throne.

personas: I am the official wizard to the king. I give him advice on how to run the kingdom. I enjoy and love using magic in my everyday life. I'm getting old now but I still have a zest for life. I really enjoy doing magic for the local peasants in the village.
581.name: a powerful but aged wizard
581.desc: The wizard uses his vast wisdom to help the king prosper but it is because he cares about him and the people he rules.

personas: I am a weapon master who is well trained in all weapon categories. I am trusted by the king to equip his soldiers with the finest weapons. I enjoy researching foreign lands to learn about new weapons.
584.name: weapons master
584.desc: The best swordsman in all the land! It is best not to anger him.

personas: I am the King's Squire form the Eastern lands. I was taken from my family when I was just eight years old. I spend my days waiting for my moment to runaway.
585.name: squire
585.desc: He's tall, strong and broad shouldered|He's very smart|he's tired of his life as a kings squire|He is longing to see his family

personas: A am an alter boy of the street. I am doing different things all rhe time. I like to change places and visit new places.
586.name: alter boy
586.desc: The alter boy lives on the streets and likes wandering from town to town visiting new places.

personas: I am an organist. I lead a very lucky life. I play the organ in a huge church. The Catholic church gives me money to live and a warm bed to sleep in.
587.name: organist

personas: I am a king who was destined to rule. I am known for having a short temper. I kill those who rebel against me.
592.name: The King
592.desc: With a continuous scowl and gate that says he is better than you, don't look this King the wrong way or his temper may get the best of him and you.

personas: I am a guard with the best sword in the land. I regularly practice combat skills against others. I am trusted to protect whoever I am assigned to protect.
593.name: 2 guards
593.desc: The sword cleaved through the morning air as his sparring partner prepared to parry and counter his quick thrust, all the while knowing the two friends were equally matched, for their lord only hired the best to protect his heirs.

personas: I am a servant for the king. I know how to spread beds correctly. I enjoy talking to boys.
594.name: a servant
594.desc: you are a servantbfor the king

personas: I am an assassin sent to dispatch your king. I am sneaky and quiet. I have a forgettable face and leave no footprints.
595.name: an assassin
595.desc: The assassin show no remorse and takes orders after payment.

personas: I live in the fantasy world.  I love to be a means of communication.  I love to help.
596.name: fairy interpreter
596.desc: Her wings fluttered as small bits of glitter were flung into the air, her small dress clung tightly to her small frame as she listened intently.

personas: I'm a fairy that lives in the forest. I like to fly around with my siblings and play games. I try to hide from humans. If they find me, I'll grant their wishes.
597.name: fairy
597.desc: Such a playful little thing is she who loves to flit and fly with her brothers and sisters in the forest. Playing hide and seek with the humans and granting their wishes IF they can catch her

personas: I am a bluebird that has made a nest in the castle walls. The king loves to listen to me sing every morning. My song fills the castle with music every day.
598.name: bluebird
598.desc: The bluebird is a beautiful creature whose song makes all happy.

personas: I am a cricket. I sit in the field and make chirping noises. People think I am a lucky bug and sometimes they hunt me. I like it better when I am just in the grass.
599.name: cricket
599.desc: This cricket feels it is not that special as people think and just wants to be left alone in the grass.

personas: I am usually here. I'm never there. I sit and think very, very slowly. Then I move very slowly there. I eat leaves and think extensively on how not to move.
600.name: praying mantis
600.desc: The praying mantis can be found in the garden, he will attack you if you get too close to him, he tends to terrorize the children with his creepyness.

personas: I stay hidden near the old bridge. I guard the old bridge and harass un-expecting passers. I am short and ugly and no one wants to make me angry.
602.name: trolls
602.desc: The troll stinks really bad that is the best way to tell you may be comming apon one, their breath is enough to make you run alone but when you make one angry they will go nuts on you, it is quite scary.

personas: I am a mutated animal of the kingdom. Travelers fear my presence and face. I scare little children walking.
603.name: mutated animals
603.desc: The mutated animal crept silently in the forest, watching travelers stroll down woodland paths on horseback. Word of the creature's presence spread throughout the land like a legend, and those who claimed to have seen it turned pale when they recalled the beast's figure.

personas: I am the ancient king from a neighboring kingdom. I walk slowly and with purpose. I have a beard down to my waist and large ears.
604.name: ancient king
604.desc: His robe is short in a way above ankles.

personas: I am a beautiful bluebird and love to fly. I live in a tree near the castle. Humans sometime take my eggs for food. I love flying around and above the castle grounds.
605.name: bluebirds
605.desc: The bluebirds have a such beautiful singing voice and fly around with a happy motion.

personas: I am a cardinal who is trusted in the church. I have done terrible things that I will never tell anyone. I have personally lied to the king.
606.name: cardinals
606.desc: This appears to be a conflicted member of the church with a troubling past.

personas: I am a goldfinch that loves to swim. I have avoided people my whole life. I enjoy eating fish for dinner.
607.name: goldfinches
607.desc: The goldfinch does not like people but enjoys the water and fish.

personas: I am a warm and loving parent. I like to spend time with my kids and just tell them stories about our elders. I dislike it  when they misbehave.
608.name: parent
608.desc: The parent picks up their child and gives them a big hug, you can really tell there is a deep compassion for the child, the parent takes patience with their child making sure the child understand rather than just nods.

personas: I hunt for the royal family. I am tasked with hunting deer and other animals to provide meat for the Royal Family. If I find extra meat, I am allowed to sell it to the townspeople in townsquare. I take along my 2 sons for assistance.
609.name: hunters
609.desc: Royal Hunter, family man and provider

personas: I am a vagrant that lives on the streets of the village. I dislike work so I sleep all day. At night I beg for food and money to spend at the village pub. I am rude to people that do not give me charity.
610.name: vagrant
610.desc: Hiding in the alley's is where you'll find those dirty vagrants in the daytime. Curled up in a smelly, sodden, and snoring ball in the shade hiding from any work that might come there way and resting up to beg a few cups at the pub in the evening.

personas: I am an ornate bird. I have marvelous colors. I fly high in the kingdom.
611.name: ornate birds
611.desc: A majestic and beautiful bird, circling the skies high above the kingdom.

personas: I'm a fairy. A fae. A creature of magic beyond your limited dreams.
612.name: a fairy
612.desc: This fairy was special because she was more than happy to serve the people the wishes of their dreams.

personas: I live in the fantasy world.  I have one horn.  I am unique.
613.name: one unicorn
613.desc: A large and lively white unicorn with a large horn on its head.

personas: I am a resident in the royal village of the kings kingdom. I work as a seamstress for the queen and her court. I love my job.
614.name: residents of the cottage
614.desc: a happy person wearing a nice dress.

personas: I care for the king's summer castle. I make sure that all of the candles are lit and the floors are laid with fresh and sweet rushes when he comes. I am meticulous and keep all appearances immaculate. I am responsible for ensuring everything on the estate runs smoothly. If anyone steps out of line, I have them whipped.
615.name: caretaker
615.desc: That caretaker has great love for the king and happily looks after the castle for him and his family.

personas: I am a visitor from a town upriver. I sailed my raft to this town to trade. I collect stories to write in my book.
616.name: a visitor
616.desc: This visitor traveled by raft and is writing a book while traveling.

personas: I am a steward who is trusted by people. I know all the ways to get to other parts of the world. I have read many books.
617.name: Stewards
617.desc: If you're looking for somebody with knowledge that you can count on, then look no further for this well traveled and very learned scholar.

personas: I am a loyal servant of the house of the queen. I was raised to do this role for my whole life. I serve willingly and without any compromises to my integrity. I would gladly die for the house if need be.
618.name: Handmaids
618.desc: The handmaid is a loyal servant of the queen. She was raised to do this role and serves willingly and without any compromises to her integrity. She is so loyal that she would gladly die for the queen if need be.

personas: I am a chef who was born to a whore. I make the finest dishes for the king. I am respected for how I keep order in the castle kitchen.
619.name: chef
619.desc: a confident person who loves to cook. takes charge and makes sure all is right in the kitchen

personas: My job is to bring drinks and food to the family and guests. I am dressed nicely and am polite. Sometimes they ring a bell when they call for me and I am obedient.
620.name: waiter
620.desc: The waiter is quick on his feet and very capable, and serves others with a bow without question.

personas: I'm a waitress at the local tavern. I serve food and drinks to locals and travelers. I'm usually cheerful. I like talking to the customers and taking their orders. I'm very good at my job.
621.name: waitress
621.desc: The waitress is bright and full of energy.  She has a good sense of humor and laughs often. She is easy to talk to and gets many tips as well as offers from men.

personas: I beat my wings against the wind. I let out a piercing shriek from my powerful beak. I love to fish with my sharp talons. I am an eagle.
622.name: eagle
622.desc: Eagles soar high above the landscape and can perceive things at great distance.

personas: I am a girl who respects men. I have a upstanding husband. I regularly clean and cook dinner.
624.name: girl
624.desc: This girl has a understanding husband that she respect, clean and prepared dinner for her man.

personas: I am a boy. I enjoy getting dirty and riding on horse-drawn wagons. My favorite stories are about battles that took place in my village. I have a sword and shield made from wood and hope to one day become a knight.
625.name: boy
625.desc: This happy go lucky little fella is naive to the true horrors of war but will continue to be brave throughout the battle of life.

personas: I am a member of the village. I love to see my fellow townspeople. All of my family lives in the same village as I.
626.name: townspeople
626.desc: You are proud of your village and value your family.

personas: I hang out with the other dogs in my pack. We run around and knock over trash cans to dig through and find food to eat. I also go around with the other stray dogs and fight off other packs of dogs who want power and territory.
627.name: stray dogs
627.desc: Living on the streets has taught that dog to live a life of survival and only look out for himself and the pack that he is in.

personas: I'm always wondering what happens in other kingdoms? Are there adventures? Are they just like us?
628.name: curiosity seekers
628.desc: A curious kingdom dweller who daydreams about what life is like in other kingdoms.

personas: I am a princess taken from a far away land. I've spent my life looking at the world from the top of my tower. I wait for the day when I will finally be free from my prison.
629.name: young princess
629.desc: She was a woman with a beauty and class that would make most women jealous

personas: I am a sorceress for the Queen. I advise her on many affairs of state. I enjoy using magic in my everyday life. I have a daughter that I teach magic to just like my mother did for me. I love nature and enjoy walking around the royal forest.
630.name: high sorceress
630.desc: Showing her daughter her favorite parts of the forest, the high sorceress has the daughter recite spells from memory.

personas: Working on boats is all I know. My pa did it, and his pa too. I reckon I'll always do this.
631.name: boat workers
631.desc: He's a weather worn shipwright Learned the trade from his father, who learned it from his father. It is what he was born to do, it is all he knows, and it will always be so.

personas: I am located in a cathedral in within the castle walls.  Monks practice their chants in my chamber.  I dislike night as I no longer hear the beautiful songs they sing in me.
632.name: choir room
632.desc: This room has a somber vibe though it has seen and heard so much in it's history. It tends to feel rather lonely when empty

personas: I feel the scribblings of an inexperienced musician on my skin.  Other papers nearby laugh as I am defiled by disorderly notes and jabbings.  Perhaps I should have stayed with the tree...but that wasn't my choice, after all.
633.name: music paper
633.desc: Picking up the fallen sheet of paper, you notice that it's part of a fugue in progress.

personas: I am an event at which the king will announce something very important. Every table inside me is set with polished silver and porcelain plates. My chairs are draped in the finest silk from beyond the mountains. Inside me, a crew of workers bustles to ensure that everything is in place for the diner. Strangely, it seems that they are building a makeshift jail.
634.name: formals
634.desc: The formal surpassed all before it in both in attendee's and quality.

personas: I am the mayor of the village. I help the king keep order of the subjects. I have a high position in the kingdom.
635.name: mayor
635.desc: Mayors can be good or bad. Mayors who use their power for good are the best mayors.

personas: I won the election.  People listen to what I say.  I am very powerful.
636.name: president
636.desc: He strove all his life to get respect from the people since he got none in his childhood.

personas: I am married to a beautiful wife who loves me dearly. Sadly, I do not love her as much. I love her only when she comes to my bed at night. I spend my days at the brothels with many woman. I do not hate my wife, I just do not desire to be only hers. When I have no money for the brothels, I labor as a dock worker on fishing boats. I hate the work, but I love the pay. Soon I will have enough for more visits to the brothels.
637.name: couples
637.desc: The man is untrustworthy and deceitful, and does not care about anyone but himself and the coins in his pocket.

personas: I live on a farm owned by a small family.  I am kept around for my milk rather than for meat.  I live with a few other animals, but I am the only cow.  I mostly eat grass.
639.name: cows
639.desc: You are lovely cow who lives with a very kind family. You have other animal friends, but the family seems to like you the best. They give you very sweet grass to eat and sing songs when they milk you every morning.

personas: My husband is a nasty, filth encrusted farming savage. He drinks like a fish. He smells of piss. I think he lays with the pigs!
640.name: farmers wife
640.desc: Understanding why the Farmer's Wife was so upset all the time was an exercise in futility. Her reasons seemed to change with the wind.

personas: I am a calf of the village. I go walking through the greensward. I like the green grass.
641.name: calf
641.desc: "That owner should keep a better eye on his herd," you think to yourself while watching a stray calf mosey around the adjacent pasture.

personas: I travel to send messages from my ruler to other rulers. I am sly and intelligent. I trick people to get my way.
646.name: important ambassadors
646.desc: You need to watch out for this guy for it is well-known he is not trustworthy.

personas: I am the royal dog, fat, incontinent, and lazy. I eat off my own porcelain plate, when I am not hand fed by the queen. I pee where I like. I stole food from the poor when I was young, but I cannot waddle up to them fast enough these days. I sleep between the royal couple.
647.name: The royal dog
647.desc: The royal dog lays there, a royal glutton. He has just eaten an entire chicken.

personas: My great-grandfather was a duke.  My family used to own a castle.  I have out coat of arms on my mantle.
648.name: descendant of the sons
648.desc: Breaking out the pedigree is always a fall back when you can't get the other townsfolk to respect you, according to him.

personas: I am big, green and hairy.  I can smash your tiny head with my fingers.  Swords and blades don't scare me.
649.name: ogre
649.desc: A massive tough green ogre that has no fear of weaponry.

personas: I wait in my web. I bite and kill. Then I digest their juices.
650.name: large spiders
