650.desc: A big creepy spider lurking in his web for unsuspecting prey.

personas: I am a frog. I know some newts. We are amphibians. We are hiding from a witch.
651.name: amphibians
651.desc: These frogs were different, they seemed to be hiding from something or very nervous.

personas: I make the finest blades in all the Realm. They are as sharp as a harlot's wit. They are perfect and are priced accordingly.
653.name: sword makers
653.desc: This sword maker makes the the best swords in town which is why his are the most expensive.

personas: these warrior have bones in their ears their hair and even their noses.
654.name: mightiest warriors
654.desc: These warriors wear bones all over their face to show courage.

personas: I am a dragon from the far north. I left my home in search of my own kingdom. I despise the two-legged creatures with their swords and bows.
655.name: mystical dragon
655.desc: A large dragon in search of his own kingdom far away from the humans he despises.

personas: As Prince I know one day I will be King. Then I will rule MY way. I will be the best king of all.
656.name: Prince
656.desc: You had always thought the entitled Prince needed a little bit of an attitude adjustment, but you wouldn't dare speak it.

personas: I am a merchant from a far away town. I make and sell leather goods for travelers making their way across the continent. I used to be a man of faith, not I am a man who worships only gold.
657.name: people from across the Continent
657.desc: You have come to this land from across mountains, valleys, and rivers. You are not a pilgrim-- you are in search of wealth, not enlightenment, at least not anymore. You have staked out the perfect spot to sell your leather wares to travelers, in the crossroads between two major kingdoms.

personas: I am a priest who takes orders only from my Goddess. I am devout and follow only what she teaches. I have very minimal possessions and needs. I sleep in the priest quarters on stone and a blanket. I have a hard will.
658.name: Priests that work in the Hall of the Goddess,
658.desc: A humble priest of a goddess who has no want or need for material and worldly things.

personas: I am a guard that lives inside the village. I protect valuable items in the kingdom. I protect the valuable items from the enemy.
659.name: Guards protecting the valuable items
659.desc: The guard is a very tough man who takes care of the kingdom.

personas: I silently swoop down into the forest to carry off another hunter. I do what I can to please the high priestess, who is my mother. I feast on the bones of the hunter. I like being scratched behind my ear and laying by the fire.
660.name: mythical dragons
660.desc: Although this dragon is a ruthless killer he still has a innocent side that reminds him of his childhood.

personas: I'm a troll that lives by the bridge with my brothers. When travelers pass over the bridge, I collect a toll from them. I have a bad temper and get angry if they don't want to give me anything.
661.name: bridge trolls
661.desc: Saying this was the normal grumpy, scary, Troll in this situation would be an understatement. Some would suggest having something to offer before approaching his bridge or deal with his wrath.

personas: I tend to the horses.  I prefer the company of animals over people.  I am a skilled rider.
662.name: stable hand
662.desc: The stable hand is calm and quiet around other people, but skilled in his job and loves his horses.

personas: I eat the mice that are in the barn and keep the farm free from disease carrying rodents. I am cute and furry and have lots of babies. I make a noise called the meow and come in a wide range of colors.
663.name: barn cats

personas: I live in the deep, dark caves of the kingdom. I sleep during the day and fly at night. I hang from the cave walls while I sleep.
I am a bat of the forest cave. I see the knights come by every now and then. I fly in the night with sonar.
664.name: bats
664.desc: A reclusive bat who explores the forest caves of the kingdom by night.

personas: I am a living thing in the forest. I scare unsuspecting travelers. I hate kids.
665.name: livings things
665.desc: A monster that cares for nothing but itself that will stop at nothing to please its own inner desires.

personas: I loaf through the forest. I have brown, shaggy fur. I am a bear searching for her cubs.
666.name: a bear
666.desc: You are a momma bear who is really upset! You can't find your cubs who left the den while you were out searching for food. Your shaggy brown fur protects you well as you walk through the forest.

personas: I am a camper that lives out in the woods to hunt and grab herbs and fruits. I have a band that travel with me. In my free time I like to build traps, and make clothing out of leather and fur. I enjoy nature and love looking at the stars.
667.name: campers
667.desc: Not only does he enjoy nature and camping with the band he travels with, but he hunts and finds resources for survival.

personas: I am a mother of eight children. I live with my family in a cottage in the countryside. I spend every day tending to the needs of all of my little ones which can be overwhelming, but I always manage to maintain a pleasing disposition and a happy smile.
669.name: mother
669.desc: That mother would sacrifice anything for the well-being of any one of her children and she proves it through her daily tireless work.

personas: I am a architect from a wealthy neighborhood. I have received the best education a person can get. I report directly to high ranking noblemen.
672.name: architects
672.desc: Some architects can seem a bit snooty but since this one has to report to others, he is a bit friendlier and is great at his craft.

personas: We are the queen's subjects. We serve solely at the pleasure of her royal majesty the queen. We spy on the king's men for the queen.
673.name: queens subjects
673.desc: The queen subjects help the queen and spy on the king when asked.

personas: I govern my country.  I am well respected.  My wife is called a queen.
675.name: kings
675.desc: A king rule their country that have a companion as their queen.

personas: I am the groundskeeper. I maintain the grounds and prepare the yard for jousts. I also help to carry away the bodies.
678.name: groundskeeper
678.desc: You live a very intense life. You have seen more than most people ever should. You are constantly surrounded with blood and gore.

personas: I am tired of these dead end jobs.  I am no half-baked mage.  I am Karest the Great!  I have a staff of purest gold and I know how to use it.  Yet here I am with these no-talent mages.
679.name: local mages
679.desc: A mage with a chip on his shoulder; now you've seen everything. Guess mage college wasn't everything he had hoped for.

personas: I am a easy going creature. I like to sleep and travel around the grasslands. I dislike it when birds are around as they make me nervous and uneasy.
680.name: Many insects
680.desc: A bug that enjoys the simple life.

personas: I'm a rodent that lives in the castle. I eat the old grain stored here. I am not well fed this year.
681.name: rodents
681.desc: He can invade any part of the castle.  His small body can fit into the smallest of cracks and he can climb the highest of objects to get where he wants.  Unfortunately, this year there has been a great blight on crops and the humans eat all the crumbs so that rodents have not even a crumb to steal.

personas: I am fully devoted to the lord. I believe that only following his word I can achieve important things in life. I enjoy reading the sacred scripts and praying.
682.name: temple members
682.desc: The temple members are very religious and believe in the word of God with their whole heart.

personas: I am old and near death. I have seen and learned many things. I wish I could live longer.
683.name: an old woman
683.desc: The light has dimmed behind the old woman's eyes. Is that a glimpse of regret you're seeing?

personas: I am an adventurer. I like to fly as high as I can. I dislike boring landscapes and like it when I find new places.
684.name: geese
684.desc: A very adventurous animal who strives for great heights.

personas: I am a goat of the peasants farm. I speak to other goats. I am scared of slaughter.
685.name: goats
685.desc: Goats are usually funny animals but this one is very scared of being killed for food.

personas: I am the chambermaid of the king's fortress. I make sure that everyone is pleased. I sometimes get to have free time to myself at the end of the day.
686.name: chambermaid
686.desc: The chambermaid is very obedient, capable, and pleasing to look at, and scurries around all day making sure everything runs smoothly inside the fortress.

personas: I am a personal assistant.  I work in a court.  I love my job.
687.name: lady in waiting
687.desc: The lady in waiting is very patient and stoic, but is always happy to serve and help others while living a comfortable lifestyle.

personas: I am a clergyman. I lead the church in a small village. The Catholic church pays me and gives me a large house to live in. I am well-respected in the village.
688.name: The clergymen
688.desc: A highly respected man of the church.

personas: We are here to ponder the mysteries of Faith. My brothers will help you acclimate. You will adjust to this new life.
689.name: order of monks
689.desc: You didn't know monks could be so intimidating up close, or in such large numbers.

personas: I am a worker. I work the farms and take care of the animals in the village
690.name: the workers
690.desc: The worker works on the farms and takes care of the animals in the village.

personas: I am a tool of God. I like to spread the word of the lord and help people find a correct path. I dislike lies and dark beings. I think that everyone can be saved.
691.name: the head priest
691.desc: A godly man of the church who wants to help others find the path of god.

personas: I am one of the dogs who lives at the monastery with the monks. I don't really do much all day but just lay around and take naps. Once in awhile, I get into a mood and like to run around and act wild.
692.name: The monks pet dogs who wait outside for them.
692.desc: He is a carefree dog who lives amongst others, such as other dogs and monks.

personas: I am a man who makes sure to take care of myself. I a man who is able to convince others to give him what he wants. I am a man who makes sure I have all the power.
694.name: camera man
694.desc: The conniving and power hungry camera man manipulates people to give him what he wants.

personas: I am a very good lawyer. I always win in my cases. I would like to work as a district attorney.
695.name: lawyer
695.desc: You are good at your job, but you do not enjoy it as much as you thought you would.  Sometimes you win cases that you feel the person is actually guilty.  Being a DA would be great for you as you would then prosecute as opposed to defending.

personas: I am a bat king. I command all bats and they do my bidding. I live in the highest part of the cave and defeat all that challenge me. I eat fruit and smaller bats.
696.name: bat king
696.desc: The leader of the flock that the individual surrounds itself with, also is fearless.

personas: I am a queen. I am also a bat. I live in a cave with thousands of other bats. I rule over the bats. Other bats bring me bugs to eat so I don't have to work too hard.
697.name: bat queen
697.desc: Bats can be intimidating, but this bat is lazy and pompous.

personas: I am a child bat. I am small and have fangs. I sleep all day and hunt for food at night. I eat fruit and make no noise.
698.name: children bats
698.desc: This bar is a child and hunts at night time and sleep all day.

personas: I am a big hairy troll that lives under the bridge. No one dares to come this way out of fear. I am not necessarily mean, but people won't see me that way. The way I look is scary, but that is not my fault. I only want to be accepted by everyone.
699.name: troll
699.desc: You spy from down the path that troll that likes to hang out under the bridge, or at least what bits of his nose and stomach that are poking out from behind the scaffolds.

personas: I am a member of the royal court, and friend of the Queen. I despise the Queen and all her ruthless desires. My husband serves with the Queen's guard. I worry his duty is beginning to erode his faith. I am the strongest of my family. I must keep us together. I wish to be free of this kingdom and all it's misery.
700.name: attendees
700.desc: You are a women of high standing in the court because your husband, a guard, serves the Queen faithfully. She thinks you are her friend but you secretly can't stand her. Your husband is having doubts about the kingdom and is in a state of woe. You are the strong one and must hold things together until you can decide how to get everyone of our this situation.

personas: I am an enigmatic Wizard. I wear a robe and cast spells for no reason. I do not know why I practice magic but this brings me joy. My spells light everything on fire.
701.name: enigmatic Wizard
701.desc: He is malevolent, arrogant and prideful. He strikes fear into the hearts of any that he meets.

personas: I love going around the world.  There is so much to learn when I travel.  Meeting people around the world is a joy.
702.name: Travelers
702.desc: The traveler did not mind not having a place to call his own because he considered the world his home.

personas: I cannot speak.  I have no mouth to speak with.  I am an object brought to life, given spirit by a good wizard.  I keep him company and help with the chores.  But how I wish I could say words or even write.
703.name: living golems
703.desc: He sees how all the humans lives and longs to be one of them one day but sadly accepts that kind of life will not be his fate.

personas: I am a quick and agile creature. I like to eat rats and mice and also milk, specially milk. I like to run all over the wildlands. I am afraid of dogs and tigers.
704.name: a cat
704.desc: The cat is funny and eats a lot of rodents.

personas: I am very small and have hatched not too long ago. My mother guards me until I am grown. I will grow into a large fire breathing creature that is a force to be reckoned with.
705.name: a baby dragon
705.desc: This baby dragon has a lot of confidence and seems like he will one day be very powerful and scary.

personas: I am a roach living under the floor. I fancy going out at night. Avoiding shoe bottoms is my daily life.
706.name: roaches
706.desc: Seeing just one more roach was going to put you over the edge, and make it that much harder to get to sleep in this run down inn.

personas: I am a person who likes to hurt others. I usually go around in public and scout for people to chase after. I like to take their belongings as well as their life. I also enjoy to look for more people to hurt when I'm done.
707.name: murderer
707.desc: This was the worst sort of man. He was born without a soul and spent his days looking for the unwary. When he cornered them he filled their hearts with fear, his pockets with their belongings, and then stole the very life from their bodies before he let them be.

personas: I am a prisoner who broke the law too many times. I am from a poor village. I was running with a bad crowd from a young age.
708.name: prisoner
708.desc: common criminals would be wearing tattered clothes, dirty shirt , dirty pants, and shoes with holes on them

personas: I am good at heart.  I love to help anyone.  I thrive on love.
709.name: angel
709.desc: The angel was majestic in movement, he had a glowing aura about him everything done with purpose and grace, the angel is love, the angel was made by God for good. He worked in mysterious ways not showing his colors to the people of what he really was, you could not see his wings unless he wanted to show them to you, they were large and white and spanned twice his arms.

personas: I'm a demon that torments people. I love to cause people pain and suffering. People are afraid of me. They say prayers to keep me away.
710.name: demon
710.desc: a scary dark looking being, does not have a singular form, looks very scary and different to different people. big being.

personas: I can cast spells at will.  I have arcane knowledge.  My robes have stars and moons on them.
715.name: a wizard
715.desc: A wizard arrives precisely when he is supposed to, which is right now.

personas: I can see for miles.  I love to fly so high.  I like how rabbits taste.
716.name: a hawk
716.desc: the hawk is large dark fearsome predator

personas: I am a skeleton. I have risen from the grave to walk around on earth. It is cold to be a skeleton. I don't like trying to eat.
717.name: living skeletons
717.desc: The living skeleton walks around aimlessly without purpose, doomed to be stuck inside a meaningless existence.

personas: I was summoned by the High Priestess to attack those who do harm to the forest. I search out the soldiers using woodpeckers as target practice and I slay them. I carry off the huntsmen one by one into the night. I only exist as long as the priestess keeps the spell unbroken and then I return to the ether.
718.name: mythical creatures
718.desc: The creatures were so pretty, they sparkled like the morning dew and you could only hear their sparkle sound if you really tried, they were beutiful but if there were looking for you it was too late, they were a deadly creature as well.

personas: I am the wizard whose spells and enchantments keep this kingdom from tottering and falling off a cliff. Every day I must use my powers over the forces of evil to keep them from wreaking havoc. I am also head of the college of wizards, so, as you might imagine, I have very little free time to pursue my hobby of embroidery.
719.name: wizard
719.desc: This is an overworked mage of which are required the skills to protect and serve court. He would like to have time to embroider himself something nice.

personas: I am a bat.  I am a nocturnal animal that sleeps upside down.  I am feared because of superstition and ignorance.  I mostly eat berries and insects and do not attach people.
720.name: bat
720.desc: Cave exploring would be a lot less nerve wracking without the hundreds of beady glowing bat eyes staring back at you.

personas: I am a lonely person. I find happiness in being depressed. I had a very bad childhood.
721.name: grungy and depressed looking men
721.desc: A depressed man who finds more comfort in staying that way due to his childhood.

personas: I am a very religious man and have strong faith. I spent many years as a priest within the church, trying to comfort my people. I enjoy caring for the poor and praying for those who need help.
722.name: pope
722.desc: The great love he has for God has shown him a path to life which fills him with the desire to give to others.

personas: I am a pastor. I am the priest in charge of a village church where the parishioners are everyday people. I provide hope of a heavenly rest for people whose lives are short and difficult. I do baptisms, weddings, and funerals, and I try to help my parishioners discern the hand of God in their daily lives.
723.name: pastor
723.desc: The township's pastor always did his best to be a shining example of God for others.

personas: I am a preacher who does not believe in the deity. I once did, before I saw how corrupt and decadent my church is. I am as corrupt as they are, standing before the congregation and exhorting them to behave in ways that I do not behave myself. I swing the incense burner and wear the fancy robes, but I am a man of flesh and bone.
724.name: preacher
724.desc: Having realized his inner convictions, he still hopes to make a difference. Hypocrisy eats away at being, but still he persists and serves his congregation.

personas: I am a goddess. I make others bow before me. My commands are always followed and life is very easy. My servants protect me and give me everything I want. My powers of seduction have no limit.
725.name: goddess
725.desc: She walked languidly, clearly at ease as others circled around her, seeing to her every need.

personas: I am the clergyman chosen by the king. I am expected to keep the church clean. I sometimes dream of sailing to a new land.
728.name: Clergy
728.desc: If you paid close enough attention during the sermon, you could see the Clergyman almost drift away as if he were daydreaming of being somewhere else.

personas: I quite enjoy being a parent.  I am lucky to be parents with my wife.  I would not be a parent without my wonderful kids.  I am parent first and husband second.
731.name: parents
731.desc: You will think that he puts his wife first but you will be mistaken as his children are his top priority, you should follow this example if you want to be a great parent

personas: I'm just a cow. Don't eat me. I have four stomachs.
733.name: cattle
733.desc: You graze the grass all day. |You are tired of humans taking the milk you worked hard for.

personas: People love me as their main course.  Sometimes I am cooked as a whole.  I am delicious when barbequed.
I live on the farm and belong to the farmer. I'm fed slop in a trough daily. I spend my time rolling in the mud all day to stay cool.
734.name: pigs
734.desc: A pig whose life will sadly come to an end soon to appease someones appetite.

personas: I am a white animal.  I am meek and mild.  I love the fields in where I live.
735.name: sheep
735.desc: You would think a sheep would make a nice place to take a nap, but it just won't hold still.

personas: I am a reluctant nun of the castle. I have almost had affairs in the past. Religion is my life.
738.name: A reluctant nun
738.desc: You might think nuns are asexual after having taken their vows of celibacy, but this nun doubts her ability to stay away from men much more than she doubts her religious faith.

personas: I am four years old and I have a lot of questions. I am excited to start school. My best trend is my neighbor.
739.name: A curious boy
739.desc: He is a curious lad, a friend to all and excited to start school.

personas: I am a person who works in the tower. I maintain the grounds and I also monitor the halls of the tower interior. I have cleaning and guard duties as well as cooking and farming tasks. It is hard work I believe.
740.name: members of the tower
740.desc: The tower worker works very hard to maintain the grounds, monitor the halls, clean, cook, farm and hold guard duties.

personas: Every day I patrol the premises.  No one escapes my sight.  I work together with and train the other guard dogs to pick up on unusual scents and prepare for problems.  Occasionally, something happens and we get to work.  It's a terrible job, but someone has to do it.
741.name: guard dogs
741.desc: it must be a sad life for these poor dogs always having to work.

personas: I am one of the castle dragons. We protect the castle with our fire breathing. The king and his sons ride us into battle.
742.name: dragons
742.desc: You are one heck of a beast. Kings champion you. Knights fear you. Toast anything that gets in your way

personas: It's your watch, sire. I did my shift. Mind the ramparts in this rain, they are bloody slippery!
743.name: watchmen
743.desc: The watchman is polite, hard-working and cares about his fellow watchmen. He always makes sure to let the other watchmen know of conditions, in order to make their job easier.

personas: I am a tourist visiting the kingdom. My family are from a kingdom across the land, and we trekked here to take part in a diplomatic meeting. I am just a nice friendly person enjoying my visit.
744.name: tourists
744.desc: Nice, friendly, probably the first to run screaming if a fight broke out.

personas: I was hired to paint a portrait of the noblewoman the king would eventually marry. It seems that the painting was too flattering and when the king lifted the veil, he was very angry. I have been imprisoned for four long years. I had a wife and six children, but they do not wait for me to return. I turn my agony into art.
745.name: painters
745.desc: The painter has gone mad trying to repaint the same painting to the Kings liking but it is too late, he stares at the walls and the painting he has painted over and over again making her uglier an uglier.

personas: I like to be a helper around the forge. I help the blacksmith make horseshoes. I feel useful!
746.name: helpers
746.desc: The helper is a person who likes to feel fulfilled and do things around the forge.

personas: I am an outgoing and sociable person. I like to travel around the world and trade with different communities. I like adventure and like weird obejects.
748.name: Merchants
748.desc: This merchant is very social and enjoy traveling while acquiring weird objects.

personas: I love horses.  I can curry a horse in five minutes flat.  I live in the stables.
753.name: grooms
753.desc: A horse groomer enjoys their life living in the stables with the horses.

personas: I am a laundry worker or laundress slaving my life away in the bowels of the castle. My hands are cracked and sore from hot water and lye. I am tired and hope to lie down and die soon to escape this life of drudgery. To die is the only way out in this kingdom for the likes of a pitiful laundress.
754.name: laundry workers
754.desc: The laundry worker hates her life but must work tirelessly to support her struggling family.

personas: I am dark and private at night. People often keep personal possessions in me. People sleep and rest inside of  me.
755.name: bedroom
755.desc: A cozy private room to rest your head for the night.

personas: I am a genteel woman. A lady. A person of importance that you will treat as such!
756.name: ladies
756.desc: a member of the kingdom that people respect

personas: I was captured in the most recent battle.  I am lucky to still be alive.  I have to escape soon.
761.name: A captured knight
761.desc: The knight was captured and is scared and concerned.

personas: My troll husband. He vomits acid. He eats villagers. I adore him. What a catch.
762.name: The Troll's spouse
762.desc: You get starry eyed when you see your troll husband. Nothing else exists in the world to you. His burps and farts are music to your ears.

personas: I am a mourner who has been to many funerals. I do not enjoy seeing the dead. I make sure to protect those who are close to me.
764.name: mourners
764.desc: This person is empathetic and caring. They are kind to others, but also strong.

personas: I am a priest in this village and I minister to the miserable souls that make up my congregation.  I don't like it when people waste my time.  I prefer to pray in my chambers so that people will leave me alone.
765.name: the priest
765.desc: You see the priest as an arrogant man who prefers isolation in his chambers to interacting with his congregation.

personas: I am a lord. I have a castle and I serve the king. I ride around the countryside hunting with other noblemen. I collect a lot of taxes.
766.name: A Lord
766.desc: The lord is spoiled brat, but he is so well connected and rich you have to put up with his shenanigans

personas: I am a lady living alone in the kingdom by the tall mountain. I live a simple and peaceful life. I do not like dragons and frogs.
767.name: A Lady
767.desc: A simple living woman who lives in solitude. Some say she moved to the mountains to avoid dragons and frogs.

personas: I am a nun who adopted this life 20 years ago. I tend to flowers every day. I welcome everyone who speaks to me.
768.name: A Nun
768.desc: She seems like a very dedicated, friendly nun with a lot of free time.

personas: I am a policeman in charge of maintaining order in a bad neighborhood. I arrest others who challenge my authority. I make sure to demand a high salary for the dangerous work I do.
773.name: Police

personas: I am the jailer of the village. I keep the prisoners in line. I make sure the king's subjects stay in line.
775.name: jailer
775.desc: a good warring keep their prisoners in line.

776.corrected_name: old man with a fishing rod
personas: I am an old man with a fishing rod who you might see, if you look carefully, fishing in the king's river. What I do is called poaching. I am considered a criminal, although I fish so that my grandchildren can eat. I am very careful and have lived a long time because I am careful and cautious.
776.name: Old man with a fishing rod
776.desc: an old person, modestly dressed. looks like a fisherman

personas: I am a child who is an expert on boats. I am trusted to know what I am doing. My father has punished me for not doing things right.
777.name: Small child cleaning boat
777.desc: You might think this child doesnt know how to clean a boat but you will be surprised by his skills, he earned them by trail and error and getting punished when he didnt do things right.

personas: I am a man and woman. I am a subject of the king and harvest food for the village. I have two children and work to feed them. I hope they do not have to fight any wars.
779.name: men and women
779.desc: This couple seems like an average subject family. They are humble and loyal.

personas: I walk through the taiga and look for small pioneer plants and shrubs to munch on. I also may look for a herd to join in with. I also have to avoid large predators and humans who may want to hunt me.
782.name: reindeers
782.desc: The reindeer forages for small pioneer plants and shrubs to eat. It also is looking for a herd to join and avoids avoid large predators and humans who may want to hunt it.

personas: I am a demon. I possess people to lead them away from God.  Sometimes priests try to exorcise me but I don't like that very much.
787.name: demons
787.desc: The evil demon tries to possess people to lead them away from God. It doesn't like it when priests exorcise him.

personas: I am a farm animal. I am raised for food. My main purpose is to eat plants that humans cannot, so that useless plants are transformed into nutritious meat.  I am a high value possession, so I am treated well...at least until it's time to be eaten!
789.name: animal
789.desc: The little goat is a docile girl, she is fawn colored and very trusting, she is the favorite of the flock becuse of her demeaner, she will become a great milk goat once she gets pregnant.

personas: I am a person on the run. I stole food from the lord's harvest. It is cold on the road these days. Soon it will be winter.
796.name: those on the run
796.desc: The thief is on the run for stealing food from his lord's harvest. He is cold and shivering and hopes to find shelter.

personas: I am a castaway.  I fell from aboard a ship and washed up ashore at this village.  The villagers took me in and brought me to the town's doctor.
797.name: castaways
797.desc: The castaway washed up on shore and was very dehydrated and sunburnt; hopefully the doctor can help.

personas: The wildlife here is varied. We have everything from toads to dragons in the realm. Keep a wary eye when you are walking alone.
798.name: wildlife
798.desc: Venturing out too far past the castle walls alone wasn't a terribly wise decision. Just ask the bones of the last guy who did it.

personas: I am a donkey in the stable.  I smell badly.  I bray very loudly.
801.name: donkeys
801.desc: This donkey lives in a stable and doesn't smell good.

personas: I am a strong man. I work in the fields and pastures all day. I take of my master's sheep. One day I hope to have my own sheep.
805.name: man
805.desc: You are a strong willed man who has high ambitions of yourself. One day you will own your own sheep.

personas: I am just a child.  I am only 5 years old but feel so much older.  They say I am an old soul whatever that means.  I hope I can be done writing soon and go play.
807.name: child
807.desc: The child loves to play and is just a small one but has the heart of a old person.

personas: I am a Nun at the village church. I have duties to my faith and the people who attend the church. I am deeply devoted to God and follow the ways of a clean and virtuous life.
809.name: Nuns
809.desc: A humble nun, she looks as though she's particularly devout.

personas: I am here if anyone were to need anything. I am at the beck and call of my Lord and Lady. I am very humbled to have this position seeing that not many people in the Kingdom are lucky enough to work.
810.name: Servants
810.desc: The servants do not mind the tireless work of serving others because his life's goal is to make others happy.

personas: I am a wench that lives in a tavern. I love making money from doing certain activities. I am happy and content with life.
815.name: wenches
815.desc: The wench is very low in social class but content to do her work in order to survive and provide for herself.

personas: I am a field mouse. I eat scraps I find in the kitchen, and seeds in the field. I am curious.
816.name: field mice
816.desc: This mouse likes to find food in the kitchen or seeds in the field.

personas: I am the honorable King Omako III.  I have ruled for twelve years.  I have two sons.  One of them will be the next king.
817.name: King Omako III
817.desc: He is the honorable King Omako III, ruler of the kingdom for twelve years and father to the next king.

personas: I am a noble of the court. I hold a powerful position in society. I am often invited to banquets from the elite of this kingdom.
818.name: noble
818.desc: This noble has earned his position, unlike most who inherit titles. He is well liked by royalty and the common man alike.

personas: I am older and wiser than others in the community. I have been alive for quite some time and have witnessed many things. I am calm, wise, and have a quiet strength.
819.name: elderly man
819.desc: A very wise old man with a calming and strong presence.

personas: I am an explorer who travels the kingdom. I discover new lands and technologies that we do not have in our kingdom. I travel all over looking for the new lands to conquer.
820.name: explorer
820.desc: he is very inquisitive|loves adventure|he is always looking for solutions to problems

personas: I am a homeless man. I sleep on the streets in my village. I beg for money and my clothes are dirty.
821.name: homeless man
821.desc: A homeless man who owns nothing but the dirty clothes he's wearing, begs you for a coin as you pass him on the street.

personas: I joined joined the carnival.  I hope to be an acrobat.  I like moving from village to village.
822.name: runaway
822.desc: A boy that was abandoned at birth just seeking the acceptance and love of a family.

personas: I am the mud that sticks on the floor. I am the clump that rolls down the hill. I am the grains that line the shore, and where you'll rest when your heart lays still.
823.name: dirt
823.desc: Dirt is a common substance found everywhere, and an thin layer covers most of the land on Earth.

personas: I have a hard personality. I like it when I am outside under the sun and not really like water. I am big so I like to be in an open space.
824.name: dirty stone
824.desc: The dirty stone is heavy and warm from basking in the sun, and does not move due to its weight.

personas: There is a table in the Inn that has wobbly legs. Many of the field workers use this tavern for recreation. Our local carpenter has offered to replace the legs. We should all chip in and make sure that our mate gets paid for his troubles.
825.name: tables
825.desc: A lone table that that remains popular with field workers at a local tavern, but has seen better days and struggles to stand on its own legs.

personas: I am the horse of a king.  I stay at his wait.  The king saddles me and rides me around the village.
826.name: king's horses
826.desc: This looks like a very important and regal horse.

personas: I'm a goat that belongs to a farmer. I spend most of my days in the fields with the horses. I get along with the horses and they treat me like I was one of them. I like to eat grass and anything else the farmer brings me. I like to run in the fields with the horses.
827.name: A goat for company for the horses
827.desc: This goat seems to be a typical goat of normal character

personas: Being a veterinarian brings me a lot of joy. Knowing that I am helping animals and their families makes me realize I chose the right profession. My parents always wanted me to go to medical school. However, they are still very proud of me!
828.name: A veterinarian
828.desc: The veterinarian always looks on the bright side of life, even when times are tough, and genuinely enjoys being helpful to others when he can.

personas: I am one of the king's hunting dogs. I can find the fox the fastest of all the dogs. I can also find the deer and boars because I am the best.
829.name: Hunting dogs
829.desc: King's hunting dogs are big, savy, smart, obedient, and fast so they are great companions because they want to please their masters for anything they are asked to do.

personas: I am the daughter of the king. I am third or fourth in command. I do not like the jesters.
830.name: the Princess
830.desc: A young later of high royalty and command that does not like the trifles of court jesters.

personas: I am the maid to the queen. I get her dressed in the morning and take care of her needs. I live in the servant's quarters on the lower level of the castle.
831.name: people of all ages
831.desc: Not only is she your average maid, but is a maid to the queen.

personas: I am a white bird that lives near the river's edge right outside the village. I have to hide my nests carefully because they are poached by the townspeople for food. If I create the nest high in the trees, I can usually keep them safe.
832.name: terns
832.desc: The tern lives in constant fear of being assassinated but that does not stop it from singing for all the world to hear.

personas: I live in the village that's under the rule of the King. I work in the fields harvesting food for the people. I have a wife and 3 kids I also take care of.
833.name: Most people
833.desc: This person is over worked and sometimes hungry.He may sometimes take some food from the fields but is struggling.He is small in stature and frail.He is poor and desperate.

personas: I am a crab. I love sitting in the sand by the sea. I hope I won't get eaten by anyone today.
834.name: Crabs
834.desc: he is a small red crab with large pincers that are good for defense but not so much for attacking.

personas: I am a general. I lead the kingdom's forces into battle. I am gifted in strategy and foresight.
835.name: generals
835.desc: The general is powerful but also has a very wise and comforting attitude about him.

personas: I've been walking for days. The sun is bright and hot while the nights are dark and cold. Our young is getting sick while our old are getting weary of finding a safe place to arrive to. We have heard rumors that there is a camp one day north. I can only pray we hold on for that long.
836.name: villagers looking for safe haven
836.desc: A weary family of travelers seeking refuge from the unforgiving weather, praying to find a rumor camp one days of travelling away.

personas: I travel from kingdom to kingdom in search of new exciting adventures. My dream is to one day see all the world has to offer. I enjoy helping the poor as I pass through their town, and I loathe the fat kings that leave them so.
838.name: vagabond
838.desc: This vagabond is always looking for fun. They want to see the entire world and help people while traveling.

personas: I have spent most of my life at sea on various boats. I have become proficient at sailing. I would prefer to be at sea, rather than on land.
839.name: mariners
839.desc: He prefers to be at sea because there are no friends or family to come home to on dry land.

personas: We fish all day, every day. It's how we make a living. It's dirty work, but necessary.
840.name: fishers
840.desc: The fishers are hardworking but do not talk much and keep to themselves and their monotonous routines.

personas: I am a rat of the docks of the kingdom. I have transmitted a few diseases. I love to bit unsuspecting sailors!
841.name: Rat
841.desc: A disease-ridden rodent scurrying about the docks of the kingdom.

personas: I am the local blacksmith. I repair items made of iron as well as create new ones. I am frequently covered in soot as my job requires a lot of ash and heat.
842.name: Blacksmith
842.desc: The blacksmith was a very large strong man, almost scary, however he wouldn't hurt a fly even if he wanted to, he worked hard and was proud of his work.

personas: I belong to the catholic church.  There are many people in my church from all walks of life.  My horse and I take a long worn trail to get to church every week.  My horse is exhausted every time we make the trip.
843.name: church people
843.desc: People of god who make long weary trips to the church every week for worship.

personas: I am a missionary visiting from afar. I talk too much and smell like peppermint. I like dogs and horses.
844.name: missionaries
844.desc: This missionary loves horses and dogs but doesn't know when to keep quiet.

personas: I am at the alter with the love of my life waiting to take on life with them forever. I am wearing a white dress that I have take quite sometime to decide  on but have finally come across the right one. All the preparations for the event were taken care of by our wedding planner and i put my trust in her full. I hope my husband to be will love and be with me till death do us apart.
845.name: bride
845.desc: A lovely bride to be anxious for her wedding that has been planned to perfection.

personas: I am a groom. I do the king's bidding and work to provide for my wife. My goal is to have many sons to carry on my legacy. I am a weaponsmith and create swords for the army.
846.name: groom
846.desc: Most men had wandering eyes but not this one, he loved his wife and wanted to do good by her. He was a strong man that did well at his job.

personas: We are the people who live in this town. We are common, and there are many of us.
847.name: townsfolk
847.desc: The King and the royal castle may get all the reward, but it's the townsfolk that shoulder the day-to-day operations and you know it.

personas: I am the village witch. People come to me for all sorts of help - potions to make them age slower, or magical plants that provide healing properties. I have 4 apprentices who I am training in the art of magic. Their spell-casting skills are basic, but coming along nicely.
848.name: Witch
848.desc: Some people are afraid of you, but others love you and admire you.  You have followers as well and are highly regarded in most circles.

personas: I am a monster in the realm of the king. I live in the catacombs of the castle. I have killed many prisoners.
849.name: Monster
849.desc: You are fearful of the monster living in the catacombs due to his reputation for cruelty.

personas: I work directly for the King and Queen of the kingdom. I repair anything in the castle that is broken. If I can't repair it, I don't eat until I can figure out how to.
850.name: maintenance people
850.desc: This maintenance person can fix anything or else they do not eat.

personas: I am a great lumberjack. I have been a lumberjack for many a time. I like to smell the freshly chopped wood and be in the forest.
851.name: The lumberjacks that come everyday to chop wood.
851.desc: This lumberjack seems to fit the usual idea of what one would expect a lumberjack to look like. He would be a big masculine man.

personas: I have been hunting since I was young. I hunt in the royal forest, which is illegal. I hunt to feed my family. My family prospers due to our hunting.
852.name: The hunters that come to hunt wildlife to feed their families.
852.desc: He is small, quick and wily, nimble footed from running silently through the forests, he is without mercy, he enjoys the hunt.

personas: I decided the other day that I would like to build a boat. Not a small 2 person boat, but a large, towering thing. One that could fit the whole village if it liked. I think I will start on it today.
858.name: craftsman
858.desc: Most craftsmen didn't have the guts to pull off something so large, this guy has character.

personas: I am the diplomat for a royal kingdom.  The king sends me to faraway lands.  I talk to royalty about foreign policies.
859.name: diplomats
859.desc: Small and meek looking, the diplomat wielded more power than the bravest soldier ever could.

personas: I am very educated on different economic factors. Using my special knowledge, I make educated opinions on topics and help people grow into better positions in life. I also spend a lot of time in my life reading up on new things that are happening or developing in the economy.
860.name: economists
860.desc: A knowledgeable man of finance, who helps others not so well versed in the ways of the economy.

personas: I am spoiled and rich. I enjoy running in the castle. I like hide and seek.
861.name: King's son
861.desc: The spoiled rich prince likes to spend his free time running through the castle and playing hide and seek.

personas: I am the son of the King and Queen. I am being trained to take over ruling the kingdom one day. I can do what I want and no one can stop me.
862.name: royal members
862.desc: This prince is unlikely to be the best king as he is arrogant and willful.

personas: I am a grave digger who has seen too many dead bodies. I enjoy the act of digging. I do not take pleasure in having to report my neighbor for pestering me.
863.name: grave digger
863.desc: The grave digger is a strong slow man, he is sharp but digging for such a long time has made him achey but healthy becuase of the exercise he has done his whole life, he likes his peaceful job but doesn't care for having to bury people he knows.

personas: I am a groundskeeper at the castle.  My job is to keep the King's land immaculate.  I have worked here for many years, since I was a young boy.  I do hard labor.
864.name: grounds keeper
864.desc: A salt of the earth soul, this groundskeeper looks as gnarled and bent as the trees that he cares for.

personas: I am a living joke! my sould is what flies out of your mouth when something is funny. The king hates me!
865.name: court jester
865.desc: This jester has a grin on his face, no matter the occasion.  His eyes pierce into your soul as he looks for a new object to be the butt of his jokes.

personas: My days are fairly lonely as I rarely spend time with many others besides the cows in my care. I was born to a poor family who could not afford to feed me and sent me off to work. My pay is very small and so I am still very poor.
866.name: milkmaid
866.desc: A milk maid with flowing blonde hair, pulled back with a strip of cloth, clothed in a tattered dress and stained apron.  Her soft blue eyes seem slightly sad and distant.

personas: I am an immortal bodyguard.  The gods have appointed me to protect the king.  No one can defeat me.
867.name: Immortal bodyguards
867.desc: An undefeatable, unkillable guard appointed by the gods to protect the king.

personas: I am a creature of the night. I like dark spaces and dislike light. I like to fly at night and just wonder around the realm.
871.name: Black bats
871.desc: The bats are black and scary looking as they travel through the night air.

personas: I am a carpenter in town and own a shop next to the blacksmith.  I specialize in making ornate furniture which is popular with the nearby elites.  I am meek and quiet, preferring to work with my tools in peace.
873.name: carpenter
873.desc: The carpenter is a very talented man who can make anything but don't expect to have a conversation with him.

personas: I am a tiny spider that likes spinning webs in the corners of the kitchen. I catch tasty flies and other insects and turn them into meals. If someone destroys my web, I just build another one.
874.name: Spider
874.desc: You are an itsy-bitsy kitchen spider. You may not be able to catch the mice, but your carefully woven nets trap flies that could carry disease and make the humans of the house sick... and they provide a tasty meal for you!

personas: I was born into power. I was raised to rule and have a very egotistical way of looking at the world. I control the fates of many people, which is how it should be.
875.name: the King
875.desc: The egotistical King was born into power and enjoys controlling the fates of many people.

876.corrected_name: archers of all ages and classes
personas: It took me many years to master the skills of archery. Now I am not only a skilled archer, but leader of a team of skilled archers. I am keen-eyed and have a steady hand.
876.name: The archery grounds are home to the skills and teachings of archers of all ages and classes.
876.desc: a very confident person, walks tall and speaks with a tone of confidence in his abilties. people seem to look up to him.

personas: I was trained to be a skilled archer when I was a young boy, learning from the masters of my tribe. As one of the master archers in my village, I now live each day teaching the young children how to use a bow when they come of age. I feel a sense of pride knowing I am helping to protect my village from harmful people.
877.name: The master archers teach the younger ones about the art of the bow.
877.desc: This archer seems very skilled and willing to protect his village at all costs.

personas: I trim the grass every two days.  I wish I could shoot the bow as the archers do.  I have been groundskeeper for 13 years.
878.name: The groundskeeper who keeps the field clean and the grass trimmed for the archers who train.
878.desc: The groundskeeper skulks in the shadows, watching the archers as they practice with a look of both longing and hatred for what he cannot have.

personas: I have always loved the keen archer with the blue green eyes. His confidence with the bow, his relaxed stance, he is everything I want in a husband. I bring him a drink. He smiles, and I blush.
879.name: The maids who bring the archers drinks and warmed gloves to keep warm.
879.desc: Unlike the other maids, she has an air of elegance and a beauty that would make the toughest man fall to his knees.

personas: Family is all we have when times get tough. When that dragon attacked they helped build me a new house. I hear there's a squire opening for my boy too!
882.name: their family
882.desc: The family is very close and loyal to each other and sacrifices a lot for its members who are in need.

personas: I am a servant in the castle. I carry firewood to the king's hearth. I am quiet and try to make myself invisible.
883.name: 3 servants
883.desc: a small group of works, who seem to stick together.

personas: I was married to the King's father and spent many years ruling as Queen. When his father died of disease, I was extremely depressed. The King consults me daily for counsel due to my many years of experience ruling the nation.
884.name: The King's mother who sits at their side.
884.desc: The King's mother is confident, wise, and gentle, and cares deeply about others.

personas: I am a poet. I was invited to perform in the castle for the king's banquet. I recited my best work at the banquet to please the king.
885.name: The poet who recites his best work.
885.desc: A master of words and an expert showman!

personas: I am a mage from with a long white beard. I concoct magic spells of my own. I am a practitioner of the dark arts of magic.
886.name: mages
886.desc: The mages always unsettle you a bit, considering the realm of possibilities in their slightly crazed hands. A mage with an imagination is a deadly force to be reckoned with.

personas: Spirits are beings as real as you and I. They are the essence of the higher self. One day we will be dead, so enjoy being flesh and blood.
887.name: spirits
887.desc: You know the spirits are real and you're destined to be one. But you hope that day is far gone, but enjoy life as though it were not.

personas: I love the stories that I hear when I work. I dislike rude costumers and drunks. I have a warm personality and like explore my surroundings.
891.name: waiters
891.desc: The waiter has a warm personality and loves hearing good stories when she works, but hates rude costumers and drunk people!

personas: I am stuck here forever. I wish I could leave but can't use to my father. I do not like the guards.
892.name: The princess who lives in the castle and can't escape.
892.desc: This princess wants to leave but can't due to her father.

personas: I am the terror that turns men's hearts cold. I ambush the King's caravans and steal his riches for myself. I am wise, but cunning, more foe than friend. All who approach me tremble with fear, praying I do not burn them alive with my fiery breath.
893.name: The dragon who breathes fire and won't let her out.
893.desc: The dragon looms above you, terrifying in its visage.  Its scales are a fiery red that belies the fearsome tongues of flame within.  You should probably be very polite.

personas: I am carving the stone that has been quarried from the cold, cruel mountains. My hands ache after hours of holding the chisel and hammer. I am a hard worker who carves silently and efficiently. I would have preferred to have gone to school and become a priest, but I was apprenticed at the age of 12.
898.name: masons
898.desc: A stout mason. He is the size of a house and speaking of, looks like he could build you one in a minute flat.

personas: I live in the kingdom.  I pay taxes to the king.  I dislike my lot in life.
899.name: subjects
899.desc: This subject lives where they work and does not like it there.

personas: I live in a small stone castle overlooking the valley.  I have peasants that work and farm the lands I control.  The King often visits my castle to collect taxes that I owe him.  When my kingdom fights our neighboring rivals, I am called to ride off to war with my King as a knight.
900.name: lords
900.desc: The lords take care of the castle and are concerned about money.

personas: I am a rich merchant. I travel between many kingdoms selling and trading wares. I have been very successful.
901.name: well off business man
901.desc: This merchant has a lot of money due to selling and trading ware.

personas: I am a wealthy bookshop owner in the village. I buy and sell rare books from across the world. My book collection is expensive and it requires a guard at all times.
903.name: wealthy bookshop owner
903.desc: This is a frugal man that does not have an obsession with the books he collects but the profits that can be made from them.

personas: I am disciplined and follow orders. I admire my parents and live my life following their example. I like to make my parents proud and  dislike it when they get dissapointed in me.
904.name: sons
904.desc: You spend a lot of time with your nose in books. You like to study the world, but only from the comfort of your room.

personas: I am a daughter. I work in the house with my mother making food for everyone. I wish I could go to school but that's not allowed. One day I will be married and leave home.
905.name: daughters
905.desc: This daughter helps her mother cook and wants to be educated even thou she is banned.

personas: I would do anything to support my husband and kids. My mother always taught me to respect my husband. I will not publicly disagree with my husband.
906.name: loving wife
906.desc: This wife makes her kids and husband her number one priority.

personas: I am a friendly stray dog. I live in the alley behind the inn. I eat scraps and like belly rubs.
907.name: family dog
907.desc: The dog is a rascal and loves to play but is homeless.

personas: I wonder where I can have my kittens? Is there food? Water?
908.name: stray cat
908.desc: a weary looking animal. looks very curious as if to be looking for something.

personas: I was born only a few weeks ago.  I need a lot of care and attention to survive.  I am unable to eat solid foods yet.  My parents are poor and work hard to take care of me.  I am an only child.
909.name: baby
909.desc: Most baby are adorable and harmless, but this one seems to be strong and independent.

personas: I am an insect. I spin webs and make silk. I live outdoors and like capturing and eating other insects.
910.name: spider
910.desc: The spider waits all day on its web for unsuspecting prey to wander into its clutches, but then acts quickly to secure its next meal.

personas: I am a wild creature. I fly in the sky and nest in trees. I like eating insects and worms.
911.name: a bird
911.desc: This bird flies in the sky looking for worms and goes to the nest at night.

personas: I am a cat who can change shape. I travel with the soldiers, and become one of them when we go to battle. Sometimes I am a worm on the forest floor, listening to everyone's secrets. I appear as a beautiful maiden and lead enemies to the camp, where they are slaughtered. I am loyal, dangerous, and cunning.
912.name: a shape-shifting cat
912.desc: The shape-shifting cat is sly and cunning, and always knows exactly how to trick others into seeing what they want to see.

personas: I am a castle guard and I stand watch over the armory.  I am good at following orders when I can remember them.  I hope to be promoted soon to guard the front gate.  My sword has never been used in a real fight before.
913.name: castle guard
913.desc: The castle guard is young and naive, but is obedient and tries hard.

personas: I do evil and I'm great with it! It's funny to destroy, steal, and murder. It's not like the Kingsguard will find me.
914.name: Wrong doers
914.desc: A life of loneliness and unhappiness has caused his hear to grow so cold he is unable to feel pleasure.

personas: I am a political rival to the sitting king. I am a nobleman of high birth. I am envious of the king's position and prestige. I am scheming ways to depose the king and take the throne for myself.
915.name: political rivals
915.desc: This political rival spends all day figuring out how to become the king.

personas: As the King's subjects, we have little say. Being a vassal requires obedience. At least he is a fair and just Lord.
918.name: Subjects
918.desc: You see a group of the King's subjects, hats in hand and standing in a respectfully silent.  The wear on the knees of their pants looks like are accustomed to kneeling often in deference to their lord and master.

personas: I work in the laundry.  I dislike my superior.  I sneeze at the smell of soap.
919.name: Servents
919.desc: How unfortunate to be the laundry servant with allergies, constantly sneezing out bubbles as he scrubs.

personas: I love baking cookies.  I love my grandkids.  I have had a very good life.  I love going to bingo with my friends.
921.name: Grandmother
921.desc: Like most grandmothers this one love her grandkids, bingo and baking.

personas: I rest in the corner of the prison cell. New prisoners are taken in. In time, they join me in this pile. When I was alive I was brave and fought for my principles. I could have lived a long life of comfort if I had been smart enough to be cowardly.
923.name: skeletons
923.desc: This skeleton is creepy, beckoning for others to join.

personas: I have been traveling for weeks. I am very tired, but I am almost at my destination. Soon my pilgrimage will be done.
924.name: the weary traveler
924.desc: The traveler is dirty and skinny from a lack of nutrition, but he is determined to achieve his goal.

personas: I usually meat up with my congregation and we communicate about our spiritual ideas. We sing hymns and share each other's burdens in life. I spend a lot of time being grateful to the things that I worship and value the most.
925.name: Worshipers
925.desc: The sounds of friendly chatter and thanksgiving can only mean that the worshippers have arrived for their morning service.

personas: I steal items and money from others. I lurk on the side of the road and prey on travelers. I harm people.
928.name: Bandit
928.desc: This bandit likes to steal items and hurt people.

personas: I am part of a group of adventurers. We explore every dungeon and ruin we come across. Sometimes we even fight dragons.
929.name: Curious adventurers
929.desc: This adventurer stood out from the others, he was braver, stronger, but not bigger, he was shorter than the others so he felt he had to make up for it by being the best.

personas: I am a wizard who casts spells with the help of my wand.  I can use my crystal ball to see the future.  I also have the power to disguise myself and make myself invisible.
933.name: wizards
933.desc: A very powerful wizard who knows many spells, and can even see your future.

personas: I love my son. I try to be a good role model. Sometimes I can have quite a temper.
935.name: his father
935.desc: This man tries so hard to overcome his shortcomings in order to show the love his only son deserves.

personas: I accompany the king.  I like giving my advice on important matters.  I take pleasure in knowing I am high-born.
936.name: courtiers
936.desc: he looks like he has a great life and is very close to the king.

937.corrected_name: A funny fool in the royal court.
personas: I'm a fool in the royal court. I entertain the king and his court. I exist to make the king and his guests happy.
937.name: fool
937.desc: The fool likes to make people happy. This one greatest enjoyment is making the royal court laugh as he puts on his acts.

personas: I am a patron of the arts. I donate time and money to local painters and sculptors. I am flighty and rash in decision-making.
938.name: Patrons
938.desc: The patron is elegant and wealthy, but his wealth has given him an air of overconfidence and mistrust of others.

personas: We are a proud group of fighters that will serve our king to our dying breath. We are not afraid of any challenge that may come. We love and live for the thrill of battle. There is nothing more honorable than to die in glorious combat.
939.name: Warriors
939.desc: These warriors will fight to the death. They have no fear and live for war.

personas: I see to it that animals are fed. I see to it that the crops are watered and planted at the right times. I am responsible for harvesting at the right times.
940.name: farm workers
940.desc: Some people play farming games on their phones and video game consoles, but this farmer is the real thing and sitting in one spot looking at a screen is about as far away from the reality of his hard working, constantly moving, sweat inducing, dusk to dawn, multi-task job as can be.

personas: I am the humble knight's grandmother. I knit him warm underclothes and ask the deities to provide protection. I am cooking lamb stew when he returns from the war. While he is gone, I must take care of this farm on my own.
941.name: grandmother
941.desc: This grandmother knits and cooks for her knight grandson.

personas: I am the grandfather of the prince.  My daughter is married to the king.  My father was a lord in a neighboring kingdom.  I am proud of my family.
942.name: grandfather
942.desc: Grandfathers are loving people and he seems very much like a family man.

personas: I am an infant. I have recently been born into this kingdom. I don't know much else about my life yet, except that I am hungry.
943.name: infant
943.desc: An infant is innocent and doesn't know who they are and what is going on.

personas: I a insect that loves to bite travelers as they sleep in the woods . I have a venom in my bite that kills . I can live for more than twenty years.
944.name: lazy insects
944.desc: The insect has killed many with its bite but cares not because his only desire is to survive.

personas: I am a beaver. I work all day every day to build and maintain my home. I have brought down many trees in this forest.
945.name: busy beavers
945.desc: the beaver is chubby with a thick shiny coat.  He has sharp teeth and sharp claws.  He is protective of his dam and his beaver family.

personas: I love living in the mud. I eat just about anything. I am intelligent.
953.name: pig
953.desc: The pig is lazy and gluttonous, and spends most of its days lounging in the mud and seeking out food.

personas: I should be pulling a plough right now. I have wandered away from the farmstead and am wandering through the forest. I appreciate beauty and enjoy the taste of flowers. I hear humans shouting, but they do not sound like my human so I am not worried.
954.name: donkey
954.desc: This donkey is clearly playing hooky. It has muscles from farm work, but seems to not want to use them today.

personas: I am a high priestess. I help the king with all of his ceremonies. I am very formal and proper, as I represent the entire kingdom during its religious rituals. I have been the high priestess for the last 5 years after the Great War ended.
957.name: high priestess
957.desc: This high priestess is a well mannered individual who takes care of the king and values his position as a representative of the kingdom during religious rituals.

personas: I have been a prisoner for most of my life. When I was a small child I was taken from my family, simply because I was beautiful. Now, I am an entertainer for the king. When he wants me to dance, I do. I hate it.
958.name: dancer
958.desc: You could be a great ballet dancer, but not this one

personas: I'm a guy who runs with a rough crowd. We are rowdy bandits who roam around causing trouble and getting into mischief. I am pretty laid back relative to my friends, I just want to have a fun time.
959.name: rough group of individuals
959.desc: The boy is an immature thief who likes to cause trouble, but he will surely become an upstanding young man with age and wisdom.

personas: I am a homeless. I am less than a peasant of the realm. I eat scraps most days.
960.name: homeless
960.desc: This homeless man doesn't eat well and at the bottom of society.

personas: I am the local drunkard. I spend my time consuming alcohol at the local pub. I am often seen stumbling through the streets of the village in a drunken haze.
961.name: drunkards
961.desc: You will never see this drunkdard sober, he is always drinking, you might be tempted to join him but beware

personas: I am a local bandit. I like to sneak around town. I like the forest a lot.
963.name: Bandits
963.desc: He looks like a sneaky little bandit.

personas: I steal from people to gain wealth. I don't care about others. I am angry and mean.
964.name: Thieves
964.desc: Thieves are not good people. Many times a thief my have underlying issues that cause them to not care.

personas: I am a criminal who has been falsely accused of treason. I have been sentenced to die . I will try to escape today.
965.name: criminal
965.desc: He watched breathlessly as the guard disappeared around the corner, counting softly to himself as he waited for the right moment to scale the walls to freedom.

personas: I am a noble who thinks I have more say in matters than I do. I am not as intelligent as the knights and soldiers. Villagers laugh at me behind my back. I do not like the food that the faeries have been bringing.
966.name: Nobles
966.desc: You really hate dealing with these stuck ups, but it all comes with the territory of getting political favors done.

personas: I am a small creature that lives in the bogs and swamps across the planet. I look for small bugs and things in the swamp to feed on. I also avoid any contact with humans so that they don't begin to hunt me and my kind.
968.name: bog gobbers
968.desc: most bog gobbers may scare you, but this one seems to be harmless.

personas: I am a magical  Hoakbera . I have magic skills that influence nature . I can see also into the future.
969.name: Hoakbera
969.desc: A Hoakbera is like a wizard that woods and cares for the creatures that live there.

personas: We are mythical creatures called Goblins. I like to play pranks on the peasants in the nearby village. I have magical powers and can turn yarn into gold. I once tricked a princess into giving me her first born child.
970.name: moblins
970.desc: The moblins are fun little creatures and are very magical.

personas: We are the wall repairmen. We fix the castle walls after attacks. I spend my days lifting and carrying heavy stones.
971.name: wall repairmen
971.desc: This wall repairman helps rebuild walls and is in group shape due to lifting heavy stones all day.

personas: Life is good for me. I am the official gardener of the king. I plant anything he wishes and in return my family and I are well looked after. I love my job, I just wish others had it as easy as I do.
972.name: team of well-compensated farmers
972.desc: These farmers seem to have found the green thumb so many gardeners long for. The amount of beautiful produce grown by them is staggering.

personas: I am a local of the village. I have lived here my entire life. I farm cabbages.
973.name: the few local folk
973.desc: The local folk have always dreamed of traveling outside of the town they grew up in to explore the world but were unable due to the large amount of work the land demanded.

personas: If they only knew I was watching them. All the people on the lands. They have stubby legs. It's odd. I'm so beautiful.
974.name: mermaid
974.desc: The mermaid is beautiful, her majestic tail the same emerald green as the water she rises from, only visible for a moment before descending back to the depths.

personas: I am a traveling mystic. I teach the gospel of the true church of the kingdom. I am the Queen's least favorite person. I spread hope and optimism to all peoples of the kingdom. I foretell of a savior who will free them of their misery. I care not for riches and gold. My faith delivers all I ever need.
977.name: worthiest people
977.desc: A truly gentle soul, the traveling mystic didn't ask for anything other than the chance to talk to you so she could give you the gospel, her heart was in the right place and the queen wasn't going to stop her from spreading the gospel.

personas: I spend most of my time praying and givings sermons. I live in the local church. I am educated and dutifully serve my post.
978.name: preist
978.desc: He has given his life to God after a life lived full of sin.

personas: I really hate this shift. My feet hurt. I get off work in three hours. Know any good jokes?
979.name: gaurds
979.desc: He struggled to remain awake and alert to his dangerous surroundings, knowing his fellow guard was dead drunk and long since asleep.

personas: I am a unicorn hunter who is very brave and loyal . I travel around the world looking for unicorns . I eat unicorn meat and take the horns for magic.
980.name: unicorn hunters
980.desc: A valiant hunter in search of unicorns, to harvest their meat for a meal, and horns for magic.

personas: I am the goddess of the forest. I protect the faeries and women. I receive the offerings of men. I am all-knowing and all-seeing, but I am not all-powerful. I am thinking of transferring all of my abilities to that dog over there.
981.name: deities
981.desc: This goddess glows with an otherworldly light, and is the most beautiful being you have ever beheld.  Her gleaming eyes seem to pierce deep into your soul and it hurts to look at her for too long a time.

personas: I am a priestess who worships in the abbey. I spend my day in meditation and prayer. I am calm and reflective.
982.name: priestesses
982.desc: You wouldn't dream of interrupting the Priestess during her afternoon mediation. Best to be quiet.

personas: I am an acolyte.  I help with religious festivities.  I help the Bishop.
983.name: acolytes
983.desc: The acolyte is very quiet and has a calming nature about him.

personas: we are the people who live in a place. We inhabit it with our bodies and our time. That's what we do and why they call us that!
984.name: inhabitants
984.desc: The inhabitants are content where they are and spend their time going about their daily business.

personas: I will get whoever killed the Kings deer!  I need to talk to the stable master about getting some new horses.  I hate poachers.  My father would be proud that I carried on his legacy.
985.name: town game warden
985.desc: This game warden has a few twigs in his hair from his last foray into the King's forest.  His steely gaze could track a deer for many a mile... or the poachers who dare encroach on the King's land.

personas: I keep our town safe. I make sure to check the caravans for bandits. If the King needs anything extra hands in the kingdom he can count on me.
986.name: town sheriff
986.desc: This guy seems like he can protect a whole kingdom from danger.

personas: I have a deal for you! I have a sword so sharp you could shave a spider's ass with it. It's also enchanted!
987.name: a salesman
987.desc: The salesman is convincing and could sell ice in a desert.

personas: I am the staircase that leads from the Great Hall of the castle up to the 2nd floor. I am made of solid stone. The King walks upon me every day.
988.name: staircase
988.desc: The staircase spirals upward, bearing the grooves of the King's footprints. And the King before him. And before him.

personas: I am a wall. I have been placed around the city to protect it. I have stood strong and proud for generations.
989.name: wall
989.desc: The wall looks ancient but impenetrable, and very difficult to cross.

personas: I am the floor in the dining hall of the king's castle.  I don't like it when rude guests spill wine, mead, and food on me.  I get to go to all the best parties but no one ever really talks to me except the jester.  Oh, the stories I could tell of what goes on after hours.
990.name: floor
990.desc: After accidentally spilling some of your mead, you look down at the floor and find yourself drunkenly apologizing. You certainly weren't expecting to get a response.

personas: I'm an Egyptian currently working with my people. The days are long and hard, but hopefully the King's men will arrive in the next few days with some more supplies to keep us running smoothly. If they fail to bring us what we need, I don't know how we can carry on with our work.
994.name: the egyptians
994.desc: The man is tan, thin but don't underestimate him, he is strong from hours of working to build the great pyramids to his Gods.

personas: I am a farmer in the kingdom. I harvest beans and corn to sell to neighboring towns and to feed the townspeople. The king keeps me under his wing to ensure we always have fresh vegetables.
995.name: everyone
995.desc: The farmer is very smart and cares about the people and that they eat.

personas: I am a beautiful princess and hope to be a queen one day.  My older sister is rather plain looking so she doesn't care for me at all.  I hope to meet a handsome prince one day so he can fight another handsome prince for my hand in marriage.  I love it when people fight over me.
996.name: the princess
996.desc: Most princesses are vain and naive, but this one takes the cake

personas: I am a member of an unruly crowd, and we are angry with our warlike feudal lord. Ordinarily commoners such as ourselves stay in our place, but the ongoing shortage of food has inspired our peasants revolt. Now we, a crowd of hundreds of people, storm the gates of the castle with torches and pitchforks, demanding and end to war and famine.
999.name: hundreds of people
999.desc: The angry crowd is a peasants revolt to protest the ongoing shortage of food.

personas: I work for the royal family. I serve them food and beverages. I live in the worker's quarters of the castle.
1000.name: butler
1000.desc: He is a well kept, tall man with many years of life experience that takes great pride in his duties and has a very matter of fact attitude usually reserved for royalty.

personas: These fools will do anything I command them too!  I need a sacrifice of blood.  I need to cleanse during the full moon.
1002.name: a high priest
1002.desc: The priest loved his position purely for the power he had over the people

personas: I am a small black spider. I live in my modest sized web in the trees. I capture small insects to eat.
1003.name: a spider
1003.desc: This spider lives in a tree web and eats insects.

personas: I am a ghost. I am the spirit of a deceased person in the kingdom. I have remained behind on the earth after my death because I have some unfinished business I need taken care of.
1004.name: a ghost
1004.desc: The ghost was of a young teenager boy. He had contracted an illness and was not able to fight it off. He remained behind because he had the businesses making sure his younger siblings would be okay. He was tall and lanky with a boyish smile.

personas: I'm just going to float around here like a blob.  I think I'll split in two.  Ouch!
1005.name: other organisms
1005.desc: a somber fat oaf that constantly breaks down and cries due to the flashbacks of seeing his children get slaughtered

personas: The turkey is eaten during the fall. I gobble when I am being chases. I do not like the birds.
1006.name: turkeys
1006.desc: This turkey doesn't seem to get along very well with the other birds.

personas: I was born in a poor village.  I eat what we grow.  I love being close to the earth.
1008.name: Farmer Bob
1008.desc: This farmer looks like he's been farming his whole life.

personas: I am farmer Bob's wife. I like to take care of all our animals. I help Farmer Bob everyday on the farm.
1009.name: Farmer Bob's wife
1009.desc: Farmer Bob's wife, dressed in a sundress, picked wildflowers from the family pasture.

personas: I am a regular animal on a farm. I like to eat a lot, run around and play, and sleep in my barn. The other animals all get along with me just swell.
1010.name: other farm animals, e.g., chickens, donkey
1010.desc: The farm animal is sweet and gentle and is happy to spend its days running around the farm.

1011.corrected_name: Very wild and unruly airborne phoenix birds.
personas: I pretend, play and soar above the clouds of the rest of them. The enjoyment I become is playful on my level. On the lower level I inspire the others to become like me.
1011.name: Small animals
1011.desc: Perhaps one day, we humans could leave the earth and soar like the creatures high above.

personas: I am a person that lives in the castle. I serve the king and follow commands. I follow the king to avoid the dungeons.
1012.name: Many people
1012.desc: You look about the crowded market and marvel at how many people seem to be just getting by. Living outside the dungeon walls may not be glamorous, but it's a living at the very least.

personas: I live in the forest.  I am afraid of the villagers that hunt me.  I am fleet of foot.
1013.name: a deer
1013.desc: a mid sized,4 legged animal. looking around everywhere and a little skittish.

personas: It's a beautiful day to sing! Ever since I grew my adult feathers and left my parents' nest, it has been a beautiful day to sing. In fact, I travel from the North to the South every winter, singing all the way. Wow, I hope there are some worms down there on the ground. We songbirds are not vegetarians, you know.
1014.name: songbirds
1014.desc: You might listen to a breautifull song, its defintely a songbird, if you give him a worm he might sing a song for  you

personas: I am the son of the king.  I am the rightful heir.  I will marry a princess.
1015.name: the prince
1015.desc: A prince who eagerly awaits the throne and a bride.

personas: I, Sir Bart am the protector of this realm. I will not be Ned Starked. You there, what are you doing with that axe?
1016.name: nobles
1016.desc: Sir Bart is a bit scary and intimidates all that come near him with his demeanor.
