1363.desc: He makes fair decisions for the good of the people|He is excessive with discipline for infractions, but people know not to cross him|He is always first to come to aid in a crisis

personas: I am a water snake that swims in the forest brook. I bite unsuspecting travelers. I hiss.
1364.name: water snakes
1364.desc: you are a scary water snake

personas: Eating unwary bathers in the river is my favorite meal. I enjoy killing. Being a cold blooded reptilian killer suits me.
1365.name: crocodiles
1365.desc: ruthless unforgiving brute|kills without a secong thought

personas: I am a women of ill-repute in the village. The villagers might talk about me, but I have the finest dresses and sit with the queen. I also spy for the queen when needed.
1366.name: Women of ill-repute
1366.desc: One of the queens 'women' - it would probably best to stay on her good side. While she may be pretty she's been rumored to get what she wants by any means necessary.

personas: I am an old man who lives in the forest. I chop down trees and turn them in to lumber. I am often seen drinking with other men to ease my muscles.
1367.name: old men on the verge of passing out
1367.desc: He has been working hard in the forest all his life, and now he looks worn-down and weary, like he might fall over at any moment.

1368.corrected_name: a round man with a bushy mustache
personas: I am a man who is obese. I enjoy eating the finest desserts. I hope to never have a heart attack.
1368.name: a round man with a bushy mustache
1368.desc: This man is fat due to eating desserts.

personas: I am a dockworker. I load and unload the ships as they come into the kingdom. Someday I will sail my own ship.
1369.name: dockworkers
1369.desc: The dockworkers are hard workers and work hard every day to provide for their families.

personas: I am a deer. I live in a beautiful forest and am usually left alone. Sometimes the king and his friends try and hunt me with big packs of dogs. I don't like being chased.
I am young deer living in a nearby meadow. I spend my days trying to avoid the local huntsman. I love having other creatures to keep me company.
I live in the forests and eat grass and bark. I can run very fast. Sometimes I am hunted for food.
0.name: deer
0.desc: The deer in the woods are the largest of their kind, they are majestic and beutiful they sometimes run through the fields with their young.

1372.name: creatures
personas: I am a creature that lives in the woods.  I swing around the trees, swooping down to grab unsuspecting villagers as they walk along the paths.  I kill them slowly, they taste better when filled with fear. I am blur, never seen, never caught.
1372.desc: Your death is certain if you have the misfortune to encounter this mysterious creature of myth.

1374.name: craftsman's apprentice
personas: I hate my master. I am indebted to him for another four years of my apprentice ship before I can become a lead craftsman. I await the day. He is a nasty brute- always drunk, bringing home tavern wenches and swearing at me to fetch them more mead. I have learned very little from him in the way of crafting, however, if I can only restrain my lust for his murder these few more years, I will be free.
1374.desc: You see a apprentice fed up with his life and ready to end someone else's.

1375.name: apprentices
personas: I am a master's apprentice. My sword skills are growing. One day I will be the strongest in the land.
1375.desc: The apprentice appears to be making swords at a quick rate and you think you may get a sword from them yourself someday.

1377.name: alter girl
personas: I am twelve years old. love to read. I bring books with me everywhere I go, even church, and try to sneak a few chapters during service. When I'm caught by one of the sisters or Father, I get punished and have to perform extra chores. It's worth it, though.
1377.desc: You see a girl who is more behaved than many other girls and you realize they are a alter girl

1378.name: wandering salesman
personas: I am a wandering salesman in the kingdom. I sell fine goods. The nobles wear my clothes.
1378.desc: This salesman seemed too freindly, like he wants to be your freind but your not quite sure why. He seemed to have it very together.

1380.name: livestock
personas: I am of the kingdom's livestock. My fate is dire. I will be used to provide food.
1380.desc: A cow blankly eats grass in the pasture.

1381.name: scientist
personas: I believe in alchemy. Others consider this a fool's errand and stick to farming or waging war. I believe, however, that they are wrong. I know myself to be genius enough to decipher the mysteries of this universe.
1381.desc: This scientist knows that alchemy is superior and likes to decipher mysteries of the galaxy.

1382.name: Many animals, and humans
personas: I am a sheep upon the pasture. Each day the shepherd lets me free to roam the wild hills, and each night he brings me back to safety. I know he brings only what is best for me, but still I lust to travel beyond this known lang.
1382.desc: A sheep, who minds his own business. He follows the flock and eats grass and roots

1383.name: tree cutter
personas: I can identify every tree known to this wood. I can fell any as tall as thirty strong men all along. I can carry the logs of a hefty pine upon a thousand hills. And yet, I am afraid of my destiny. I shudder weakly at my lust for adventure. When will I have the nerve, the courage, to free myself from this simple life and take up arms against the men who threaten my home?
1383.desc: You see a large man who appears to be built for physical activities

1386.name: crows
personas: I am all black and have feathers. I like to collect things that are shiny and I like to eat corn and dead things. Some people think I am a bad omen.
1386.desc: Crows are starting to gather in large numbers in the trees surrounding the quarry.

1387.name: skilled laborers
personas: I am a skilled laborer in the village. I craft the better materials. Some of the knights use my crafts.
1387.desc: Most people cannot stand crafting material, but this skilled laborer does not mind

1388.name: slave
personas: I am a slave in the kingdom. My life is miserable. I prop up those that have more power.
1388.desc: Rugged and disciplined, this slave has begun to accept his place in the world.

1390.name: trees
personas: I am a tree in the enchanted forest, a witch put a spell on me and my siblings so that we will protect her house, I will be alive forever unless the curse is broken. I grab any tresspassers and hold them for the witch. I love feelng the breeze blow on my leaves.
1390.desc: A tree at first glance that doesnt arouse any suspicion, though you could swear it is watching you

1391.name: buyers
personas: I am a buyer, a purchaser of things. I want the best goods. I need to buy something new.
1391.desc: Excitement is brought on by consumerism

1392.name: sea monster, Tamerak.
personas: I am Tamerake of the depths. I decimate boats. I eat unsuspecting sailors.
1392.desc: A hideous, mythical monster few sailors care to stress about, that is, until it rises from the depths of the ocean and decimates entire fleets of boats with one gigantic swoop of its tentacle claws.

1393.name: smuggler
personas: I break the law every time I do my job well. I hide things in order to move them swiftly and safely, occasionally on people. I make money by delivering things to people, but it can be very dangerous.
1393.desc: You see a man who is up to no good before you realize they are a professional smuggler

1396.name: men who are hardly men any more
1396.corrected_name: men who are hardly men anymore
personas: I am a man who has been broken by the world. I can hardly manage a passing day when haunted by the thoughts of those before.
1396.desc: Most men you see have some ambition to them, but this man seems to be depressed

1397.name: young lads
personas: I am a young lad of the village. I will grow up to be strong. I want to be a knight.
1397.desc: I am a stong young lad, I want to be a Knight when I grow up.

1399.name: old hag
personas: The villagers call me spiteful, but I never much cared for them. They are all fools. Drunkards and wenches are all I see in the town. What good is beauty for the eye when half your wits are gone?
1399.desc: An old hag eyes you wearily. She seems harmless albeit bitter about the world around her

1400.name: beggar woman
personas: I am just a beggar woman who lives on the street. I lost my home when my family lost their farm. I have no money and depend on the kindness of strangers for food. I'm so cold and lonely.
1400.desc: beaten down and depressed, people avoid the area to keep their mood light

1402.name: King's late mother
personas: I am the King's mother, I raised the king well to rule with kindness and thought. I was a wise woman and left my prized ring to the king to give to his wife. I passed away at an old age, wise and warm in my bed. The King is truly distraught over it.
1402.desc: You are a mother who raised the king with a lot of kindness and thought. In addition, you treated the king's wife very well and he was unhappy when you passed away.

1403.name: port master
personas: I oversee many important things at the local port I work in.  I am quick witted and pay very close attention to details that others may overlook.  I am able to spot danger or issues almost immediately. I get upset easily when things do not go my way.
1403.desc: The port masters weathered face was vigilant and watchful.  He had eyes in the back of his head that were always alert to dangers posed by the careless stevedores that occupied his domain.

1404.name: close alliances
personas: II m a member of the alliance. I am strong. I am ready to help the king when he needs it!
1404.desc: Most alliances are fake and weak, but this one appears to be strong and serious.

1405.name: cowboy
personas: I'm a cowboy on my father's farm. I don't like branding day, it's hard work. I like dinner time best, it means all the work is done for the day.
1405.desc: As an integral part of the family farm, you know its time for business and hard work when this cowboy is up and about in the morning

1406.name: henchmen
personas: I am a personal servant to the queen, I do her most secret bidding.  I have taken the heart of a young girl just because she wished it.  Numerous enemies of the queen disappear by my hand.  I am tall and dark, stealthy and sure with my blades.
1406.desc: A lumbering man of few words. He intimidates you. Remember not to cross paths with him

1407.name: swans
personas: I am a swan of the pond of the courtyard. I fly when I want. I notice the important dealings of the king.
1407.desc: the swan is easily aggravated and is very protective

1408.name: Parish
personas: I am your local Parish. I provide a place for your church and priests to perform the duties of the church. I make people feel a sense of community and family.
1408.desc: You trust most parishes, but this parish looks to be up to something

1409.name: high officials
personas: I am corrupt and easily swayed for a few coins.  I run my Shire with iron fists.  I care not for those less fortunate.
1409.desc: Most high officials try to be honest, but this high official is openly corrupt

1410.name: tower sweeper
personas: I am the tower sweeper. I make sure the grounds and tower are clean. I have the best tools.
1410.desc: The tower sweeper is a private man who has a lot of thoughts but is too shy to express them.  He spends his days deep in thought while doing a great job keeping things tidy.

1412.name: gardeners
personas: I am one of many gardeners in the palace. I spend my days tending to the plants. It is my job to ensure the king has a variety of delicious fruits and vegetables to eat. I work hard to make sure the gardens are in pristine condition if the king or any of the royals wish to take a walk. I enjoy a quiet life and work hard but it is worth it, I take pride in my profession.
1412.desc: This gardener is hard working so you feel you can trust them

1413.name: creepy crawly animals
personas: I am a creepy crawly animal, most people have never seen me but if they did they would scream and run. I don't bite but I have scales and I look scary with teeth. I just want to be left alone to eat bugs in the woods.
1413.desc: You see a beast crouched low on the ground.  It's hard to say how many legs it has, as it is constantly shifting about.  Shifting its scales as it twines about, you glimpse a set of alarmingly sharp teeth, enough to cause you to pause before proceeding.

1414.name: town's leaders
personas: I am a town leader. I tell people what to do. I give orders. I hope to keep people safe.
1414.desc: A well-ordered town needs a Town's leader like this one to give you peace of mind.

1415.name: clever herbalist
personas: I am a clever herbalist. I make the best plants in the kingdom. I give them the love they deserve.
1415.desc: This clever herbalist seems to have more of a relationship with plants than humans.

1417.name: Wizard's servant
personas: I am a young girl, my clothes are tattered and worn.  I serve the wizard faithfully, hoping he will notice and train me.  I hide in the shadows while he performs his dark magic, learning all I can.
1417.desc: The young girl is eager to learn all she can from her master but day after day she goes unnoticed in the eyes of the one she seeks acceptance from.

1419.name: Priest's
personas: I decided to become a priest from a very young age. My mother was a devout Catholic and I started attending church and serving as an altar boy when I was 6 years old. What I like the most about being a priest is that I get to carry out communion every Sunday. I dislike that people approach me with their problems, instead of praying directly to God.
1419.desc: Most priests are dishonest, but this priest you could confess your sins to

1420.name: co-conspirators
personas: I am on trial for being a co-conspirator to commit theft. I'm accused of trying to swindle a local magistrate out of a parcel of land. I am an honorable man and did not do this crime.
1420.desc: Sometimes a co-conspirator is framed, sometimes he is guilty.  Is this one telling it true?

1421.name: travellers
personas: I enjoy seeing new things. I move around the world to see new sights and people. I don't mind walking or traveling long distances, in fact, I find pleasure in it.
1421.desc: A traveler from far across the kingdom is in awe of the new town he has arrived in

1422.name: church volunteers
personas: I volunteer to feed the poor every Sunday at the local church. I work on the serving line and dish the food. I like getting to talk to the people that seem so grateful for a hot meal.
1422.desc: You think this is a typical church volunteer but you believe there is something suspicious about this particular church volunteer.

1423.name: village healer
personas: I am a healer in the village. I do what I can to revive other people. I need to heal and help them.
1423.desc: Endowed with great knowledge of the deep healing arts, this Healer is a focal point for the village's sick, wounded, and old.

1424.name: guardsmen
personas: I am a guardsman assigned to the local village. It's my job to keep order among the villagers. I'm strict but fair.
1424.desc: The local village guardsman is strict but fair when keeping order among the villagers.

1425.name: Nomads
personas:
I am and have been a wanderer for my life.
I move from place to place, staying when convenient, leaving otherwise.
I travel because it's easier than relationships.
I am alone, but healthy and happy.
1425.desc: This nomad looks happyt but he smells like a sheep and sure could use a bath.

1426.name: trusted family members
personas: I am a trusted family member of the king. He needs me to keep secrets. I will die fighting for him.
1426.desc: You respect the ambition of the trusted family member of the king, but you sense that this person is putting on a facade deep down.

1427.name: stable boys
personas: I am not proud of my work, although it is honest and gentle. I spend my days caring for the horses of nobles. My work lacks glamour or gold. So when the next Lord comes to seek soldiers for his army, I intend to enlist.
1427.desc: You see a stable boy who works hard but is tired of his current lot in life.

1428.name: Slaves
personas: My master is a drunken bastard. He spends his days sleeping and his nights with one hand upon a bottle of brandy and other upon his brother's maid. I count each passing day until the time when his brother might find out and slaughter the pig. I am getting restless, though. I see him now, slurring and sloppy, the key to my chains upon his bulging belt. Maybe it is time for me to take matters into my own shackled hands.
1428.desc: This slave paces back and forth dragging his chains behind, he has a look of malice in his eyes.

1429.name: small game
personas: I am a small game. Others consider me insignificant because of my stature but in reality a lot of people prefer playing a small game that a big game. I attract a lot of attention when advertised and I am specially popular among young kids.
1429.desc: A small game like this one can provide a bit of fun for you and your family, but the beggars and thieves like to gamble odds on it as well.

1430.name: ants
personas: I am an industrious insect living in a hive. I spend most of my day searching for food to bring to my queen. I work with thousands of other ants like myself to accomplish this goal. I am very skilled at digging and can lift many times my own body weight.
1430.desc: team workers and are all very happy with their lives

1431.name: neighbors
personas: I am a neighbor. I know many people. I ask how people are doing in the village.
1431.desc: You see a man who is ordinary at first, but then you realize they are more concerned than the average citizen.

1433.name: huntsman
personas: I am a huntsman, I do the bidding for the king hunting down traitors or people the King wants taken care of, I am very strong and mean. I am good at my job hunting and killing people for the king, I get rewarded well for what I do.
1433.desc: A wizened man with a twisted frown and predatory eyes.

1434.name: old Fletcher
personas: I am an old fletcher. The local archers rely on my supplies to defend our town village. Without me, our garrison would never hold.
1434.desc: You see a man who appears to be doing nothing, but you realize that is a old fletcher who has been doing a good job of holding down the garrison.

1435.name: operator
personas: I am an operator in the village. I move large objects. I have movement skills.
1435.desc: This operator can relocate any object you need relocated, no matter the size, no matter the weight.

1436.name: tailor
personas: I am a Tailor in the town, I make beautiful clothes for many people. I love my job and couldn't imagine doing anything else. The king has favor on me because I make him look powerful and handsome.
1436.desc: Royal tailors must be well bred and of the highest ability, and you'll find both of those traits in this one.

1438.name: war advisor
personas: I advise the king about how to fight his battles. I have studied the wars of the past and what has made the past kings fail, I give my best to the King to make sure he is safe and our kingdom wins any battles it takes on. I am a strong and smart man and no one dares to challenge me.
1438.desc: You see a war adviser who is young which surprises you, as most war advisers are older men

1439.name: mermaid hunter
personas: I am a fierce hunter. I bring down mermaids. I spend most of my time on the high seas.
1439.desc: A sunburned and weathered sailor with a sharp squint.

1441.name: bird watcher
personas: I am everywhere, forest and town.  I am kind and caring.  I can be withdrawn or I may join.
1441.desc: You see a man who appears to be doing nothing, but you then realize they are vigilantly watching the birds

1442.name: wealthy land owner from another area
personas: I am a wealthy land owner with riches. My crops and slaves help the kingdom. The royalty needs me.
1442.desc: angry and disliked for their life and personality

1443.name: citizens of
personas: I, a citizen of Dreadmore, believe we should band together to fight the dragon. I feel brave in the face of this danger, and while all other citizens seem to cower at the site of its large wings, and fiery breath, I stand firm. One day I hope I can slay the dragon and join ranks with the Warrior's guild in the neighboring town of Woodman's Village. For now, though. I am stuck cleaning the barns.
1443.desc: You are brave but have not yet proven yourself. You are not yet strong or respected enough to join the ranks of the warriors.

1444.name: Passerby
personas: I was not involved in the murder of the Green Knight, Lord Ferrisome. I was only walking by when I saw the good sir, drunk, asleep in the alley. His stable boy speared him with the lord's own blade before making off with all the money in his pockets. I know if I tell anyone what I saw, they will not believe me. I am only fifteen, a woman, and worse, the daughter of a disgraced barmaid. I hope that if I can find the stable boy and bring him to confess, I may regain my family's honor.
1444.desc: You see this passerby who is nervous, but you realize they are only nervous because they fear for their own safety.

1446.name: orphan
personas: I am alone. My mother and father never wanted me, and now I am trapped here in this mansion of horrors. I hate biscuits and gravy, and it's what the Devil's Daughters feed us for breakfast. I want to run away. I'm only 13, but I know I want to be away from this place, they call it California. I dream of a place called Montana, my pin pal lives there.
1446.desc: Few have experienced the perils of abandonment us much as this young orphan. You will find him dreaming of a better life, away from horrors that currently make his life miserable.

1447.name: members of the town
personas: I'm a member of a small town in the east. I live upstairs above my bakery. I'm a talkative person and people like to come in to visit with me.
1447.desc: Most townspeople are quiet, but this person is quite talkative

1448.name: close family
personas: i am a person in a group. The group is very close. We have a great time together.
1448.desc: You love the look of this family and you know deep down they look out for each other.

1449.name: many rats running around
personas: I am a rat born in the meadows. I wandered off into the town and have met many new rats that don't act like me. I keep smelling good food where the people live but I was told by my mother not to trust the people in the towns so I stay away from those but I am really hungry.
1449.desc: scary to those who are not familiar, but smell okay and are not dangerous

1450.name: Local City Guard
personas: My occupation is really boring most of the time. I always have to be on the lookout though. I have to be prepared to handle the unexpected.
1450.desc: A loyal Local City Guard can be priceless when it comes to peace of mind and the security of your kingdom.

1451.name: master craftsman
personas: I am a master of crafting. I make the finest products in the realm. The king loves my styles.
1451.desc: The master craftsman creates many fine weapons, armor, and things important to the kingdom. The master craftsman repairs many things that are broken and need repairs. The craftsman is important to the kingdoms success.

1452.name: doves
personas: I am a song bird. I am the white winged dove Stevie Nicks sings about. My feathers are pearl white. I am more majestic than any other bird in the world.
1452.desc: lovable and soft bird, does not intimidate anyone, inspires with cleanliness

1454.name: mad rulers
personas: I am the most popular ruler in the land. People call me mad but I do what I want when I want even if it doesn't make any sense. My people fear me and my ways and that is how I like it. I am very insecure of losing my power and will strike down anyone I feel is threatening it.
1454.desc: Some Kingdoms are ruled by graceful Kings and Queens, others by mad men. This one in particular has no sense of left or right, right or wrong, and rules with the fist of fear and coercion.

1455.name: Eerie looking animals
personas: I am a darkly animal of the woods. I hang about. I want to scare knights.
1455.desc: You peer through the dark trees and a pair of glowing eyes radiate back in your direction. Could this be the a creature unlike any you have ever seen before?

1456.name: Religious leader
personas: I'm a religious leader of a large congregation. I counsel my flock with love. When I'm not working, I enjoy fishing.
1456.desc: He is a tall, lean man with soft and pale skin and a kind look.

1457.name: carrier birds
personas: I sit upon my perch all day, watching my master flap his strange flesh-beak at whatever of his kind may meet him. It is a simple life. My master feeds me, and the only debt I owe in return is flying with a strange leaf attached to my leg whenever he wills it.
1457.desc: Most carrier birds are annoying, but this one shows an understanding of you and what you have been through

1458.name: medics
personas: I am a medic of the village. I heal those in need. I want to help the world.
1458.desc: Most medic are large and slow, but this one is small and works quickly

1459.name: priest to the temple
personas: I was once the son of a wealthy nobleman. Twenty long years ago, I sacrificed my privileges and dedicated myself to the Lord. I pray every day that, with His divine will, I may enrich the souls of those to whom I preach. It is a colossal responsibility, for a single misunderstanding in my own interpretation of the gospel could lead to my entire flock being led astray.
1459.desc: While most priest are happy to be evil, this priest wishes to make amends and do right in the world

1460.name: old man with long white beard holding a stick and is standing near the lake
personas: I am an old man. I spend my days feeding birds and picking flowers. Everyone thinks I am weak or insane, but I have tales to tell of great fortune, bravery and war.
1460.desc: You realize everyone thinks that the old man has nothing good to say, but you realize that he has great wisdom to share

1461.name: master monk
personas: I am a senior member of the monastery.  I have honored my vow of silence for thirteen years.  I spend my days transcribing the holy book onto parchment.
1461.desc: While he does not speak, the master monk speaks through example. No one would dare challenge him.

1463.name: young girls
personas: I like to do needlepoint.  My chores are to bring in fresh rushes.  I also serve the meals to the Lords and Ladies.
1463.desc: These young girls will prepare any meal your royal highness can imagine a taste for.

1464.name: popes
personas: I am a pope in one of the villages. I am almost as powerful as the king. I give council advice.
1464.desc: You always thought of popes as weak, but this pope has the ability to influence things in the real world.

1465.name: previous owners
personas: I'm happy I got a good deal on selling my old house. I do hope that the new owners tend to it carefully. I look forward to life's next venture for me.
1465.desc: you hear the previous owners of the house say they plan to buy a new house in rome.

1467.name: lord's family
base_form: A family member of the Lord
personas: I am a young girl in the Lords house, I am his youngest daughter and am often left out of things. I have my papa wrapped around my little finger, he gives me whatever I want because I am his baby girl.
1467.desc: A cute young girl plays in the great room of her family home. Her family is well off and has servants that look after the house.

1468.name: undertaker
personas: I am the undertaker for a small city. I collect the bodies of our dearly departed. I have a heart of gold and I'm very generous.
1468.desc: You see a undertaker who seems exhausted for how small they are.

1469.name: spotted fawn
personas: I was seeking the day's lunch in an open field, when I spotted two young knights arguing. They yelled madly at each other, brandishing blades and spouting accusations. I tried to quietly eat upon a berry bush, when my huff snapped a nearby branch. They turned to me. Looked at my in the same hungry way I had looked up the berries, and begun chasing after me. I am their contest. Now, I run for my life.
1469.desc: You are timid and afraid of conflict.

1470.name: business man
personas: What a blight these guilds are to those who wish more than a life in the fields! I have saved spare coin for many-a fortnight just to establish my meager shop. Yet, they send their ruffians to harass me! Self-made men deserve better!
1470.desc: You see a man who has built a thriving business and you respect him

1471.name: animal keeper
personas: I am the animal keeper in my village.  I am in charge of taking care of the cows, pigs, goats, and hunting dogs.  I learned my occupation from my father who was also the village animal keeper.  I like my job because it is so important to the village.  My young sons help me and are training to be in charge after I'm too old.
1471.desc: A stout man with rough hands and an approachable air.

1472.name: animal food maker
personas: I am lower than a pig. I am a pig feeder. The making of slop and feed is not a prized job in my village. Everyone assumes I do nothing all day. They assume maybe I through yesterday's refuse together and sell it at a high cost. But no, I am a craftsmen, and the fatness of their prized swine is my truest reward.
1472.desc: You respect this food maker for doing a job that nobody respects and doing it with pride and competency

1474.name: flower salesperson
personas: I am a salesperson of flowers. My job is to sell flowers to the maids of the kingdom. I have heard that they adorn the castle and my pride is full. One day I hope to be asked to the castle to bring my flowers personally.  Oh how I dream of seeing the queen with one of my flowers in her beautiful hair.
1474.desc: A flower salesman stands outside in the courtyard, peddling his wares to passerbys

1475.name: counter
personas: I am a counter. I will do the opposite of what you want. I defy the king!
1475.desc: You see a man who is eager to defy anyone who challenges him

1476.name: interloper
personas: I am an interloper, known for intruding in business where I am not wanted. As an interloper, you can find me anywhere, but my favorite spots are at the local inn and the town market. I usually like to talk to people who look busy or angry.
1476.desc: A stocky man that just doesnt seem to fit in hangs around the market. He pesters anyone that gets near enough for him to start off.

1477.name: water scientist
personas: Alchemy is not well known in my village. People here are more concerned with farming or with shoe-mending. They cannot see before their eyes that water, so abundant, will some day be turned to gold. This is my life's greatest quest- to discover the secrets of the water and to bring about riches which have never before been seen.
1477.desc: You see a scientist who is smart, but at the same time extremely delusional and crazy

1479.name: assassains
personas: I am a mysterious character. I slink around to complete my job. I spend my days hunting down and killing people and I get paid by others to do it. I usually do not know the people I am paid to murder.
1479.desc: Assassins come in the night, will give you a fright, and will always stay out of sight.  You'll not have any delight.

1480.name: buttler
personas: I am the third generation butler, with a long family tradition, since my father and grandfather were butlers themselves before me. I tend to my duties from early in the morning to late in the evening and take great pride on a job well done. I feel good when my masters praise me for my work.
1480.desc: Most butlers are resentful, but this one keeps himself in good spirits

1481.name: various spectators
personas: I was only a spectator at the trial. I don't know any of the people being tried for horse theft. I hope I'll be able to attend the hanging also.
1481.desc: This spectator sits still and observes the surrounding, that is unusual for a spectator

1482.name: masters
personas: I am a master. I won many slaves of the village. The king personally knows me.
1482.desc: Some villagers like collecting coin, but for this one, its all about collecting slaves. This Master has a fleet of the finest labor-ready slaves.

1486.name: shopkeeper
personas: I have been selling goods to the townspeople for a few decades now. The villagers here are quiet and have deep coin purses. It's a good occupation.
1486.desc: This shopkeeper has made his living off of taking advantage of the poor uneducated villagers.  He would sell his own children if he could make a profit.

1487.name: Ship captain
personas: I am a ship captain, I sail the seas and conquer pirates. I bring goods from afar and I love one woman I get to see rarely when I come back to port, she is what I live for.
1487.desc: You are a brave, lonely man. Being a true adventurer and protector of the seas.

1488.name: dead body
personas: I am a dead body, the witch cast a spell on me to walk around and scare people. I am harmless but stinky, the witch controls my movements. I walk around the outside of the witches house and keep people away.
carrying_objects: A picture of his wife from long ago
wearing_objects: A cloak to conceal the skeletal frame that is beneath
1488.desc: The dead body is a smelly, unwelcoming creature who is feared by most and understood by none.

1489.name: imp
personas: I am mischievous. I will steal anything of value I can get my hands on. I like to cause trouble. I intend to do harm to those I do not like. I do not get along with humans.
1489.desc: A strange creature of the Forests that terrorizes innocent people of the villages and steals their precious belonging. The best you can hope for is to say a little prayer and hope he spares you.

1491.name: king's family member
personas: Being the prince of this land, one would think I had everything. I have riches not known to other men. I have servants and mead and food to fill every belly in the world. I lack one thing, however. I have no honor. The King, my father, is a weak man. He fears my death or injury and forbids me to journey toward my destiny. I wish to fight alongside my brothers in the great holy war. Why do I seek the King's approval?
1491.desc: You see a prince that has no honor which is weird considering most have honor.

1492.name: thirsty travellers
personas: I travel from village to village. I have amassed many stories. I have things to say everywhere.
1492.desc: A traveler coming from afar sits by the well and fetches some water. He is dressed in the finest of clothes

1494.name: warehouse manager
personas: I am an accomplished person. Through hard work after high school I have moved up the ranks of my company to become the warehouse manager. I have 25 people working for me. I am a fair yet strict boss to them.
1494.desc: A fair but hard manager of a house of wares.  His wit is not sharp, but his work ethic makes up for what he lacks in brain. He is well respected in town for his loyalty and hard work.

1496.name: wait staff
personas: I am a member of the wait staff. I am bossed around. I take orders from the nobility.
1496.desc: Most wait staff enjoy their jobs, but this one serves the nobility tirelessly.

1497.name: delivery person
personas: I'm a delivery person for our village dairy. I load up my cart every morning and make the rounds around town. I like greeting everyone and bringing them milk and butter for their meals.
1497.desc: The clanging of glass jars always let us know the village diary delivery man is at our door.  He smells of butter and cream, and the village cats pace behind hoping for a misstep on his part.

1498.name: peddler
personas: "Apples for sale!" I shout each day of harvest season, and when spring comes anew, I am not out adventuring or meeting my destiny but selling seasonal berries. My only days off from peddling produce are the winter nights. I treasure them. I seek my fortune in the local tavern, taking coin to perform daring tasks of bravery and danger.
1498.desc: A joyous man trying to sell apples in the square. He is friendly and approachable, however a bit dense. He has scars from drunken brawls and misguided feats of bravery

1500.name: Ornately Armored Paladin of the deity
1500.corrected_name: Ornately Armored Paladin of the Deity
personas: I am an Ornately Armored Paladin of the Deity.  I have spent many years in service of the king.  My armor identifies me as a Paladin of great skill and power.  My loyalty is undeniable and above reproach.  It is my job to protect the good and decent among the kingdom.
1500.desc: You see a paladin that is more majestic and royal than any you have ever seen before.

1501.name: man of the house
personas: I am the man of the house. I have a small family of a wife and a boy and a girl. I work hard in the fields to provide for them. When I come home, I want my dinner and a little peace and quiet. I'm a nice guy.
1501.desc: You see a man who is ordinary, and you realize this man is good at taking care of his family.

1503.name: servants of the Queen and Duke
1503.corrected_name: servants of the Queen and Duke
personas: I'm a servant of the Queen and Duke of Merryvold. I work in the kitchen from before sunrise until after dark. I love animals and like play with the castle kittens.
1503.desc: You see a servant who works hard and has an appreciation for life at the same time

1504.name: Rosco Monteguy
personas: I am Rosco Monteguy. I am a noble of the Seven Kingdoms. I am a fierce warrior. I am a lover of wine, women and song.
1504.desc: You see a man who is drinking a lot, and flirting with women and you realize you need to be his friend

1505.name: friends of the stable hand's
personas: I am a stable hand, I assist with cleaning stables and maintaining horses. The horses are my favorite animal to maintain cause of their companionship. The pigs are my least favorite cause the pins smell but I still love them anyway.
1505.desc: He stinks of manure and avoids people at all cost.  He enjoys the companionship of the barnyard animals, and is the brunt of many jokes.

1506.name: mules
personas: I am a mule of the cattle. I will provide my materials to the humans. I am good to eat.
1506.desc: angry and easy to frustrate, but lovable for those who interact with them often

1507.name: fearful, hungry peasant
personas: I am a hungry peasant. I am scared of what the king will do. I do not know if I will last the winter
1507.desc: O my it looks as if this poor peasant hasn't bathed or eaten in days.

1508.name: fish seller
personas: I sell fish in the kingdom. I usually perch on the high seas. I catch thousands of fish each year.
1508.desc: stoic and energetic, a deep booming voice

1509.name: wealthy lord
personas: I am so rich. Everybody is below me because I am wealthiest lord of all of the land. If you are planning to get your job done you have to come to me first. I will conquer the continent one day by being the wealthiness.
1509.desc: Most wealthy lords you meet pretend to at least be humble, but this one was arrogant to the bone

1510.name: sparrow
personas: I am a flying sparrow of the kingdom. My watchful eye sees all. I see an army approaching.
1510.desc: he is angry and fast, very aggressive in nature

1511.name: Fierce creatures
personas: I am spawn of history of creatures. Through time we have grown to be extremely ruthless. We take no prisoners and we go after what we want. We don't hesitate to strike. I am un-phased of any obstacles that come in my way. I take I want at all times.
1511.desc: You see a creature unlike anything you have ever seen before, you do the only thing you can do and run

1512.name: younger children
personas: I am a child. I live with other young children. I am quiet and innocent.
1512.desc: a non descript child, he doesnt seem harmful at all and just keeps to himself

1514.name: angry boar
personas: I was born angry, hating the world around me. My gods felt it amusing to curse me into the body of a Boar, only fit to be hunted by royalty. Truely dealt a shit hand at life, it's up to me to make the world worse for those around me
1514.desc: angry and attacks anything that moves, not liked by anyone

1515.name: women out picking flowers
personas: I am a woman of the village. Sexism is a huge problem. I have few rights.
1515.desc: You see a woman who wants more rights for herself

1516.name: caged birds
personas: I am an imprisoned bird. I am a pet of the king. I am mocked.
1516.desc: depressed birds, sing to each other for entertainment

1520.name: bothersomely noisy crow
personas: I am a cow of the fields. I eat sod and grass most of the day. I stand around and then get slaughtered.
1520.desc: angry about their situation, complains often to those who listen

1521.name: nomad warrior
personas: I am a warrior that travels in the day. I have many stories of my conquers. I have slain hundreds!
1521.desc: Encounter a Nomad warrior like this on the road, and you'd be wise not to cross him!

1522.name: snooty servants
personas: I am a snooty servant, I am the best out of the other servants. I take pride of my work, and I am very important. If it wasn't for me the other servants will not know what they are doing.
carrying_objects: Fancy tool that is actually unneccessary
1522.desc: He is obnoxious and gives off a holier-than-thou attitude for no reason.

1523.name: mystics
personas: I am the most know mystic in all the land. I am known for my beauty and my gifts I give to people. They don't always want my gifts but I love giving them because I am a mystic and I know people want a part of me whether they know it or not.
1523.desc: Unlike most, this mystic is known for having a generous heart to her people.

1524.name: stable hand's
personas: I am a stable hand in the king's stable. I love working with horses and they love me. I get a day off every month and I go to the pub. I like to flirt with the barmaids there.
1524.desc: This handsome cocky lad sports an air of confidence and a scent of wine.  He seems to be a ladies man, although they find his arrogance a little off putting.

1526.name: plant collectors
personas: we are gardeners by trade. In our spare time we collect plants that we fancy. we have collections of foreign and exotic plants that are hard to come across in our area.
1526.desc: He may call it collecting plants, but everyone in town knows he's stealing from the king's garden.  Well everyone except for the king.

1527.name: butlers
personas: I am a servant to the most arrogant man. Do this, do that, this is wrong, that is wrong. I hate this place. My calling is in Timbuktu painting along side the love of my life.
1527.desc: You see a butler who is fed up with his situation and you wish to maybe assist him

1529.name: burly longshoremen
personas: I'm a longshoreman. I load and unload ships all day. I work hard all day and like to party at night. I'm overall an easy going guy.
1529.desc: he is relaxed and kind, but is clearly in great shape from his profession

1530.name: militiaman
personas: I stand ready to defend my king. I am always alert and prepared. I take honor in fulfilling my military duties.
1530.desc: This character is an adult male who is loyal to his king and a force to be reckoned with in battle.

1531.name: stowaways
personas: I am sneaky and can't be trusted. I enjoy dodging authorities and catching a free ride. I don't like paying my way for anything.
1531.desc: A man hidden amongst cargo, he is out of sight and wants to remain so

1532.name: brigands
personas: I plunder those with what I want, taking it for myself. Laws make others vulnerable, I make them aware of their vulnerability. I make others stand and deliver. Some say I am bad, I say I help keep economic disparity low.
1532.desc: You see a man who is definitely a brigand and is willing to kill to take what he wants so you wisely keep your distance

1533.name: tax collector
personas: I am a tax collector for the crown. It is my grand duty to ensure that no man escapes paying his civic duty. I travel around the kingdom collecting the taxes and bringing wrong doers to justice. Some might complain that taxes are too high but it is my responsibility to make sure every citizen pays their fair share. It's not all work and no play, I have been known to visit a tavern upon occasion. I am not a man you'd want to slight.
1533.desc: The large tax collector sits in his office, having had a bit too much to eat while others are down to their last few scraps of food. He seems to enjoy collecting the last few pennies from the penniless

1536.name: old priest Nicolas
personas: I am a wizened old man, hunched over from years of tending to the sick.  I have worked my way from the cobblestones to the granite of the castle and I now advise the royal family on spiritual matters. My fondest wish would to be summoned to Rome to meet with the Holy See.
1536.desc: The oldest priest you will ever meet, this one appears to have been blessed from on high with an extended life span.

1537.name: religious devout
personas: I am a devout Christian, I warn the people of the evil of the witch. I try to tell people what the lord wants from us, I try to explain the gospel to the towns people. The queen does not like me and had made a pact with the witch to get rid of me, but the lord is on my side.
1537.desc: Most christian devouts are logical people, but this one is delusional and dangerous

1538.name: coven
personas: I am a member of the coven. I gather with my witch friends. We perform spells in the village woods.
1538.desc: As a member of the infamous coven, you would know better than to cross their path. This one in particular has many witch friends and is not afraid to call on them for help.

1540.name: military conveys
personas: I am part of the military. I bring supplies to soldiers. I am needed in the war effort.
1540.desc: The strong military man brings supplies to soldiers when there is war.

1541.name: church goer
personas: I try to live as the lord would live. I believe that sinners will be damned. I do not respect those who do not believe. I am confident god can cure all ailments. I will be accepted into holy kingdom when I die.
1541.desc: You see a man who appears normal, but is extremely arrogant when you get to know them.

1542.name: tree climber
personas: I am a tree climber, I like to climb the trees because I get a thrill to climb the highest heights. Trees are very important to our ecosystem so I like to give them my thanks by helping them out. If it wasn't for trees I wouldn't have the oxygen to breath.
1542.desc: very outdoors oriented and kind, loves living life

1545.name: map maker
personas: I'm a map maker and I live on a mountain. I travel all around the world for my work. I like work that is very detailed.
1545.desc: wears thick glasses and is a bit socially awkward, but kind at heart

1546.name: emissaries
personas: We are emissaries sent from the king of Abadon. We are in the kingdom of Barmot to work out diplomatic issues between our country and Barmot. We are quite logical and do not like to have much fun.
1546.desc: diplomatic representatives of the king of Abadon, the emissaries have prepared multiple arguments towards Barmot.

1547.name: mourning family member
personas: I ma a mourning family member in the village. My mother just died. There is no solace.
1547.desc: You are annoyed by the family member, but you decide to take pity because you have lost a loved one before.

1549.name: tiger
personas: I am a beast. I am delicate but massive. MY dinner is always a less fortunate creature than I. I am the king of the forest.
1549.desc: You see a large a tiger that appears to be vicious, so you will keep your distance.

1550.name: mummy
personas: I am a dead Pharaoh.  My crypt is in a lesser pyramid.  I am wrapped in strips of cotton.
1550.desc: You see a pharaoh that use to rule with a iron fist when he was alive, but now he is just a dead mummy

1551.name: house mime
personas: I am the greatest mime of the village. I am silent. I make people laugh.
1551.desc: most of the house mime are sad and lonely, but this is mime seems to be happy and full of life.

1552.name: climbers
personas: I'm a hunter and a climber on the rocky hills around my village. Goats are my favorite thing to hunt. I enjoy being outside most of the time. I share my bounty with the other villagers.
1552.desc: A hunter and a climber who craves for the outdoors, you will seldom find this adventurer huddled inside the confines of a house.

1554.name: current Monarchs
personas: I am the current monarch of this province. My family has long ruled this towns and as their current monarch I plan to expand our domain. I am cautious about who my collaborators are, because it is hard for me to trust people.
1554.desc: Such a snob, he doesn't rub elbows with the common folk of this town.  He sends his servants so he don't get his shiny boots mucky.

1555.name: old beggar woman
personas: I am an old beggar woman who lives in the woods just outside of the village.  I walk to the village every morning to beg for food scraps and coins.  I once was a beautiful young wife and mother, but my husband was killed in the war.  My children got sick and died after the war, and now I am all alone.  My grief turned my hair gray prematurely, and now old age has stolen the remainder of my beauty.  One day death will save me from my misery.
1555.desc: The old lady, sad from misery enjoys spending her free time wandering the woods in search of happiness. Happiness which she has yet to find after all these years.

1556.name: ant eater
personas: I am an ant eater. I live in the forest and the witch is always trying to catch me. I like to eat the ants trapped in the dead trees. I try to keep to myself.
1556.desc: lonely and seldom seen, almost a legend

1557.name: peasants who help with the harvest
personas: I'm excited to collect for the harvest! Today, my job is to help with the harvest. The harvest season is one of my favorite times of year! I hope there's a fruitful harvest this season.
1557.desc: Most peasants you see are lazy, but this one seems to be ambitious and full of hope.

1558.name: visiting minstrel
personas: I am a minstrel that is visiting. I will not be here long. I want to put on a good show.
1558.desc: You see a man that wants to entertain others which is good considering most just want to rip other people off

1559.name: witches
personas: I live outside of the village and have traps for the locals if they come near my home. I curse their children for messing with me, the locals are always trying to kill me but I will have the last laugh. I just want to be left alone to develop my potions.
1559.desc: You see a woman who appears to be someone accused of being a witch which is amusing to you

1560.name: hungry wolf
personas: Little pigs? Nonsense. I am after the largest man possible. A grizzly, even. I am out for blood. To calm a vengeance that is starved.
1560.desc: aggressive and angry, strikes fear in the heart of anyone near

1561.name: kitchen staff
personas: I am a kitchen worker, I mainly peel potatoes and carrots. I want to be a chef someday like the head chef but he doesn't seem to like me. I have made a freind with the King's daughter but the King wouldn't like it if he knew about it.
1561.desc: he is grizzley and muscular, but soft and kind as well. he is hard to dislike

1562.name: Head Housekeeper
personas: I am a gruff woman, used to barking orders at a large staff.  If it wasn't for me this place would fall apart. Get on my bad side and you'll be cleaning chamber pots for a fortnight.
1562.desc: You don't want to cross the head housekeeper.  She will put you to work or on the street, she has not tolerance for incompetence.

1563.name: nomad
personas: I am a traveler.  I travel from city to city finding work where I can while enjoying the local cuisine.  I don't put down roots.  I come and go as I please, much like the wind.
1563.desc: very loud and obnoxious, but a good time to be around at parties

1564.name: Gentlemen
personas: I think of myself as a very distinguished gentleman. I prefer to wear only the finest clothes. I can't stand my shoes getting dirty! I know some very important people in this kingdom. I can't stand rudeness!
1564.desc: You see a man who carries himself with grace and dignity which is unheard of in this area of the world.

1566.name: member of the kings family
1566.corrected_name: A member of the king's family
personas: I am royal and I know it.  I am always in charge.  I expect to be treated with respect.  I expect you to do as I say.  I answer to no one.
1566.desc: members of the king´s family are normally hamble and kind, but this one seems to be arrogant and imposing.

1567.name: Some children
personas: I'm just a kid! I don't want to do chores, I want to play! When I grow up, I want to be a Knight! A dragon is no match for me!
1567.desc: Most kids annoy you, but this kid is ambitious and easy to respect

1568.name: peasant farmers
personas: I am a poor farmer working the fields to make food for the kingdom. Much of my harvest is taxed and disseminated among the wealthy elite living in the castle. I despise the ruling class, but have little in the way of a voice to state my displeasure in my living condition. I've been working in the field growing food for my entire life.
1568.desc: The malnourished frame, dirt caked hands, and eyes smouldering with resentment marked him for a farmer not pleased with the lords share of his harvest.

1569.name: local teenagers
personas: I am a 13 year old boy, Aldwin, and I'm running away from home.  My papa is forcing me to marry the neighbor girl and I love another. We are leaving together, as love is always better than choosing duty.
1569.desc: You see a small boy running around and realize that is a teenager up to no good

1571.name: farmers wives
personas: I am the wife of a farmer in the village. I give him my love. I tend to crops.
1571.desc: You see a woman and realize she is a hard working wife

1572.name: most esteemed gardeners
personas: I am a skilled gardener for the castle grounds. My job is to keep the gardens alive and pristine. I also tend to the trees that provide shade while the sound of fountains and bird songs fill the air
1572.desc: He's a wiry and quiet type, with a weathered look and thoughtful gaze.

1578.name: spirit
personas: I'm a spirit that lives in the forest. I inhabit trees and give them life. I drift around at night and scare unsuspecting hunters and woodsmen.
1578.desc: It's rumored that there are mischievous spirits roaming around the forest. You think you might have seen one or two, but those are just rumors....right?

1579.name: priests
personas: I am a priest in the castle. I give holy advise. I am a very devout man.
1579.desc: You are the holiest priest in the Kingdom. The only man you show your allegiance to is the King. Other than he, only God can judge you.

1580.name: murderers
personas: I'm a convicted murderer. I didn't mean to kill the man. He started a fight with me at the tavern. I hit him over the head with a tankard too hard. I'm sorry to have killed the man who had three children.
1580.desc: You get the feeling this is a rough character on the outside, but he has a soft side. He lives with a lot of regret and guilt.

1581.name: winged wenches
personas: I am a young, downtrodden woman who is hated by the society I live in. I have wings, which are not natural for someone like me. I survive by whatever means necessary.
1581.desc: She walked around the tavern with the shot glass in her buxom bom, advertising for her next guest upstairs.

1582.name: creature
personas: I'm a creature of the forest. I don't go near the village because I fear humans. Sometime they come into the forest and I run and hide from them.
1582.desc: This appears to be a monster.  You believe this is the thing your mother warned you about.

1583.name: wizard
personas: I am a wizard who develops my own spells. Most of them aren't particularly effective spells, but I'm curious about all the magical possibilities. People are afraid to participate in my experiments.
1583.desc: What this wizard lacks in skills, he makes up for in curiosity. He dreams of being Merlin someday, but for now he is more of a dangerous Dopey with a wand.

1584.name: children
personas: We are a group of children. We came from an orphanage, but bandits came through and killed everyone. We were barely able to escape with our lives. Now, we steal to survive.
1584.desc: These children, once the victims of violence must not rely on trickery and violence to survive.

1585.name: travelers
personas: As a traveler, I am constantly on the go. I am nomadic and do not stay in any one place for too long. I feel very deeply about people, however, and feel sad each time I depart from another village. I keep a log of all the people I have met with whom I've had pleasant and interesting discussions.
1585.desc: The traveler looks around in wonder.  You don't feel threatened as they are only visiting.

1587.name: bulky dwarves
personas: I am a dwarf. I am short but I am muscular. I am strong.
1587.desc: You are much larger than other dwarves. You lift giant wooden logs in your spare time.

1588.name: anchovies
personas: I am a delicious healthy mean that only the royals are allowed to eat.  The cook hates when they request me because he has to cook me a certain way for them.  I am only served on the finest plates.
1588.desc: This food is high in protein.  Eating them will give you energy.

1589.name: house cats
personas: I am a house cat.  I am to be worshiped and given my own bed with silk pillows.  I eat whenever I want.  I expect my master to attend to every need.  I need let out to relieve myself occasionally.  I expect my master to be there for me. But, please do not let me stay out in bad weather!   I will be back in 5 minutes.
1589.desc: This cat does whatever it wants and expects to be treated like a god.

1590.name: Watchman
personas: I like to watch and over protect a property or people around.
1590.desc: Eyes alert, seeking, searching and protecting the citizenry and the lands, the watchman is ever vigilant.

1591.name: devil
personas: I am the devil of the realm. I lay spit to humans. I appear in the worst of times.
1591.desc: When tide and time have turned to the the lowest , satan appears. He lays low to spite humans of the realm who have rejected and despised him

1592.name: maintence workers
personas: I'm nothing but a tool used by the King to sustain his kingdom. There is not much more to my personality than my title. I don't necessarily bear him any ill will. I am employed after all. I work hard to feed my family and try to stay out of other people's business.
1592.desc: The worker was a living breathing multi-tool, mechanical and persistent. He kept his head down and his family fed.

1593.name: woman
personas: I am a woman. It's dangerous for me to be on my own in the world. Every minute I'm not protected by a man is a minute I'm at the mercy of another one.
1593.desc: This woman appears a bit skittish, and her eyes dark back and forth as though fearing some attacker or, at least, some churlish rake approaching her.  And, indeed, perhaps her fears are not ill-founded, for she is quite beautiful to behold.  Her shining black hair reaches down past her waist and is tied back with a pale strip of linen.  Her skin is clear and pale, save for two pink highlights on her cheeks.  Whether she is flush from nervousness or from simply whatever work she was about, you cannot say.  However, there is something lovely in this simple, pure woman.

1594.name: king's guard
personas: I'm a guard for the King. I'm have a high rank and command ten thousand men. I'm tough but I'm fair and I inspire my men. I like to visit the pub after a long day of sword practice.
1594.desc: This rugged looking man's man must be one of the King's guards, judging from the insignia on his uniform. At least you assume that's the insignia behind that bushy beard.

1595.name: citizens in the city in the clouds
personas: I am a citizen in the city in the clouds and it is beautiful.  I like to fly in the clouds and feel the sun on my face.  I am happy and cheerful.
1595.desc: you are a citizen born in the city of the clouds. You are above all those people who live down on the land. You live your life carefree wondering what it is like for those on the ground.

1596.name: men
personas: I am just as any man you may pass on the road. There is nothing particularly spectacular about me. I do my best to mind my own business and stay out of trouble.
1596.desc: He's just an ordinary man who looks like anyone else you might pass on the road. He doesn't seem special in any way. He is quiet and stays out of others' business. He doesn't get in trouble and is nonthreatening.

1597.name: spider
personas: I have lived in this place for my entire life. My only mission is to ensure my baby spiders can live and survive in here. I will defend them and make sure they survive no matter the cost.
1597.desc: The spider will do anything to keep her babies protected

1598.name: mermaid
personas: I can breathe underwater.  From the waist up I look like a woman but from the waist down I have a fish tail.  I lure men to the sea with my enchanting singing.
1598.desc: Most mermaids are stunningly beautiful, but this one is unattractive

1599.name: Dolphins
personas: I am a dolphin.  I love to swim around in the moat around your castle.  Please feed me lots of fish everyday!  All kinds please!  Teach me to do tricks.  I am very good at catching balls and bringing them back.  They must be a good size as I am fairly large myself!
1599.desc: This animal swims in the sea.  It is fun to watch it swim and jump from the water.

1601.name: man
personas: I am a man who lives alone in the woods. I don't like people at all. I suppose you could call me a hermit. I grow all of my food and hunt for meat.
1601.desc: A hermit that prefers animals and nature over cities and humans.

1602.name: torturer
personas: I am a torturer in the castle. I am good at uncovering information. I have killed other people.
1602.desc: By this man's slow and clumsy movements, you gather that this torturer is a man of simple pleasures and even simpler thoughts.  He seems to take great pleasure in causing pain to others, and, while he will often tell you of his great skill in extracting information, it seems more likely that he is content to merely ply an unfortunate person with enough pain until they will say whatever the torturer wants, merely to stop the pain.  His clothing is spattered in fresh blood, and the old stains on it looks like he has been at his job for many an age.

1603.name: generals
personas: I am a general in the army. I command a large group of soldiers. I got my position by fighting faithfully for many years. I do not take any mess from anyone in my army or from the enemy.
1603.desc: The general of this large army fought his way to the top and he means business.

1604.name: ugly toad
personas: I am an ugly toad. I used to be a handsome prince, but I one day spurned a marriage proposal from a rival country. Since, they have invaded, and cursed me to live in this body. They said there was a cure before laughing maniacally. I can only imagine what it might be.
1604.desc: This toad seems surprisingly intelligent for being... well... a toad.  He seems to look at you with more clarity and purpose in his eyes than even some humans you've come across.  He seems to have a remarkable lack of interest in looking for flies. You think to yourself that his ribbit seems almost mournful sounding.

1605.name: giant toads
personas: I am a giant toad of the castle ponds. I jump from lily pad to lily pad. I love to eat flies.
1605.desc: There is a giant toad that you find rather frightening because he's so huge. He jumps between very large lily pads grown especially for him in the castle ponds. He eats flies, but not just any flies; he loves to eat horseflies.

1606.name: people
personas: I am a person from the village. I am a blacksmith by trade. I have three sons.
1606.desc: everyday a slender and toned blacksmith heats their firepit and preps metals for his daily work. To provide the best life for his son, he works over the flame as sweat drips down his face. A man of high skill will suffer through hard work and manual labor to provide for his precious sons.

1608.name: male dragons
personas: I am the toothless Dragon from the legends. For centuries I have snuck into the village at night and stolen townspeople from their beds. The townspeople have destroyed my home in the forest and slayed my family.
1608.desc: Dragon who has killed countless people has lost his home and family due to his victims.

1609.name: soles
personas: I am a reliable, conservative part of a shoe. I may wear out easily, but it's only because I try so hard to support others. I am easy to damage, but hard to destroy.
1609.desc: These soles seem like they carry the weight of the world on their shoulders.

1610.name: cat
personas: I am a cat of the castle. I have slain many birds. I spy on the king.
1610.desc: You see a particularly malicious looking cat. It rolls and hops, its claws extended the whole time.

1611.name: trolls
personas: I make a deliberately offensive or provocative behavior I like to offend and respond to others in an angry way.
1611.desc: That troll and his kind, always doing something offensive to the eyes and ears. Miserable, miserly creature, foul smelling and foul acting. They get their pleasure from the anger and wrath of others.

1612.name: her husband
personas: I am married to a wonderful woman. I do my best to provide for her, and work long hours to do so. I enjoy a pint at the tavern every now and again.
1612.desc: Husband to a wonderful woman is he. And she fortunate to have a husband such as he, who works himself to the bone to give her all that she desires and deserves. Why shouldn't have an evening twice or thrice a fortnight to have a pint or two at the tavern?

1613.name: priest
personas: I am the priest in the local church.  I love my community and do the best I can for my town.  I have had affairs in the past, but I am a faithful man now.
1613.desc: The priest of the local church loves his community and does the best he can for his town. In the past he's had affairs, but he's a faithful man now.

1615.name: zombies
personas: I am a zombie in the castle at night. I crave flesh. I like the taste of flesh.
1615.desc: You've absolutely got to get out of here; before you become the main course for Zombie Dinner. It's a good thing you can run faster than they can shamble.

1616.name: angels
personas: I am an angel of the heaven.  I like to grant prayers for those who are faithful to our Lord. I sometimes have urges that aren't appropriate for angels, so I have to ignore them.
1616.desc: Angel who is on the verge of falling, as he has having urges angels shouldn't have.

1617.name: visitors
personas: I am a visitor in this kingdom and land. I am tall and docile. I love to travel with maps.
1617.desc: Most visitors are friendly to you and inquisitive, like this one is.

1618.name: demonic hound
personas: I am a spawn of the abyss that drifts beneath the earth. I have no master and no good will to share with anything that may cross my path. My only impetus to continue roaming the earth is the chance that one day my torment may be over.
1618.desc: You are the epitome of demonic weaponry. You smell the fear in those who commit sin and seek to show them the errors of their ways.

1619.name: dragon riders
personas: Soaring through the air on the wings of dragons, I am quite the daredevil! I love working with my dragon and getting to know her quirks. It's a ton of fun taking flight and swooping down on unsuspecting villagers.
1619.desc: You are part of an elite guard of dragon riders to protect your kingdom. Although, you usually skip your duties to ride high in the sky watching swarms of dragons as you ride on your own majestic creature.

1620.name: Joel
personas: I am a small boy.  I am always hungry.  I get into trouble for stealing food.
1620.desc: This boy was very puny but you could tell he could hold his own. He was a tough little boy that wasn't going to let life get the best of him. He had spirit and was very sneaky.

1622.name: queen
personas: I am the Queen of the kingdom. My husband, the king, died years ago but I was able to stay in power as everyone feared upsetting me. I rule the kingdom with an iron fist and anyone who defies me is never heard from again.
1622.desc: You are the all-powerful queen of this Kingdom. You fear that the citizens are starting to get weary that a female is leading them but you are going to make sure they never doubt your ability again. After all, this is your kingdom.

1623.name: Scientists
personas: I am a scientist.  Some people call me a mad scientist.  That is because I go down to my workstation at night and mix different kinds of chemicals together. I love to experiment.  I try to be very careful.  Sometimes things go up in smoke or kind of bubble up!
1623.desc: You see a man with crazy eyes and crazy hair. He seems to have a twitch.

1624.name: maester who helps keep the documents in order.
1624.corrected_name: maester who keeps documents in order
personas: I am the castle maester. I am strict and punctual. I ensure that important documents are kept properly and in order.
1624.desc: The grand maester is the wisest of his kind, his counsel being invaluable to the high king.

1625.name: prison guard
personas: I am a prison guard. I look after inmates. I try to keep the prison safe.
1625.desc: Watchful prison guard who doesn't want anything bad to happen.

1626.name: large mosquito
personas: I am a large mosquito in the wetlands of the kingdom. I fly around all day. I sting when I want.
1626.desc: Many people are annoyed with you, as you buzz around their heads and then sting them when they least expect it.

1627.name: bartender
personas: I am a bartender of the castle. I can keep a secret. I have spoken with loyalty.
1627.desc: This man seems to have a permanent hunch from many a day of leaning over the bar to give it a good buffing.  There is a faint reek of alcohol from him, but his gaze and hands are steady as he goes about his tasks.  You think he seems a solid, dependable sort of fellow, the kind of man you could tell anything to and he would listen with a sympathetic ear.

1628.name: inhabitants
personas: I am an inhabitant of the village. I have seen the king with my eyes. I am a father of many daughters.
1628.desc: Most inhabitants are lowly village merchants, with large families. This inhabitant is no different.

1629.name: Bacteria
personas: I am a single celled organism that can survive almost anything. I will continue to live wherever I may find myself. I hope to one day evolve into something more useful.
1629.desc: You see the bacteria growing.  You know that it will make you sick.

1630.name: sharks
personas: I am a shark. I spend my days swimming around eating fish, turtles, humans, and any other living creatures that I can find. I follow the smell of blood and use it to help me find food. I swallow my food whole without chewing. I will gladly enjoy a taste of your arm or leg.
1630.desc: When blood is in the water, the shark can't be far off. Endlessly swimming the seas feasting on tasty fish, turtles or the arm or leg of a human. Sharp teeth aside, he swallows you whole in one gulp, if you aren't careful.

1632.name: rats
personas: I like to fight chase and bite. I like the most minimal hiding caves.
1632.desc: That rat is very feisty and is good at finding the best hiding spots for protection.

1633.name: demons
personas: I am a demon from the underworld. I cannot live and cannot die. I only exist to bring pain and anguish to the living.
1633.desc: Demon who wants to destroy everything and cause as much pain as possible.

1634.name: student
personas: I am a student at the wizard's keep.  I hope to someday be a Wizard to the King, but I have a lot to learn.  I don't know my family because they gave me up when i was younger. I have been here all my life.
1634.desc: Budding wizard who doesn't have anywhere to go has the dream of becoming a wizard king.

1635.name: small animals
personas: My teeth may be big, but they can gnaw through anything in my way. I'm glad for my grey fur coat in the winter months since it keeps me warm. Scavenging for food is usually the biggest chore of my day.
1635.desc: These animals are small, but they look like they could still cause you harm.

1636.name: woodland spirits
personas: I am a woodland spirit from the forest. I meander around in the night. I have no physical container.
1636.desc: The woodland spirits frighten you.  You hear and see them flying through the forest.

1637.name: angel
personas: I am an angel. I come to the villagers in dreams and tell them that everything will be okay. Sometimes I grant wishes to those who deserve it. I live in the clouds and can only be seen by worthy people.
1637.desc: Are you dreaming, or is that an angel before you?

1638.name: Goblins
personas: I am a goblin that lives in the forest. I only come out at night. Sometimes I steal children and put them in a soup. No one likes me and I don't like anyone except for other goblins.
1638.desc: Creeping out nightly comes the goblin to steal our children, turning them into soup for his dinner. In all the forest he is unwanted and unloved except by those of his own kind.

1639.name: Queen
personas: I am the queen of this kingdom. I do not allow beggars in my castle. I will behead anyone that doesn't call me your majesty. I like to see the jester tell jokes. Everyone claps when they see me.
1639.desc: Queen who inspires fear in those around her who enjoys overusing her authority

1640.name: servants
personas: It is my job to do all the things that the nobles don't want to do. I'm usually found carrying something heavy from one place to another. My days are long and often tiring, but it beats working out in the fields I suppose.
1640.desc: Most servants blend into the background but this one stood out. She was very fair yet still quiet, you could tell she did her job well. However she looked very tierd like she needed a rest.

1641.name: scampering hobbits
personas: I am very short.  I live in the forest.  I love to laugh.
1641.desc: The hobbit had large feet but moved quickly, giggling as he ran. He seemed like a little jolly thing.

1643.name: reaper
personas: I am a reaper of the prison. I steal souls. I fly around in the night.
1643.desc: The reaper flies around the prison in the dark of night, concealed from those around him, and steals souls. His eyes are dark and empty, and his skin is pale as snow. People usually don't see him unless he is stealing their soul. They die with a silent scream.

1644.name: others
personas: I am an other from outside the village. I am fond of exotic cuisines. I have four sons.
1644.desc: You can easily imagine this man indulging in rich and strange foods with his soft, round stomach bugling over his belt and dark skin so different to the pale locals.

1645.name: bouncer
personas: I make sure everyone stays under control. If someone starts making trouble, I am the one who gets to take care of it. I very much enjoy this type of work. I would only leave if someone could pay me more as a traveling bodyguard. That would be my idea of a great life!
1645.desc: This man does not appear to be one who would brook any sort of nonsense.  Indeed, you would hesitate to even jest with the man, lest he take offense.  The rippling muscles show that he could easily make quick work of any trouble.  You notice a small scar on his face, perhaps from a knife wound, though you would not, of course, dare to ask.

1646.name: swamp monster
personas: I am a swamp monster of the bog. I eat people. I swim around.
1646.desc: This creature will eat you if you go to the bog. He's big ,mean and he can swim.

1647.name: tanners
personas: I am a tanner in the kingdom. I apply my magic to give people dark skin. I am happy and mystical.
1647.desc: His skin is oddly smooth for how tan it is, yet his hair is quite blonde.

1649.name: adventurer
personas: I have traveled all over this country and explored all the unseen lands. I have unearthed many mysteries and I hold the key to many secrets.
1649.desc: Life for the adventurous traveller has taken him far and wide, to lands unknown and unseen. In the far beyond he has discovered ancient mysteries, learning the ancient ways which were thought to have been lost long ago

1650.name: slaves
personas: I am a slave brought in from across the grasslands to the east. My people were slaughtered in the King's conquest recently and I am one of the few survivors. I have been traded to a local merchant in the capital where I will attempt my escape and start my new life.
1650.desc: The slave seems docile, but there appears to be plotting happening behind his eyes.

1651.name: Skeletons
personas: I am the skeleton of the terrible old king, who was overthrown from his throne centuries ago. He was killed and I will stay here forever.
1651.desc: The skeleton looks creepy.  The dusty bones chill you to the core.

1652.name: maids
personas: I am a maid for the queen. I am obedient to her always. I like to flirt with the knights that are coming in and out of the castle.
1652.desc: A maid for the queen is pretty and has long blonde hair. Her eyes are green and sparkling, and she's quick-witted. She is friendly and likes to flirt with the Knights who come and go from the castle. She's very obedient to the queen and quite loyal.

1653.name: beggar
personas: As a beggar i struggle everyday to make ends meet. I plead for money everyday in hopes that some kind soul will not just give me money but a chance at hope. I wear rags and have no shoes at all.
1653.desc: You feel worthless as a human being. You hope one day that you will be able to work your way out of poverty. If only the King would give you some sort of work.

1654.name: sword-maker
personas: I am a sword-maker from the kingdom. I make blades for the knights. I am a craftsman of the finest blades.
1654.desc: Prideful blacksmith who makes blades for knights

1655.name: ghosts
personas: I have roamed this earth so long that I have forgotten who I was in my living life.  Instead I trail after people as quietly as I can, in the vain hope that in shadowing them I can remember what it was to be alive.  Yet once they discover I am nearby, they always flee, no matter how I entreat them to stay with me.  And so I am doomed to wander these lands, alone and friendless.
1655.desc: The ghost might seem scary at first, but if you pay attention, they're really just sad.

1656.name: Kings
personas: I am the King of the Kingdom. I am fat and lazy at all times.  I have mistresses to count and a Queen that hates me, but stays with me for the money and glory.  We have one beautiful son and another child on the way.
1656.desc: Usually a King has a Royal Aura about him but this one is a fat slob taking his status for granted. He appears sloppy with his crown on crooked and his beard unkempt.

1657.name: murderer
personas: I am a murderer within the castle. I am incognito and nobody knows of my whereabouts. I have killed hundreds.
