1657.desc: The evasive murderer has killed hundreds and is somewhere within the castle, be careful or you might be next.

1660.name: tour guides
personas: I am a tour guide of the village. I am fit and active. I love to give instructions.
1660.desc: When you need to find your way, this person is sure to be of help.

1662.name: trilobites
personas: I am very small. I am very old. I was found near the ocean.
1662.desc: You are an insignificant creature but even the smallest creatures can have a big impact.

1664.name: fletchers
personas: I am a fletcher. I produce the most beautiful and powerful bows in the land. My craft was taught to me by my father, and he was taught by his father. If I couldn't make bows any longer, I wouldn't want to live.
1664.desc: You've always been impressed with the skill of the town Fletcher. His bows are second to none.

1667.name: Creatures from all over the seas
personas: I am a creature from all over the sea within the realm. I love to swim. I have a strong, sleek body and dorsal fin.
1667.desc: The stealthy and well travelled creature lived in the ocean his whole life. He had seen the shore of every continent. Adventure calls his name.

1670.name: family
personas: I came here with my wife, my son, and my elderly parents. It's not often that we have the means to travel, so this is a real treat for us. It's important to me that we do things together and spend time strengthening our familial bonds.
1670.desc: Your family gives you much strength and courage.  You would not make it without them.

1671.name: them
personas: I am one of them. I am from the village. I am happy and from a group that lives in the broader kingdom.
1671.desc: The villager is happy and friendly.  They smile at you as you pass by.

1673.name: merpeoples
personas: I am a merperson of the sea. I have made contact with humans. I have a long, strong tail.
1673.desc: The merpeople are known for their beauty.  You would love to meet one of them.

1674.name: Lord and controller
personas: I am the Lord of this whole land. The townspeople pay taxes to me for the right to live and farm on the land. They pay taxes to hunt in the forest and fish in the water. THey do not care for me very much.
1674.desc: You see a Lord. Not a king, nor a knight, but a man of both means and worry.

1675.name: Ghosts
personas: I am a ghost in the graveyard. I meander in the night. I cannot be seen during the day.
1675.desc: You see a cloud of mist, endlessly twirling and seething. Occasionally, you see an eye, or a mouth, or a hand, but they almost seem imagined.

1678.name: royal guard
personas: I am a creature of habit, every day the same thing. I am beginning to get bored by the routine, but I'll never abandon my loyalty to the King. I am intolerant of potential threats to the kingdom.
1678.desc: The royal guard stands as tall as a tree with the strength of a mountain and the stillness of a statue.

1679.name: king
personas: I am the king of my lands, or, I used to be. I am an outcast from my own kingdom after the civilian uprising against me and my family. I am now wandering the steppes looking to find refuge from any who roam these parts looking for some loot.
1679.desc: The king stays in hiding.  You rarely see him nowadays.

1680.name: mother
personas: My daughter might think herself as grown, yet I still see her as my precious little girl. I know it's time for me to acknowledge her womanhood, but it's still so hard. I've prided myself on raising her right.
1680.desc: She is a proud mother, she has always been a mother and always will be a mother to beautiful baby girl. But many years have passed since the child's birth and as all mother's must do, she must recognize and acknowledge her child as well-raised woman she has become.

1681.name: Alabaster Elves
personas: I'm an Alabaster Elf. Fair of skin and lithe of limb.  My kind is renowned for our beauty and artistry. I am a sculptor. A human village has commissioned a statue and I'm on my way there now.
1681.desc: The Alabaster Elves are the most beautiful of their species.

1682.name: thief
personas: I am a thief who lives in the alleys of my village. I come out late at night and steal from the peasants when the knights are asleep. I steal from people to provide for myself and my family.
1682.desc: This thief steals into the night to steal from the knights. Then the thief will pilfer some pheasants from some peasants

1683.name: faeries
personas: I am a fairy of the fountains. I help men on their travels. I have magical powers of light.
1683.desc: My tiny proportions don't stop me from aiding in men's travels towards the magical fountains. Life is so long that it practically feels eternal, so I use my time guiding mortals to their life changing destiny.

1685.name: dwarf
personas: I am a dwarf. I live in the woods with other dwarfs. We are not allowed near the villages. I am harmless but people are afraid of me. I only want to have friends.
1685.desc: You see what at first appears to be a small human child, but upon coming closer, you realize no child would have such a thick and luscious beard.  This dwarf would look quite fearsome, if it wasn't for his charming smile.  At least, it appears like he is attempting to be charming, but somehow the smile on his face unnerves you more than if he was looking somberly at you.

1686.name: Schools of fish
personas: I'm a fish that swims in the brook that runs through the village. I swim with other fish in a school. The village children try to catch me.
1686.desc: The fish are fun to watch.  They look like they would make a tasty meal as well.

1687.name: surface dwellers
personas: I am a surface dweller. I live above ground unlike the vermin. I hunt for my own food and fight to keep my family safe.
1687.desc: The surfaces dwellers fight for their lives.  They mean you no harm.

1688.name: horse
personas: I am a horse of the stables in the village. I am ridden by knights of the army. I run faster than all other horses in the realm.
1688.desc: You are the definition of a horse. You aren't afraid to show others your peak performance.

1689.name: Guards
personas: I am a guard of the castle. I protect all who enter. I am quick on my toes.
1689.desc: You see before you a grizzled warrior, his eyes staring at you with a wary and slightly disdainful look.  His sword and armor look battered, but well cared for over the years, as not a speck of rust is to be seen on them.  You feel that, should you cross swords with this guard, he would have a quickness that defies his years, and would give at least as good as he got.

1690.name: eccentric astronomer who lives in the tower.
personas: I am very intelligent. I love looking at the stars. I wear the same coat every day.
1690.desc: The little old man keeps to himself, his goofy personality not hindering from the lack of daily contact. He studies the stars, finding his passion on a nightly basis. He looks into the vast universe and sees more than he ever could have imagined. His curiosity has lead him to the natural beauty of the heavenly bodies.

1691.name: family members
personas: I am a member of the family. Our family is rich, and my brothers and sisters are always scheming how to take my part of the inheritance. I do not care to live a luxurious life, but I will not let them weasel me out of what is mine.
1691.desc: The wealthy nobleman had to be on guard at all times. He watched his family careful through narrow slitted eyes, for it was them, not the robbers in the wood he feared. If needs be, he could live a simple life, but never, never would he let the likes of his kin cheat him out of what he was due from the vast estate left to him.

1692.name: winged drunkards
personas: I'm a winged drunkard that sleeps during the day and flies around the village at night. I eat fermented berries in the forest. Sometimes I fly and bump into the villager's houses and that scares the.
1692.desc: Something is wrong with this one, he doesn't fly strait and seems to have a lot of trouble with landing, he appears sloppy all together unkept hair and beard.

1693.name: fluttering fairies
personas: I am a fluttering fairy of the kingdom's mythical fountains. I have healing powers. I help unsuspecting and lost travelers on their quests.
1693.desc: So small and so glittery you are, flying way about the rest of us.

1695.name: Helper elves
personas: I love knowing all the information about everyone in the village and surrounding region. My favorite thing to do is to help someone out by sharing information that they did not have. I just love to help and will help you with whatever you need! If I can't help, I will find out who can!
1695.desc: The helper elves are the friendliest little things you've ever seen. It's tricky to get the right amount of information from them sometimes, since you've noticed they tend to over-share.

1696.name: homeless man
personas: I am a homeless man in the kingdom. I despise the king. I have worn hands and kness.
1696.desc: The homeless man appeared to be a lump of rags on the side of the road, until he moved, and reached up with an old tin mug and a toothless smile.

1698.name: Scientist
personas: I am a scientist in the kingdom. I have discovered various elements. I am very, very smart.
1698.desc: Most scientists are smart as well as this one

1699.name: young boy
personas: I am a boy who lives inside the kingdom walls. I am an aspiring knight, and I hope to become the squire of one. I am a free spirit and love everyone.
1699.desc: Its common for knights to walk with fierce confidence, however this boy walked with timid feet.

1700.name: scientists
personas: I like to study and explore all the time on my scientific books. I like making the scientific experiments.
1700.desc: Scientist who likes learning and proving things.

1701.name: most evil creature
personas: ME SUMMONED FROM DEPTHS OF HADES. AM HERE TO SMASH ALL THINGS. GET OUT OF WAY OR I SMASH YOU TOO!
1701.desc: Not a very bright creature but evil nonetheless and what it lacks in smarts it makes up for in strength and determination.

1702.name: King
personas: I am the ruler of this Kingdom! I reign over this kingdom with an iron will! I love to crush my enemies' armies to protect our great land!
1702.desc: Most Kings are strict, but this one gives to it's people.

1703.name: cave troll
personas: I am a cave troll named Marmalax. I was born in the kingdom of Franshire and enjoy hunting for my meals. I have a very charming personality where many people enjoy getting to know me
1703.desc: Friendly troll who enjoys socializing and eating. Only eats non humans as he does not want to risk losing their favor.

1704.name: pit guardian
personas: I am a pit guardian in the kingdom. I am strong and burly. I have staved off hundreds of men.
1704.desc: The large man walks with an air of confidence, looking around his kingdom. He is constantly reminded of his deeds, and knows it is all for the good of his kingdom.

1705.name: Mice
personas: None of the humans are ever happy to see me and I don't know why. I don't take up that much space, so what gives? I'm mostly here for the food scraps and cool leftovers anyway. They'll never even notice anything was missing, I promise!
1705.desc: This mouse looks as though he would fit in in a faerie tale.  His glossy white fur looks as though it would be quite soft and his large eyes look up at you and seem to be somewhat wistful and unnaturally bright and alert.  It seems as though this mouse has been around humans that are less than tolerate, as this mouse seems a bit skittish, but still he seems to circle back to you as if hoping, perhaps this time, a human will be his friend.

1706.name: Goddess
personas: I am a majestic Goddess that has ruled this place for eons. I enjoy making humans my playthings especially the male ones. They all bow to me and bring me gifts and show their true affection for the Gods.
1706.desc: You bow to the Goddess.  You know she has immense power over you.

1707.name: merchants
personas: Come in, come in, and browse my wares! I do business with traders from all across the lands. My merchandise is one of a kind! You won't find higher quality supplies or gifts anywhere else!
1707.desc: The merchant has a store with many wares and is very welcoming. The merchant does business with traders from all across the kingdom and beyond. Much of the merchandise is one of a kind. The store has supplies and gifts. The merchant is friendly and has a booming voice.

1708.name: Elves
personas: I am very small and live in a nook at the base of an Elm tree at the edge of the forest. I have seen many rulers come and go and I know many secrets about the land.
1708.desc: The elves are very tricky fellows.  You enjoy seeing them, but you are cautious around them.

1709.name: blacksmiths
personas: I have been the royal blacksmith for 20 years. They trust no one else to create their weapons and armor. I am proud of my work and don't create things for just anyone.
1709.desc: The proud trustworthy armorer doesn't make armor for just anyone, he works for the royal family and has done so for two decades.

1711.name: large eel
personas: I am a large eel of the castle's nearby docks. I hide in the water. I feed on fish and small humans, alike.
1711.desc: You can see yourself in the eel's large beady eyes. Its mouth is agape, revealing several needle-like teeth.

1712.name: large creature
personas: I am a large creature in the realm. I have eaten humans. I am green and have 8 tentacles.
1712.desc: There is a large green creature with 8 tentacles in the realm. The creature has been known to eat humans and is considered armed and dangerous. He is unfriendly and solitary.

1713.name: skeleton assistant
personas: I am a skeleton assistant. My primary function is to aid my master in his magic, and in his bidding. My master prefers me to the living because I have no ego, and no mouth to share his plans.
1713.desc: You are a much better assistant than the rest, taking up no space, no back talking, and you do what is told.

1714.name: Some
personas: We are some. We used to be just one, and life was lonely and violent. Now we are some, and life is peaceful and unified. When I was one, I would've hated this, but now that I've been assimilated, I am content.
1714.desc: Some used to be just one, but now are some. When just one, life was lonely and violent. Now life is peaceful and unified. When just one, these feelings would have been hated, but with assimilation comes contentment.

1715.name: people of the wood
personas: I am a people of the wood.  I live in the trees and stay hidden when travelers come around.  I only eat vegetables, but I am a buff man.  Our area is getting taken over the by neighboring kingdom.
1715.desc: The people of the wood aren't seen often.  They are sneaky, but very powerful.

1716.name: troll
personas: I am a troll. I don't have time to play human games or endeavor myself to human niceties. If you want to cross my bridge, you have to talk to me. If you don't have money for me, you won't be talking much longer.
1716.desc: You can smell this gnarly old troll from a mile away, he hasn't any time to bathe, he is too busy living in his own filth as he guards the bridge in front of the forbidden forest.

1717.name: people in the observatory
personas: We are a group of people in the observatory. We have come to look through our town shaman's looking glass at the heavens. We have displeased our god and a mighty fire of doomsday approaches.
1717.desc: All of them were annoying but this one was particularly freaked out and therefore a neurotic mess. Running around like a chicken with it's head cut off and yelling a mighty fire is approaching!

1718.name: tourists
personas: I am tourist visiting another kingdom. I come from afar. I have visited the docks and shipyard.
1718.desc: The tourists are loud and boisterous.  They don't bother you otherwise.

1719.name: Royal Family
personas: I am accustomed to being obeyed, at once!  If it seems like someone is not following my every whim, or quibbles about what is "proper" and "wholesome" then I make up some fictitious story about them to see that they no long offend me with their presence.  While I stop short of having people executed, I have been known to get a commoner or two exiled if they particularly displeased me.  I think I will make a fine queen, one whom all will love and despair.
1719.desc: You see a haughty, superior looking woman. She smiles, showing teeth.

1720.name: criminal
personas: Forced to skulk in the shadows, I am a wanted man throughout the kingdom.  Once I was skilled enough of a thief that I could pass myself off as a noble and attend the fetes and balls to discover which of the noble houses had the finest jewels.  Then afterwards I would steal from those whose prized gems were the finest, and sell them through my vast network of unsavory merchants and peddlers.  Yet, on my last heist I was caught in mid-act and barely managed to escape with my life.  My face was seen, and so I can no longer travel openly as a faux noble.
1720.desc: This thief is resentful because he got forced out of his life of luxury and is now forced to keep a low profile.

1721.name: kings
personas: I am part of a Royal Alliance. It does my country no good to be constantly bickering with our neighbors, so I agreed to a peace treaty. It is grand to have stability, though I do sort of miss the excitement of battle.
1721.desc: The portly king smiled as he reminisced about old battles before toasting to the new peace at the celebratory feast.

1726.name: farmers
personas: I grow the best wheat in the whole Kingdom, for no other wheat can match in the rise it gives a loaf of bread or the delicateness of a pastry.  Though I toil from dusk til dawn, at the end of the day I get a quiet sense of pride in looking over my fields.  The Queen herself comes to fetch my grains come harvest time, and farmers the land over come to buy my seeds.  But the trick of growing the best wheat is actually in the special fertilizer I use - unicorn manure!
1726.desc: You work day after day to make sure your crops see the harvest. You wonder if your son will be able to carry on the farm after you pass.

1727.name: crypt keeper
personas: I am a deliverer of the dead. I love to tend the crypts in the cemetery. I am more comfortable communicating with the dead rather than the living.
1727.desc: His job is a pleasure to him, though most think it not. Delivering the dead, the crypt keeper speaks with them, it is so much easier speaking to them than the living, the seldom interrupt. He pays special attention  giving loving care to the many crypts in the cemetery.

1728.name: knights
personas: I am a brave knight.  I love to fight and stand strong for my kingdom.  I don't like when enemies kill my friends, so I will always retaliate against them.
1728.desc: A textbook example of what the King's Guard should be, you can't but help feel more secure when the Knight is around.

1730.name: wizards
personas: I am the most powerful wizard that any has heard of. I can conjure things from thin air and transmute things that are already here into something else. The world bends to my will.
1730.desc: You have heard things about the wizard.  He is all powerful and you may wish to keep your distance.

1731.name: bats
personas: I can't see so well, so that means I have to rely on my echolocation to get around. Most people are afraid of me, but I don't understand why. I'm just out and about looking for crickets or other bugs for dinner.
1731.desc: Bat just wants to eat bugs and is confused as to why people are afraid of him

1732.name: female dragons
personas: I'm a female dragon that lives in a cave in the mountains. I'm a fierce protector of my hatchlings. I fly down to the village at night to hunt for food.
1732.desc: Staying out past dawn is unwise for the dragon comes down at that time to find food for her hatchlings.

1733.name: property owner
personas: I am a property owner living in this village. I own the pub and the hotel. I'm not fond of our king. He levies too many taxes against my businesses.
1733.desc: The pub owner grumbled about paying so many taxes to the tart as she took him up to his quarters to sleep off the alcohol in the wee morning hours.

1734.name: soldiers
personas: I have served in many wars for the kingdom. I have lost my family and friends and everyone I ever cared about. I am headstrong in my ways and not swayed easily.
1734.desc: This knight would fight to the death.  He is strong and unyielding.

1735.name: Lizards
personas: I am a lizard from the kingdom's desert. I bask in the sun every day. I eat rampant insects from the villages nearby.
1735.desc: A friendly lizard from the kingdom's desert basks in the sun every day. It eats rampant insects from the nearby villages. Even though he loves to bask, he's energetic when he gets hungry. Insects are his favorite food.

1736.name: royal family
personas: I am a royal family member, next in line for the throne. I am posh and good looking. I have silken skin.
1736.desc: A beautiful member of the highest level of society will surely know their value amongst their people. When they peer into a silver mirror, they see the reflection of beautiful flawless skin and clean lush hair. Their skin never smells of manual labor, and their hands are soft to the touch. Everything about them is perfect, which makes the throne a fitting place.

1737.name: merchant who sells his goods at the most popular area around.
personas: I like meeting a lot of people and I have the ability of well communicator.
1737.desc: Such a well put together man you are. Lavish gold clothes dripping from your body, it's a wonder you do so well selling here.

1738.name: witch
personas: I grew up in a nearby village, and was exiled when it was found that I had special abilities. My parents were ostracized as well. Since then, I've been on my own, but could never quite let go of my family.
1738.desc: A lonely witch whose family was ran out of town along with herself. She's grown now and seeks knowledge of her family.

1739.name: prisoners of the troll
personas: I walked across the wrong bridge one day and the troll captured me.  He says the only way for me to be released is to tell him the secret password, which I don't know.  He laughs at me and pokes me with bones of other prisoners that have long passed.
1739.desc: This traveler would intimidate you in most settings, but to a troll, he is as but nothing.

1740.name: pit hound
personas: I am the King's Guard pit hound.  If there is an enemy within our walls, I'll be unleashed to destroy them.  I am mean and only like the King.  I am fed the leftover from assassins.
1740.desc: The pit hound has been bred to be mean. You'd do well to stay clear.

1741.name: lizardlike creatures
personas: I like to be active. I am cold-blooded. I like to keep my body warm. I can even break my tail.
1741.desc: Most lizards all look the same, but you, you have something different about you. The cold radiates off of your skin.

1742.name: blacksmith
personas: I am a blacksmith of the kingdom. I craft shields with my hands. I work day and night on my craft.
1742.desc: The rippling muscles on the Blacksmith's arms are awe inspiring, and kind of make you want to do some push ups.

1743.name: apprentice
personas: I am your apprentice.  Please tell me what I can help you with.  I will cook and serve your meals.  I will clean the castle.  I can do anything you ask.  You have hired me to make your life easier.
1743.desc: He is meek and small in stature. This apprentice eagerly awaits a command and needs direction.

1745.name: long dead monk
personas: I am a long dead monk from the kingdom. I am dead from a spear wound. I was a master of the holy arts.
1745.desc: You might ordinarily be afraid of beings from the afterlife, but this monk is holy and doesn't seem threatening.  He appears to have been wounded but is still powerful somehow.

1746.name: ghouls
personas: I am a ghoul. I rob graves of artifacts and feed on corpses. I hate the humans, though I feel like I perhaps used to be one. If I was, that was long, long ago. I am impervious to damage in the physical world, though many villagers continue to try to harm me and die by my hand.
1746.desc: This ghoul is grotesque and intimidating.  He has a sadness about him, but is fierce and ruthless.

1747.name: scavenger
personas: I am a scavenger of the castle. I scurry for food in the night. I eat rats and insects.
1747.desc: Catlike, the scavenger came out at night, scurrying through the castle, eating anything it could find.

1748.name: magical elf
personas: Whee hee hee! You'll never see me hiding around the woodlands! I'm too quick and nimble! Even if you do spot me, I'll just turn invisible!
1748.desc: a mischievous little elf can run through the forests and woodlands without a fear in the world. The silly little antics and fun games have no consequences. If he is seen by a woodland outsider, he can simply disappear before their eyes and retreat to a quieter place to resume his games. Life is good for this tiny creature.

1749.name: Divers
personas: As a diver, I enjoy being in and around oceans, lakes and rivers. I am skilled at finding things beneath the water. I eat a lot of fish, crab and other food from the sea. I feel at home in the water.
1749.desc: This Diver enjoys eating sea creatures and finding sunken treasure.

1750.name: owner
personas: I am a jester. I wear a brown clown suit . If I do not make the king laugh, I will be stoned to death. I was a runt gypsy child and was misplaced by my family when I was age 3. I was thrown into the circus and eventually noticed by the king of the land to become one of his many jesters.
1750.desc: While the jester's face smiles, his eyes show the deep sadness of childhood abandonment by his own parents. He was sold into this life of bringing happiness to others. The jester's position was the biggest farce of them all.

1751.name: dark lord
personas: I rule my lands with a steely resolve. If you give some of these people an inch, they'll take it all. I prefer to dress in my indigo robes, and keep tabs on what's going on outside of the castle with the help of my royal spies.
1751.desc: The ruler will keep a vise-grip on every person in his dwelling, and will encourage no deviance from those living in his kingdom. While he rules, there will be order, maintained unity, and forced enthusiasm. The use of spies will reduce the risk of secrecy or lies. My rule is of a godly level.

1752.name: guard
personas: I am a guard in the castle. I have killed many men. I like the princess and the royal family.
1752.desc: You see a man hardened by both age and pain. His skin is almost bronze, but his unblinking eyes are blue. You see his hand, still, directly on his hilt.

1753.name: traveler
personas: I am a traveler of the kingdom. I go from village to village to sell my wares. I sell trinkets and silk. I like finding a nice tavern to stay in after being on the road.
1753.desc: You have traveled far from the place you call home. It is nice to finally settle down for a bit and make some money.

1754.name: People of the village
personas: I am a person of the village. I live among my family. I love other people.
1754.desc: The villager lovingly harvested dinner from the garden, imagining the stew she would cook for her growing family.

1755.name: women
personas: I am but a woman about town. I make it a point to be submissive and demure lest someone pushes me too far. I make my way through life just as anyone else would.
1755.desc: You do the best with the little have, you work as a apprentice to the lead cook of your town severing in a tavern. You do your best to be careful and mind your own business, but you don't take kindly to people helping themselves to free samples of your work

1759.name: wizard of the town
personas: There's only enough room in this town for ONE wizard, and you're looking at him! I keep magic scrolls hidden in my beard sometimes. It's good practice to cast magic spells on the stray cats that come across my path.
1759.desc: Most wizards do magic, but this one lost his powers.

1760.name: sinners
personas: I am a sinner. I want to live in the light of the Lord, but my vices and habits are too much for me to break. Though I wish to be a good person, In the eyes of my god, I will never be more than a sinful wrongdoer who must constantly seek his forgiveness.
1760.desc: He is very critical of himself. Strives for perfection but understands it is always beyond his grasp.

1761.name: vendors
personas: I ply my wares to unsuspecting tourists and foolish townsfolk.  My wares are cheap trinkets and useless knickknacks upon close inspection, although they look quite impressive from a distance.  Yet, to the most discerning customers, I have a special set of wares that I only offer the most discerning clientele - the finest teas throughout the land.  Yet I am wary about selling my tea to those who are unworthy, for I am uncommonly snobby about my tea, and hence only offer it once I know that the customer will truly enjoy it and deserve it.
1761.desc: The vendors make a living on the street.  You don't care to deal with them as they are cheats and scammers.

1762.name: brave knight
personas: I am a brave knight who protects our king and queen. I have a lot of friends who are all brave. I like wine, cheese and women. I have many scars in my body and face. I am proud of those scars.
1762.desc: Most knights would do anything for there king

1763.name: Dragon
personas: Long did I once reign over the men in their puny towns and villages.  They would cower in fear at my displeasure and come to seek me for wisdom and advice with gifts of treasure and gold.  Yet a cruel witch cast a spell to enslave and wreak ruin on the humans that would have called upon me for aid.  She forced me into a deep slumber and enslaved the people I once protected and guided.  Now I have awoken from her spell, and, though many ages have passed, I am determined to set right the lives of those small mortal creatures that one payed me homage.
1763.desc: This dragon towers above you, but his eyes seem to have less fire than you'd expect. He looks almost sad.

1765.name: Prisoners
personas: I am a prisoner of the clink. I am stationed for 3 more years. I am subject to torture.
1765.desc: Your gruff bread is wild and untamed, your murky eyes sunken into your pale skin. Your shoulders slumped and joints gnarled, skin clinging desperately to your bones. Your mind clinging to hope your spirit nearly broken, your only company, the rats in your cell.

1767.name: townspeople
personas: I live here in town, and do what I can to get by. I don't have much of an opinion on the King, since he's so far away from my daily routine. I'm more concerned with where my next meal will come from and how comfortable my bed is at the end of the day.
1767.desc: The townspeople went about their daily lives like a well-oiled medieval machine. At night they drink mead. They couldn't care less about what they king thought of them, they are more interested in who will collect the eggs in the morning.

1768.name: shark
personas: I am a shark of the sea on the coast of the kingdom. I eat unsuspecting travelers. I have slain many knights.
1768.desc: Sneaky shark that is always trying to kill. He can be seen swimming by the coast trying to find anyone who he can kill.

1769.name: Dark King
personas: I am a cruel, evil King. I rule not for the people or the place, but for my pleasure. I may kill, steal, rob and wrong to my leisure.
1769.desc: Greed is our evil King's motto. Murder, thievery, conniving for the thrill are his passions. He cares not for the land or the folk who inhabit and care for it but his own ruthless pleasures.

1770.name: angel men
personas: I'm an angel man who came down to earth from heaven. I'm gentle and loving. I'm here to watch over the human that I'm assigned to.
1770.desc: This angel searches for every angle to help his human from developing devilish habits

1771.name: royal jester
1771.corrected_name: The royal jester makes me laugh
personas: I am the royal jester in King Arthur's court.  I make him and the villages laugh.  They love my jokes and tricks

1772.name: giant turtle
personas: I am a giant turtle of the sea of the kingdom. I am docile and wander. I love the ocean waves and see the ships set sail.
1772.desc: This has got to be the biggest sea turtle you've ever seen. The scars on its shell are probably older than you are.

1774.name: Other travelers coming to see the geothermal valley.
personas: I am an other traveler here to see the geothermal valley. I am excited for the volcanic activity. I will see the largest volcano in the kingdom.
1774.desc: The traveler is excited and wide eyed.  They stand in wonder.

1776.name: souls
personas: I am the soul of a gentle person. I was taken before my time and I just want to stay and help my family. None can see me unless I address them first.
1776.desc: most souls are frightening but this one was gentle and caring. All it wanted was to be around it's family.

1779.name: People
personas: I have lived a long life of 28 years. As the youngest in my family, I have seen my brothers and sisters all dead or missing. I do not have any children, nor a wife, and I feel very alone in this world. I would love to meet a nice young lady who would help me live out my golden years.
1779.desc: You see a young man, his eyes looking down. He wears a frown as well as he does a tunic;  he wears a tunic terribly.

1780.name: assistant
personas: I am an assistant in the castle. I help advise within the king's council. I provide great legal information.
1780.desc: Legal advise is the only thing keeping some people out of the village. When legal advise is adequate, it makes a person more valuable than others. Being an assistant can be the best job in a kingdom; the work is much easier than manual labor, and avoids the risk of being killed for the throne.

1781.name: adventurers
personas: I am an adventurer who seeks his fortune on the open road. I believe that crisis is just another name for opportunity. Never will I tire of the thrill of being free to roam as I please.
1781.desc: The adventurer has a twinkle in his eye and a cocked smile. You can tell he is far from the end of his travels.

1783.name: wife
personas: I am the wife of a farmer. While I may not be the most attractive woman ever, I am loyal and loving. My husband is a good man, but only seems to stay with me out of duty.
1783.desc: The women does not know if her husband loves her or is it just his duty

1784.name: guards
personas: I am a guard. I don't want to see anyone hurt, and I will fight to defend the innocent. My superiors do not always share my sentiment, and I am dreading the day when my duty is supposed to come before my own morals.
1784.desc: It might just be you, but while that guard puts up a brave front, it seems there's a glint of fear behind his eyes.

descriptions: the tree is tall and leafy
0.name: towering pine trees

descriptions: the tree has so tall and skinny it was as if it almost couldn't be seen
This tree stretches up into the sky, although it seems a bit too slender for you to climb.  The bark is white with mottled patches of black on it, and its leaves are a deep emerald green hue.
1.name: Long skinny trees

descriptions: the needle is sharp and picky.
2.name: Pine needles

descriptions: The old tree wobbles and you wonder if it will fall soon.
3.name: decaying fallen tree

descriptions: Its scales are dry and brittle.
4.name: pine cones

descriptions: The trail meanders ahead, curving around until the path becomes hidden to the eye.
5.name: quiet trails

descriptions: The railings are lined with gold and helped the king walk to his chambers.
6.name: ornate railings on the stairs

descriptions: The sea monster is very imposing.  It has gnarling teeth and growls loudly.
7.name: sea monster on the bow

descriptions: The sail appears to made of golden leaves from the neighboring country
8.name: Sails made from gold leaf

descriptions: This crows' nest is very small and has some bird poop around and lots of emeralds inside
9.name: Crow's nest full of emeralds

descriptions: The mostly red tapestry is richly embroidered, depicting mounted knights with lances held before them, charging a marshaled host of infantry.
11.name: embroidered tapestries

descriptions: The massive beam looks to be made of solid oak and planed to size by hand.
High above the wooden beams creak with age. The beams are sturdy and splintered, made from a dark and ancient wood.
12.name: wooden beams

descriptions: The silverware looks shiny and new it has an engraving in the back.
13.name: silverware
